{"product_id": "733180", "page": 1, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2018-01-16", "text": "Disclaimer: Special thanks to the developer\nfor providing me the key and the opportunity to explore and give an honest review of this GameBoy style platformer.\nPixel Art: 2/5 (Graphic glitching!)\nImmersion: 2/5 (Slow movement & bad controls)\nGameplay: 2/5 (Poor level design))\nControls: 1/5 (Very poorly implemented)\nValue: 1/5 (Asking way too much!)\nDifficulty: 4/5 (Artificially difficult due to controls)\n--------------\nOverall 1.6 (Difficulty always excluded)\nWhen I first saw this game (read the few reviews...all positive), I really thought and wanted to like this game, but it has WAY TOO MANY issues!!!\nI have to believe that other positive reviews are friends of the dev trying to make this game much more than it is :(  I only experience disappointment and pure artificial frustration :(\nFirst of all, my pet peeve, is someone trying to make a game look and feel retro by adding graphic glitches!  I HATE this more than anything and will seldom give a game the light of day that uses this very bad and clich\u00e9 technique!  You cannot jump without the game glitching, which annoys the hell out of me!\nAs simple as the graphics are, it either seems they make the load times extremely slow to make the game feel old, or it is very unoptimzed!  Far cry and every other advanced game loads faster!\nThe graphic design was endearing for about 60 secs, then all the issues overwhelmed me :(\nThe hitboxes are very poorly configured, where you can touch baddies, only just not their core.  It is hard to know when you will be hit or not.\nMovement is slow, attack is laggy and jump delayed :(\nControls are very BAD, very restrictive!  You can attack or jump but not at the same time, so if there is a fast action where you need to attack, then quickly jump to avoid a projectile, forget about it!  The attack action takes so long to complete, until you are able to jump again.\nFor example, during second boss fight (library), you want to quickly attack, but you have to end up counting your shots, then prematurely stop shooting, since you will not be able to avoid his attack unless you are standing stationary and ready!  Not nimble at all!\nAlso, trying to jump down from platforms, you press down and jump, but it only works half the time (jumping up once, before allowing you to jump down).\nPoorly designed baddie actions that can be unavoidable (really detracts from joy)...I enjoy tough as nails, but don't like illogically challenging.  Put into situations where attacked from all sides without a way out.\nThe difficulty curve feels like a sine wave, rather than anything gradual to learn, enjoy and grow with :(\nI would have loved a better experience with this game, I only think it was released before being ready and did not have enough QA, game play and feedback :(  It might be enjoyable to the person who developed it, but I don't think they asked its players what they thought.", "hours": 1.3, "compensation": "Product received for free", "user_id": "76561197964345647", "username": "Sazo", "products": 853, "early_access": false}
