{"product_id": "733180", "page": 1, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-11-29", "text": "Disclaimer: I am an amateur platformer who received the game for free to help beta test.\nAs of writing this review I have 23 hours on record, and I still have not beaten this game. I am right at the end, but just need some more practice. And thankfully, every time I die I know exactly why because there is no randomness! (I died because I suck.) But with every death, I learn and learn and improve and keep getting farther and farther with every battle.\nAre you a fellow amateur platformer? Do not be discouraged! It is indeed challenging, but it is oh so rewarding and fun.\nA seasoned veteran? I garuntee you will fall in love with this game. There is so much potential for speed running this game, and you might even get caught up on a few unique twists to the norm.\nThis game is so expertly crafted and quite surprisingly, genre-bending. As soon as I thought I understood what the game was about, BOOM, it redefined itself. Over and over again. I constantly kept discovering things and had to put my controller down because I was so awestruck and genuinely excited.\nMusic? Excellent, original, and catchy while keeping true to it's 4-bit and retro roots.\nGraphics? Awesome and imaginative 4 bit graphics. It is surprisngly immersive.\nStory? Yeah, there is a surprising and quirky story in there. And it isn't half bad. I am interested in how it's all going to tie up in the end. (No spoilers.)\nFun? YES. It is so satisfying to destroy space aliens.\nConclusion: This game is worth so much more than $10. Highly reccommend this title for gamers of all skill levels and backgrounds. In the words of a famous infomercial host \"Make like N'Sync and BUY BUY BUY!\"", "hours": 23.0, "compensation": "Product received for free", "username": "MajkSoldier", "products": 208, "early_access": false}
