{"product_id": "718650", "page": 1, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2018-01-18", "text": "This is one of those cases I wish we had a third choice but yes and no.\nThis game has potential and is fun, but ATM it only runs in 1080p and quite a lot of systems are not yet implemented. I expect this game to become really interesting, but I can't recommend to play at the current state unless you're in deep love for indirect control RTS (like Majesty) or have a lot of time in your hands. If you do have that time, tough, it's already a smooth ride: I encountered 0 crashes, bug or glitches - kudos on the tech quality assurance.", "hours": 1.4, "user_id": "76561198013728428", "username": "Brigador", "products": 361, "early_access": true}
{"product_id": "718650", "page": 1, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2018-01-16", "text": "I never really review games but I liked this one and decided to give an honest review on the good and bad. I love the creativity and how it looks and the music. I get absorbed into it without realizing and when I glance at the clock suddenly an hour or two has gone by. The game is pretty fun though at the moment lacks a goal beyond spread and win. The game almost forces you to keep building which forces you to scramble for resources and as a map has a very finite amount and each island has a very small amount even if you sit it to high eventually you get to a point where you find all you have done for an hour or so is move an island and drain it or create one and hope it has what you need....hopefully as the game develops the work more on that....I love base building games and this one has a ton of potential ...interested to see more races join more development of the races and (hopefully they adjust the resource system to make it more manageable.", "hours": 6.4, "user_id": "76561198219522632", "username": "CanaWolf", "products": 9, "early_access": true}
{"product_id": "718650", "page": 1, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2018-01-14", "text": "If you enjoy building empires or city building games, this is a good one. Haven't encountered any bugs as of yet and the game is quite dynamical and well balanced for an empire building game!!!", "hours": 8.4, "user_id": "76561198014820430", "username": "Volk", "products": 213, "early_access": true}
{"product_id": "718650", "page": 1, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2018-01-12", "text": "I really enjoyed this game! Like many of the other reviews mentioned, the graphics and the music were both amazing. But also like many of the other reviews mentioned, the game is currently a little short of content.\nSome pros:\n- The theme is awesome. The game play is really smooth and I like how the resources are balanced. You don't see common people hang around everywhere, which makes the game appear clean. The only click-able units are fighting units, which you would occasionally want to click on in order to check on their status.\n- I like how population translates directly into money instead of being mediated by resources. When there are too many resources to manage I tend to get confused and anxious. In this game, fundamentally, you just have to balance building huts (population) and assigning farmwork. Other resources are important, but won't break your kingdom (as long as you have a market). I didn't need to worry about, e.g., my citizens not having jobs but still consume food (a big problem I had back with age of empires).\n- Graphics! Music! Again, huge promises.\nSome cons:\n- As much as there are a lot of elements existing in the game, the strategy ended up being quite linear. The best attack strategy seems to be tornados, which also ends up being cheaper (if you buy mana at market) than investing in fighting units. I spent a lot of time and resources having my wizards, knights, and marksmen learning all kinds of skills, having them ride on rivens and eagles, spamming them with healing health, only to have them die to enemy ground units super quickly. I won my first game by using 3 tornados to destroy enemy castle. It would've taken me at least another 3 hours if I had to do it with only fighting units. I like the idea of directly participating in fights like using tornados, but the uselessness of my units was kind of a bummer.\n- Relatedly, unit commands are a little too simple and the AI doesn't seem very good. I couldn't find a way of sending one unit home (the one everyone's attacking and is about to die) while letting others continue. I also never really observed my wizards use their tornados.\nBottom line:\nAgain, super impressed by this early access already. Looking forward to future changes.", "hours": 3.4, "username": "July7", "products": 40, "early_access": true}
{"product_id": "718650", "page": 1, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2018-01-07", "text": "Well for what it's worth the game is a lot of fun. Although a lot of content seems to be lacking at the moment (being still in alpha stage that is to be expected) it does deliver a promise of a great game. I would recomend it, even though it is a bit expensive for the stage it is in right now.", "hours": 3.7, "user_id": "76561198004781496", "username": "Guybrush_Threepwood", "products": 12, "early_access": true}
{"product_id": "718650", "page": 1, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2018-01-07", "text": "Keep it up guys! This has so much potential! great idea for a game. Love it so far, going to keep smashing away at it.", "hours": 57.8, "username": "Gman", "products": 79, "early_access": true}
{"product_id": "718650", "page": 1, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2018-01-06", "text": "Early Access game, so take that into consideration.\nInteresting approach to RTS, nice graphics.  At this point, not certain of how much replay value there will be.\nAlso, some of the core mechanics seem to push a player into a particular play mode, whereas I like games that allow you to be a turtle, or be agressive, or be balanced.\nThere's a knowledge tree powered by scholar points, but the earn rate for scholar points is far too low to be useful at this point in game development.\nCompared to other early access games, Driftland seems farther along.\nUnfortunate that Steam restricts you to an up or down vote, because I would give it a medium, worth watching rating, but I can't recommend it yet.", "hours": 5.4, "username": "Whereupon Grimble", "products": 306, "early_access": true}
{"product_id": "718650", "page": 1, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2018-01-03", "text": "It uses an elegant concept that allows for a lot of fun empire building. It's got a lot of things to keep track of, but a very well designed UI keeps it from feeling like you're having to micro-manage. This is clearly a game that the designers put a lot of thought into. Despite being a game in progress, it's already enough of a full game to enjoy and a very good deal for the price. I can't wait to see what else is added.", "hours": 11.4, "user_id": "76561198052189930", "username": "blayzekohime", "products": 35, "early_access": true}
