{"product_id": "738600", "page": 1, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2018-01-02", "text": "As a first timer computer gamer, this experience was challenging and interesting. I played this game on a desktop computer. The finger technics were new to me and there were quite a lot to learn before I figured out how the movements work.\nAfter all, the game was interesting with various parts and the music suited well to the environment.\nSpace and the spaceship are fascinating and thought-provoking.", "hours": 2.4, "user_id": "76561198798568356", "username": "katikas", "products": 1, "early_access": true}
{"product_id": "738600", "page": 1, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-27", "text": "The experience takes more than 20 minutes for sure - at least from me:)\nAlso I got inspired somehow about the Mars invasion generally with this VR app and its post Earth theme. Also had to watch one series about Mars from Netflix and the movie \"Martian\":)\nAnyway, you'll face some challenges with the space shuttle (no spoilers here!) during the journey. But don't panic, with a common sense you'll survive.\nThe controllers work pretty ok, I'm using HTC Vives with Windows 10, GTX970 graphics card. I have not tried the multiplayer mode yet.", "hours": 2.2, "user_id": "76561198150138703", "username": "FI_lthrn_1958", "products": 52, "early_access": true}
{"product_id": "738600", "page": 1, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-15", "text": "I enjoyed playing this game and I think and hope that VR games will attract more players as VR headsets become increasingly available. I liked the post-acopalyptic outer space theme, which is very current and continues to inspire people as we try to make a more sustainable world that can sustain life now and in the future. This game seemed to explore what could happen if people fail to do this. The asteriod scene was thrilling and several of the tasks onboard the ship explore everyday obstacles/situations that need to be resolved in challenging circumstances in space. All in all this was a very interesting indie game.", "hours": 0.8, "username": "Renikka", "products": 2, "early_access": true}
