{"product_id": "597590", "page": 1, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-03", "text": "Not what I was expecting... it\u2019s even better. It's a tower defense game with cool mechanics that looks good and definitely has the B-movie feel to it.  You are stuck in the floor and must stop the bugs from getting to you. You are equipped with toys and items found in your basement. You can deploy toy soldiers / bug spray and more. Your main weapon is a nail gun but be careful you have limited ammo. For $5 right now it's a steal with 15 levels of game play, multiple difficulty settings and an endless mode you will get 10+hours of game time before you know it. If you miss the sale no worries the $8 price tag is well worth it.\nHere is some game play footage.", "hours": 6.7, "compensation": "Product received for free", "username": "Logicbomb", "products": 1136, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "597590", "page": 1, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-02", "text": "For the price this is a pretty well put together and charming game. Good one for parties and people terrified of spiders:) First few levels are very easy once the bugs start coming from all over it gets challanging. Graphics are clean and work well in VR.", "hours": 0.4, "user_id": "76561198116304836", "username": "Aerowyn", "products": 393, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "597590", "page": 1, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-01", "text": "I always see people commenting that there is no AAA games for VR, me on the other hand I love indie titles they seem to have much more freedom to made any game they wish and so many indie titles are hidden games waiting to be found and for such a low price too and this is truly one of them, such a great game with awesome game play, I have only played it for an hour and I have recommended to all my friends who have VR and I also recommend it to you too.\n10/10 a true gem of a game", "hours": 0.9, "user_id": "76561198016565355", "username": "Dal1Dal", "products": 789, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "597590", "page": 1, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-01", "text": "You are playing as someone who is having a nightmare and you are stuck waist deep in the floor, an evil spider queen is sending her hatchlings (and various other insects) to you and you need to defend yourself with various object that you collect in your environment.\nThe basic gameplay is okay (it is fun to watch the little toy soldiers walk over every surface and fight the spiders), it is what it is: a wave shooter with some tower defense elements, but very few games had me as motivated to not fail as this game. I don't have that much of a problem with spiders in real life but the nasty black creatures in this game make me quite nervous and I'll be fighting pretty hard to keep them away from my face.\nOnly gripe I have with the game is that the angle some of the weapons are using is wrong, the grip of the nailgun etc. should properly align with the grip of the Vive wands.", "hours": 0.4, "user_id": "76561197971140093", "username": "TheCze", "products": 999, "early_access": false}
