{"product_id": "734580", "page": 2, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2018-01-15", "text": "Game has a really good concept, large scale desroy the enemy base game set in ww2 with base building and looting mechanics. But in its current state writing this review (it is in alpha) the game is not good. The looting is slow and non intuitive, there is no crafting system yet so you can't make a scope, or a piece of armor or, or a backpack(!). The hitreg in the few fights that I had was TERRIBLE. In one instance there was a guy that was literally afk. I go up to him shoot him once in the head with the springfield, 25 damage. Ok... do it again 25 damage... again 25 damage... then the forth shot didn't do any damage at all then the last shot killed him. Either headshots don't work, or there's a massive hitreg issue. The next time I shoot someone with the m1919 and it does 70ish damage from far away, so I take it into close quarters and shoot a guy (saw blood and heard the impact) about 4 times and didn't see a single damage marker pop up. That's the point where I stopped playing but would be very willing to give the game another try in the future; but I just can't reccomend it in its current state.", "hours": 0.5, "username": "Link Freeman", "products": 222, "early_access": true}
{"product_id": "734580", "page": 2, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2018-01-15", "text": "Unique concept, intuitive mechanics, but the essentials for a shooter are barely there! Netcode is abysmal with constant phantom hits, lag and rubberbanding. Gonna keep an eye on it, as the WW2-tower defense-looter shooter is very appealing!", "hours": 18.6, "user_id": "76561198188498707", "username": "Gustave Le Bon", "products": 33, "early_access": true}
