{"product_id": "734580", "page": 2, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2018-01-14", "text": "A diamond in the rough, I'd say. A F2P World War 2 Multiplayer game with crafting mechanics. Buggy, but fun, and has a lot of potential considering it's in Alpha.\nPROS:\n+ Free\n+ Small download size (less than 1 gb)\n+ 100 player servers\n+ easy to understand/play\n+ crafting is decent\n+ destructible environment\nCONS:\n- Windowed mode seems buggy\n- Server lag issues & Lack of server variety\n- Rough graphics and UI\n- Little variety starting off\nConsidering it's in Alpha, BattleRush has a lot going for it. If the bugs are ironed out, the UI is updated and cleaned up, and if there can be fixes for servers, it could be great. It could also really use weapon variety for players starting off. There's not much choice when you begin playing, which is a definite downside.\nI say give it a shot, give it feedback, and see how it grows. It's got my attention.", "hours": 1.0, "username": "Daniel Valtameri", "products": 118, "early_access": true}
