{"product_id": "427100", "page": 7, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "text": "In this Update, you'll receive some new content and overhauled features free of charge, e.g. the new Sound Engine, which we've been working on for the last quarter. The \"break\"-mechanic has been improved, and also the A7 has been fully reconstructed. Prepare yourselves for a racy and tuneful Roller coaster ride!\nShould you have active repaints subscribed from the Workshop, the game start - after you clicked on \"Start Game\" in the Main Menu - might take a bit to load, due to the changes we made to the texture memory of mod repaints, in order to additionally improve texture streaming.\nAs always, we would love to hear your feedback to this update! Hit this link\nto start typing...", "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "718650", "page": 2, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-28", "text": "if you are a big fan of old RTS games like \"age of empires\" , \"age of mythology\" , \"rise of nations\" , \"american conquest\" or even \"battle realms\" or in some cases \"stronghold 1/2\" and you are looking for a game like those in 2017/2018, this is obviously NOT the game you are looking for.no matter how much they claim, this game is NOT similar to our beloved RTS games.let me give you one simple example, YOU CANT SELECT YOUR TROOPS. but if you are looking for a cool RTS game which has its own way of gameplay, then you can give it a try (but still i think you have to wait a bit more longer,because right now the game has only 2 races and 1vs1 AI)\nthis game is kinda fine in it owns style,but the only reason i give thumbs-down to this game is, they claimed so much that this game is gonna be like our memorable RTS games, but it dosent feel like those games AT ALL", "hours": 1.3, "user_id": "76561198247591520", "username": "YeaYeaWhatever", "products": 8, "found_funny": 2, "early_access": true}
