{"product_id": "427100", "page": 8, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "text": "We've made a huge change to our update process, thus there will be no patch this week. However, you can access and download beta patches starting now on.\nThis function is available by accessing the\nin your Steam library under the tab\n. We'd appreciate your feedback in order to deliver more convenient updates for all of you in the future.\nYou'll find the previous updates in the category\n.\nThis update includes several GUI improvements and fixes.\nPlease submit your feedback on our official forums\nto maintain organization, that'd help us alot. We really appreciate every single piece of feedback.", "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "427100", "page": 8, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "text": "The beta phase of patch 1.11 has been finalized. We've been able to fix some additional bugs thanks to your feedback.\nIn addition to that we've been able to fix two AI issues. The AI won't drive into trucks trailer anymore. The braking lights flickering while waiting at traffic lights has been fixed.\nWe've also updated the standard repaint of both MAN Lion's Coaches according to the international design. You'll still find the old release repaint in the customization labelled as \"Fernbus Sim Release\" and another new repaint can be found in the list as well. A neutral white repaint with Flixbus decals.", "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "427100", "page": 8, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "text": "A new BETA Update for Fernbus Coach Simulator is available for testing!\nWe would be glad to get your feedback to make this release as stable as possible again. ou can find a tutorial on how to download game betas on Steam here:\nhttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Uu_ZBRBLDMU\nIn this Update, you'll receive some new content and overhauled features free of charge, e.g. the new Sound Engine, which we've been working on for the last quarter. The \"Break\"-mechanic has been improved, and also the A7 has been fully reconstructed. Prepare yourselves for a racy and tuneful roller coaster ride!\nHit this link to our forums\nto send us feedback and bug reports!\n---\n: This is a BETA Update. Please note that this software can cause technical problems and make your computer system be instable. Please only use beta versions if you really know what you\u2019re doing.", "early_access": false}
