{"product_id": "734580", "page": 3, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2018-01-12", "text": "Yes, the game is a bit buggy but it's HUGE multipayer and WW2 setting made me fall in love with this game. Matches can sometimes be realistic. And If you get into close combat the fights can be goofy. You can craft vehicles and march the huge battlefield the game has to offer. The map is massive! But overall I recommend it to those WW2 lovers.", "hours": 6.2, "user_id": "76561198263764077", "username": "\u2720DemoLex\u2720", "products": 26, "early_access": true}
{"product_id": "734580", "page": 3, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2018-01-12", "text": "TL;DR: Flawed, confusing, and maybe a little p2w, but free & pretty fun. Definitely a lot of potential. If it seems interesting to you, give it a try. The download is relatively small.\n\nA lot more fun than it looks! It's got good mechanics, definitely a solid ground to build from, and I'm excited to see where this game goes.\nA couple complaints, though.\n1. It's a little early to have DLC to the extent that it has, and as a relation to that getting the non-paid classes seems to take forever.\n2. Optimization, really would love to see improvement in this area, I get around 30fps, which considering the graphics and everything involved I think could be better. An option to turn the grass off would be nice as well, and could also help with this issue.\n3. Crafting requires products of trees and rocks. However, you have to pick just one tool to start with, so you end up having to scavenge for specific resources or looking for another tool. I'm not super crazy about that, but it's not a huge issue either, because the scavenging is fairly reasonable, and the other tools aren't impossible to find by any stretch.\n4. It's a bit hard and confusing to get into, the guides are a bit hard to understand imo. As well as this all the crafting seems to be done at the factory, so I don't know the point of the other places marked on the maps. Improved guides would be much appreciated.\n5. I'd really like to be able to hold RMB to aim down the sights, as opposed to being stuck with a toggle. More of a nitpick than a serious complaint, but I feel it's valid.\nOverall, it's more fun than I thought it would be, and I'll probably be playing it quite a lot. I hope it succeeds. I may at some point purchase the DLC to support the developers, but as it currently stands and with the way it is implemented feeling relatively pay-to-win, I don't think I will quite yet. I think they'd actually sell more if they consolidated DLCs into cheaper less numerous DLCs. Certainly, I'd be more inclined to buy.\nBut on the whole, for a free game with a relatively small download size, I don't see any reason why you shouldn't at least give it a go. :)", "hours": 25.0, "username": "mynameisMatthew", "products": 191, "early_access": true}
