{"product_id": "718650", "page": 3, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-26", "text": "This game has a lot of potential but right now has so many balancing issues its not a very fun game. You can completely ignore the RTS elements if all you want to do is win. The AI won't do much either to fight back and your own troops are very frustrating to control right now.\nI would say, wait on this game. There is real promise with the spell system and shaping the map as you play. Right now there just isn't much of a strategy game here. But if they keep working on it, I'm sure I'll change my review to recommonded.\nLink to full review:", "hours": 9.8, "username": "Moose Hugger", "products": 304, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": true}
{"product_id": "718650", "page": 3, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-24", "text": "Good game. Just one thing, when you unlock a chest with a skill that your soldier (in case you only have one) already has (and you don't have a second soldier active), the chest will dissapear and the extra skill is lost.  Thanks", "hours": 19.3, "username": "Elchardus", "products": 131, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": true}
{"product_id": "718650", "page": 3, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-23", "text": "I like it, I do, there is just not enough to it at the moment. Now I know this is EA, so there will be many changed and I will update things accordingly.\n- The islands are interesting, although they do limit the amount of interaction with other players in early game.\n- There is no real threat apart from some easily dispensable flying beasts, as you are not connected to other players.\n- It feels like the game plays itself and my job is to build the buildings it requires to do that.\n- Not a fan of the orders, again it feels like my job again to to get the gold to fund the game playing itself.\n- No score screen (I may have missed it?). I earned those stats...\n-The inverted floating main menu guy thing really bugs me.\nTLDR - It has potential (Yeah, that again), does not feel like the game needs me to play.", "hours": 7.6, "user_id": "76561198070579310", "username": "Merkeh", "products": 77, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": true}
{"product_id": "718650", "page": 3, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-19", "text": "Great Game, it's at a state serveral EA titles never arrive, feels like a perfect mix from serveral RTS Titles mostly a mix Netstorm and settlers 7 with flying island ang magic. GREAT :D", "hours": 6.2, "username": "medic@work", "products": 98, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": true}
{"product_id": "718650", "page": 3, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-18", "text": "As it is right now I can't recommend it. Hold on and wait. HOWEVER, READ THE FOLLOWING:\nThis game has a solid and very interesting core. Another reviewer mentioned Majesty, and this is a very good comparison. However, the game has a few problems. First of all it feels like there is not a lot of depth. As it is right now the island system feels kind of gimmicky. It's still a nice spin on things, though. The problem is that you only have three different heroes: Knights, rangers and mages. In addition to three classes of flying units you can get if you find their nests and capture (\"tame\") them: Ravens, eagles and dragons (each one better than the following). These can be mounted by said heroes. I played one game and I didn't really feel there was much replayability involved. Simply rush the nests, put heroes on the fliers and then zerg the opponents castle. However, I feel there is some potential here, and I hope it'll get better over time. I'm also looking forward to the campaign update. If it gets better, I will update my review for sure.", "hours": 1.6, "username": "XartaX", "products": 485, "early_access": true}
{"product_id": "718650", "page": 3, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-16", "text": "has potentual but graphics were not good compared to the ram it took too play it an there were a lot of lulls in the real time play. it was a decent concept but needs a lot of polishing...i mean a lot. i give it a thumbs down for now I hope it changes but the trend that game makers are carving today i doubt it very much.", "hours": 0.4, "user_id": "76561198032121810", "username": "double0proph3t", "products": 138, "found_funny": 2, "early_access": true}
{"product_id": "718650", "page": 3, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-16", "text": "EXCELLENT CONCEPT! EXCELLENT GAME! Please stop crashing though... -.-\nOkay folks, it's your friend Rascaldees here with another astonishing report from the Capital Was-... what's that? We can't do that because Bethesda is a sue-happy company and would probably sue us for doing that? They might sue us for saying that as well? And it's even worse because I'm still typing everything that I say?\nOH! Well, my bad then George!\nSo ladies and gentlemen (get triggered) here are the pros and cons of this game:\nPROS:\n1) Excellent concept. I LOVE this game and personally? I HATE most fantasy games of all types. I think fantasy is over-done. However this here game? It's easy enough to pick up and easy to overcome most obstacles while still being challenging enough to stay engaged. Also, floating islands are just badass.\n2) The controls are really easy to pick up. I can't stress to developers how important USER INTERFACE is. Quite frankly? The graphics could be the best in the world with the best story and the best... you get the idea. But if the UI sucks? If the controls suck and I can't understand them? I'm not using them. I don't like that to deconstruct buildings in great number (I often build a lot of turrets in games like these) you have to repeatedly click the button each time but... eh...\n3) The damned game just \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665ing rocks. Support this developer. They're awesome.\nCONS:\n1) Okay, so there is a bit of a con here. I'm perfectly okay with 'hero' units as most strategy games have them. But your ENTIRE ARMY should not be only hero units. Personally? I think it would be damned awesome to see millions of soldiers fighting over a bridge that links two islands together rather than just a small handful of guys smacking each other. Numbers in a strategy game are part of the charm in my opinion.\n2) Economy can be a bit hard to grasp for new players. This isn't so much a con as other cons I've mentioned but... it is a con rather than neutral. I won't spoil too much here but your economy is based on having a certain number of people not working with others working and the former generating the cash. This seems... a bit backwards. Otherwise my neighbor should generate taxes in reality but he takes taxes instead.\n3) -sigh...- This is probably my biggest pet peeve about this game. Each individual building has a unit capacity. That's fine but... PLEASE FOR THE LOVE OF GOD MAKE IT SO I CAN RECRUIT A KNIGHT FROM ANY KNIGHT-BUILDING THAT JUST ADDS IT TO THE TOTAL KNIGHT-CAP! PLEASE! CONSOLIDATION! DO IT! OR I'LL GET SHIA LA BEOUF!\nSuper ultra mega horrible TERRIFYINGLY STUPID RIDICULOUSLY ANAL PROLAPSE CON!:\nI can't create a continent-battleship! \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665s! I built a buncha turrets on a landmass, put a Wizard's tower lv 3 on it (my original plan was to use this island kinda like a \"tug boat\" for other islands that were just too far away to reach and then I was like... wait a minute...) and then built knight's doodads and marksmen doodads with their own farms (because I'm just weird) and such to that nature and had a mini-nation on an island which I was going to hurl at the enemy and laugh as they failed to comprehend that I could suddenly attack from anywhere!\nBut the turrets said 'no' as soon as I disconnected the bridge and this makes me sad. -100 points! And no, nothing will replace this until I can have my continent-battleship! Or at least a gunboat. Small continent... typa thing.", "hours": 8.9, "username": "Rascaldees", "products": 98, "found_funny": 2, "early_access": true}
