{"product_id": "748610", "page": 1, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2018-01-17", "text": "Airport Madness 3D: Volume 2 is essentially Airport Madness 3D: Volume 1 with a few more things;\nAirports\nAircraft\nSlight polish & improvements to graphics\nUI has had an overhaul\nStats now log your \"Career\" progress at each Airport\nNothing above really justifies a \"New\" Volume?  It could all have been added to Volume 1 tbh.  Now perhaps there is some behind the scenes non-tangible improvements but I honestly doubt it was so extensive a new volume was required.\nI think the Airports should have been DLC as should the Aircraft and in all honesty the \"Career\" element is long overdue and should have been patched in for free.  As a result now ALL Volume 1 players have a game with limited content that they can never upgrade (just my 2p).\nThat being said, if you don't have volume 1 and you're into ATC then this is a very good middle-ground opener for those wanting to get into ATC.\nIt is deliberately very challenging & this is a good thing because it will challenge you a great deal.\nThe inclusion of more airports keeps things interesting and also offers up a number of different challenges.\nOverall\nGood game that runs at a solid 60FPS and has no real issues (now that bugs have been ironed out).  It will challenge you beyond your limits and if ATC is of interest to you then you will enjoy this game on the most part until the unrealistic(ness) of it all forces you to move onto something more Simulation.\nAt this price I think it is borderline taking the mick but it does what is says on the tin, it's a good Simcade and really it has no major faults or issues that I can see.", "hours": 0.9, "compensation": "Product received for free", "username": "Sim UK", "products": 301, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "748610", "page": 1, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2018-01-08", "text": "Really good little ATC game! Very similar to the first one-just more airports but they are better this time round. The game has simple controls and simple mechanics but is difficult to master. Theres a good range of different airports and different planes and you have to monitor the speeds of different aircraft as well to ensure you don't have crashes. Really loved the recent radar update too!", "hours": 6.6, "username": "LachD_1223", "products": 146, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "748610", "page": 1, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2018-01-07", "text": "Wonderful game, although I wish there were a bit more options available, like being able to select the active runways and being able to open and close (change) them during the game.", "hours": 16.5, "user_id": "76561198043854939", "username": "Iwan", "products": 33, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "748610", "page": 1, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2018-01-07", "text": "I've played most other games in this series, from the original to the first AM3D, and have always enjoyed them. This game does not disappoint, with some new very enjoyable levels. Lukla in particular is very fun, with it's one way runway. However, there are a few small issues. The main one that at larger airports (O'hare, Toronto, etc) not all runways are avaliable for planes to taxi too. It seems the reason is due to the lack of space. Perhaps, at these airports, the individual runway buttons could be shrunken down to smaller sizes, like in AMWE. Aside from that, I just hope more airports are added. In particular, EWR would be really nice. There are some negative reviews for the game, but I think most of these come from people who came in expecting a incredibly realistic ATC simulator, which is not what these games are meant to be, although there is definetly a lack of realistic ones. All in all, I would give this game a 9/10.\nP.S: openscope.co is a good 'realistic' ATC sim if thats what you're looking for.", "hours": 2.8, "user_id": "76561198080015735", "username": "United781", "products": 23, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "748610", "page": 1, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2018-01-02", "text": "Really fun game! I 100% recommend you buy it if you have not already.", "hours": 4.4, "user_id": "76561198367115040", "username": "ScriptedLazer", "products": 7, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "748610", "page": 1, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-20", "text": "I've been a long time supporter of this developer and this is his first release I'm rather upset with.  Like all his previous releases, he promised new airports released as part of the purchase which has traditionally been about one a month.  Instead of getting free new airports as advertised, he goes straight into Version 2, the quest for more money!\nOkay, I have enjoyed his releases so I went ahead an purchased this release.  It's not a stand alone, it doesn't introduce anything new that AM3D V1 doesn't already have, just more airports.  Well, actually these are mostly airports already developed in his earlier 2D versions, but at least they do present some different challenges.  But he was apparrently in a bug rush to get this out as there's quite a few pathing bugs on the ground.\nThis is the first time I'm sending this developer negative press/feedback mainly since this release has more bugs than Version 1 and for the false advertising on the first release that was supposed to see the additional airports as part of that purchase.", "hours": 72.0, "user_id": "76561198022263223", "username": "jeandeaux", "products": 85, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "748610", "page": 1, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-05", "text": "It's okay, but not worth the asking price of \u00a315.49, I paid \u00a313.94 on discount and I still feel its not worth it.\nA very shallow game of something very complex, that I would only recommend  if it was at least half the price.\nI played for an hour and was bored, no real challange after you figured out the layout of the runway and taxiways.", "hours": 1.3, "user_id": "76561198033067923", "username": "sulaco76", "products": 60, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "748610", "page": 1, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-05", "text": "I really enjoyed Airport Madness 1 and was surprised when they brought out the second one I wish they just added the Airports to the first one nothing has changed graphically or what I can make out so far.\nIf you enjoyed the first one then you will enjoy this one but it is a bit pricey I recommend this game I have a feeling that the first one is going to be abandoned.", "hours": 12.9, "user_id": "76561198062085771", "username": "matt19852085", "products": 247, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "748610", "page": 1, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-03", "text": "This is a great game and the developer is very responsive, I cant wait for night operations and would love to see a range ring and undockable radars that can be moved to another screen. I also hope that the developer can implement the ability to click on an aircraft in the air radar windows and have its label pop up. This would be ideal for IMC conditions. Great game especailly love SFO its a real challenge, well done to the developer", "hours": 11.9, "user_id": "76561197999570593", "username": "GreyAlien", "products": 46, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "748610", "page": 1, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-03", "text": "On a positive side, If you don't have Airport Madness 3D, I highly recommend it. But be aware that it's not a real simulator. That said, it is very demanding and a lot of fun keeping all the inbound and outbound traffic without crashes. It brings also some slight improvements over its predecessor.\nOn a negative side, if you have Airport Madness 3D, I cannot recommend it. In my humble opinion, Volume 2 should have been a free upgrade to the previous one or, at most with just a small fee for previous owners.", "hours": 40.6, "user_id": "76561197992779378", "username": "Mikas24", "products": 69, "early_access": false}
