{"product_id": "618710", "page": 1, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-10", "text": "This is a great wizardry-style game. Full disclosure, I totally understand this game isn't for everyone. But I enjoy it for what it is. It's a great homage to classic CRPGs. I do like how after the initial dungeon the game becomes open ended. Though it can be difficult, it does give you a lot of options for characters and equipment.\nElminage is very old school in comparison to modern rpgs but the menus and navigation are really well laid out. A lot of older CRPGs suffer from clunky interfaces and thankfully Elminage does not have this problem.\nThe game has a ton of obscure secrets so I do recommend reading FAQs to get full enjoyment out of the game.\nWhile not perfect you will get your money's worth if you enjoy dungeon crawlers.", "hours": 39.4, "user_id": "76561198040306007", "username": "Sidbot", "products": 445, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "618710", "page": 1, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-08", "text": "I REALLY like this game! A true Wizardry successor! A varieety of dungeons, hard fights, many many dungeons, slow progression where you have to work up you characters... just love it! Thank you! If you like this kind of game, don't pass this one, specially for the price! Hey, is there more games like this that needs to be brought to the PC? Oh and any chances of a MAC port?", "hours": 18.3, "user_id": "76561198008423537", "username": "dugalm", "products": 232, "early_access": false}
