{"product_id": "734580", "page": 4, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2018-01-08", "text": "The game is buggy as hell.  At first I complained it was P2W because people had rocket launchers when I played my first game and you can pay real money for classes with additional ammo.  After playing for 2 straight hours it's not really a big deal.  The starter bolt action rifle 1 shot headshots anyone no matter what class they are.\nIt's a pretty fun little FREE game.  I think the easiest way to describe it is Foxhole the FPS.  The systems are almost identicle.  Big map, you can craft and gather.  Then you need to push to the enemy base and destroy it.\nThe most important 2 things this game needs are 1 from the developer, better netcode.  Gun fights are terrrrrible.  I'll be 6 feet away from anyone and they rubber band all over the place.  Can't land a shot because they keep rubber banding.\nAnd 2 it needs a big community.  The map is huge.  If the server isn't full the game is tedious as hell because you'll be running for days and not see anyone.  SO DOWNLOAD AND PLAY IT!", "hours": 6.9, "user_id": "76561197991844714", "username": "Rex Smashington", "products": 515, "early_access": true}
