{"product_id": "718650", "page": 4, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-13", "text": "TL;DR: A unique take on rts games that still manages to hit all the core features rts veterans love and expect.\nOne key element that I have noticed is the players' \"mana\" and abilities grants a high potential for having different balanced focuses and tactics that essentially run off a risk/reward system.\nDo you invest lots of a small amounts of mana to scout and then play pinball off floating islands in search of treasure and the enemy? Do you use a little more mana to chain together as mana islands as possible, risking fights with neutrals but snowballing your economy? Or do you use your mana sparingly, saving it for defense or when you need it most?\nSince the maps are proceduraly generated you will have to be adaptable to utilize what you are given as efficiently as possible and use it to steer your overarching strategy.\nThere are only two negatives. The first is the worker system is a little more dense than it needs to be-- which means as a casual player it is hard to forsee the shape your economy will take-- ending with you rushing to place buildings down as rapidly as possible with little thought beyond the next move ahead. With experience you will know exactly which resources you need for what but the lack of resource theme makes it less easy to catch on than the casual gamer might prefer.\nThe second negative is that the game is so good you won't want to wait for the next wave of features you know will be great! (Early access probs).", "hours": 7.5, "username": "Livebait \u262d", "products": 52, "found_funny": 2, "early_access": true}
