{"product_id": "718650", "page": 4, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-10", "text": "Early Access Review.\nFirst thing I want to say I really love the games potential and undestand it's Early Access so think should change before it actually released.\nEconomy:\nDoesn't seem complex enough and is easily exploitable I've read a few people complaining how it's too hard but sad part it's not. Build cost does not increase when leveling up buildings; less is more Also there is no need to go beyond 2 Islands from your castle (The further away the more it costs). Farming is the only thing that hurts your income but after unlocking the Mill (unlocks literally in the begining) it becomes extremely easy to over power a few farms. Mills Stack infinately in my end gams I had 15 Mills and 3 Farms all level 3 and with the 20% bonus from the tech tree, supporting a population of 750. When it comes to the other resource you can just spam out Market places the more you have the cheaper the goods become just need allot of them to notice a difference. In the end I had only Farmers everyone else was gathering gold.\nAI:\nObvious they are not ready yet and spam way to many bridges.\nMagic:\nThe current magic is very abusable once you get you economy in line you can buy all the mana you need and just spam cast tonados to wip out enemy castles. Need some way to prevent spells from affecting your home islands.\nBlowing up islands was fun and was abused too. I explored the Ai bases to find all there nest and just blew up the island that connected to it followed by stealing the nests.\nUnits:\nReally like the units but game reminds me of Majesty units are only controlled by posting bounties. When it comes to gearing the units you have to buy each piece of gear.  There is no retreat yet so your units either win or die during war.\nA word to the wise if you are like me and spammed wizards having 10-20 of them all casting spells (You need to buy there spells for them btw from the library) crashes the game.\n* End Game", "hours": 4.9, "user_id": "76561198024439208", "username": "Revelion", "products": 85, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": true}
