{"product_id": "748610", "page": 2, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-01", "text": "I have been a  Big Fat Simulations-fan since Airport Madness part 1, so it won't be a surprise to read this positive post. Airport Madness 3D-part two has eight airports in various difficulty levels, starting with Hong Kong (easiest IMHO) to Lukla (very, very, very hard).\nThere have been lots of discussions why this should or should not be a seperate game. Well, i for one feel the gameplay is different. This installment has upgraded the levels of difficulty slightly (never has so much crashed in the first 10 hours of game-play). Also, do not forget this is still a one-man show who has delivered and fixed everytime. The best change is a fix for stuck aircraft.\nIf you don't have part one, buy the bundle. If you do have part one, get this one also.\nI do have to say that Airport Madness World Edition also had potential, so i hope the 3D versions will be kept up-to-date in the future.\nThumbs up for the developer (still hoping both editions will get four more airports as upgrade...).\nReview edit (dec. 17th 2017): The only downside is that scores are saved locally at this time, so if you play on more then one machine (like me), you will have different scores on both.", "hours": 16.6, "username": "cHabu", "products": 439, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "748610", "page": 2, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-11-29", "text": "For my previously semi-unhelpful views on Airport Madness 3D, head here:\nThe Madness begins again! A 2nd volume of 8 fantastic airports to play with, crash aircraft and get frustrated over. Then play them again and again and again! Because you're not actually frustrated with the game, but with yourself for failing hard!\nIn the first Volume the original 4 airports that came with Volume 1 were pretty good. As the game developed 4 more were added over time, showing a marked improvement in quality with each new airport release. Volume 2 alone is a collection of airports that showcases how much Big Fat Simulations has improved over that original volume. The airports are more detailed, more complex, and compared to the original airports, some here are huge!\nIf you're new to Airport Madness 3D, I will reiterate, this is an Arcade game based on time mangement and ever increasing levels of multitasking. So I recommend starting with Volume 1. The airports in Volume 2 are no pushover to beat..\nHong Kong is a good starter, but is very heavy traffic, finding gaps are easier, but queues will quickly arise.\nLondon & Nepal will test your time management skills to the limit. Every inch counts on a Single Runway where air traffic will be coming at you head on as you try to move aircraft back the way they came.\nChicago is the jewel in the crown with 8 runways to keep track of and aircraft coming and going on each. Multitasking better be your strong point. Crashes are a certainty, the very definition of Madness!\nAlso, more 'feature' content will be coming in the future too at no additional cost. This isn't just more airports at a price (which the developer deserves to be paid for).. There are planned features such as emergencies, night time play and more! So this is a game worth investing in as the developer is always adding new stuff through updates and patches.\nSo whilst Volume 2 may be more of the same gameplay, this is by no means bad at all.. The series goes from strength to strength, and Volume 2 offers the best Airport Madness experience to date!\nI love it! Plain and simple... Here's to another 75+ hours of fantastic fun!", "hours": 27.3, "user_id": "76561197966526680", "username": "Saracen26", "products": 729, "early_access": false}
