{"product_id": "512270", "page": 5, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-02", "text": "Should have been awesome but was barely good. Liked the concept though but too scripted and terrible controls.", "hours": 0.1, "username": "Dreddloch", "products": 70, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "512270", "page": 5, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-02", "text": "I would really like to reccomend this purely because the space station looks so good and the floating feels great. Problem is this is a neausa inducing experience from the start and then theres the jet pack portion. Worst jet pack controls I might have ever seen on any game, I almost threw up on my Vive.", "hours": 0.2, "username": "Bartuby_jones", "products": 127, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "512270", "page": 5, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-02", "text": "Excellent, but I wished I could see more of the inside of the station. Is there more to come?\nThis experience feels like beeing the bigger brother of \"Astronaut VR\" for Cardboard.", "hours": 0.4, "user_id": "76561198052816759", "username": "michael.kosi", "products": 38, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "512270", "page": 5, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-02", "text": "I was really looking forward to playing this, but I had to turn it off just seconds into the game. The game is a motion sickness simulator, even on the \"easy\" setting.\nI'm not easily upset by VR games, I can cope with contiunous movement just fine, and I love hurdling myself around space in Lone Echo. However, in Lone Echo, you have one to one control over your position. Here, your movement only moves you forward along a path predefined by the developers. This is a major not done in VR, the player should always have immediate control of where he is going. Your hands also lag sluggishly behind - I get that this is to emulate the experience of being trapped in a space suit, but it is very discomforting and breaks immersion. But worst of all, they happily rotate your head around, a cardinal sin in VR games. When the other astronaut comes to greet you and rotates you to where you need to be going, I nope'd out instantly.\nThe game invokes the kind of ill feeling that lasts for half an hour or more after you've already taken off the HMD.", "hours": 0.1, "user_id": "76561197984631526", "username": "Lhorkan", "products": 55, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "512270", "page": 5, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-02", "text": "0/10 Doesnt contain lootboxes", "hours": 0.4, "username": "Staberas", "products": 441, "found_funny": 2, "early_access": false}
