{"product_id": "512270", "page": 5, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-01", "text": "I don't get the negative reviews.  This is a really fun zero gravity space simulation of an emergency situation aboard the ISS. And it's free.  The visuals are good.  Sounds/ voice acting is on  point.  The only real negative is that the controls could have been done better, from gripping objects to using your jetpack.  Otherwise, a very good, short space narrative experience.\nAnd to all the people giving this title a negative review because you got nauseuous.  Guess what?  It's not a game problem, it's a you problem.  Either get used to VR or stop reviewing VR games and/or sell your VR HMD.\nRating 7/10", "hours": 0.2, "username": "FastLawyer", "products": 1215, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "512270", "page": 5, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-01", "text": "This experience is incredible. I realized how nuts it is to leave the interior of the ISS for a spacewalk. I was saying \"no way\" I'm going out there!!!! My hands got really sweaty. Even just feeling like you have no gravity made me extremely nervous. One wrong move and I float away forever.\nYou start in the exit pod and are told to take this clip on a cord and clip it to a bar inside. Then to open up the hatch and get out. YEAH RIGHT, I'm going into space at the trust of one little carbiner!?!? I felt like I was there, and I knew if I really was I would NEVER want to go out. Even just being near the hole was freakish.\nI thought they did a great job with the hands and arms. No other game really does this well. The helmet too was very immersive.\nThe only issue I had was with the jetpack controls which were near the end for me \u2013 assuming I used them incorrectly, the ending probably is different when you are successful. I had an issue with determining whether I was supposed to be successful or not.", "hours": 0.3, "username": "Felewin", "products": 49, "early_access": false}
