{"product_id": "609150", "page": 1, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2018-01-17", "text": "Thanks Square Enix for this great game. I enjoy playing the game and remined of star ocean 3 with less private actions and complete themin one walkthrough.\nThe fighting system is similar to tales of series SO 3 . The port it is good and the graphic is also good.\nI didnt have any crash during the gameplay of 130hr. I am using gtx 970m and intel 6700hq.\nLooking forward for more Star Ocean games and JRPG games from SQ.", "hours": 152.3, "user_id": "76561198209958109", "username": "mohd_rmi", "products": 33, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "609150", "page": 1, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2018-01-16", "text": "STORY: You play as Edge mavrick a boy who wants to travel to diffrent planets and discover new things so anime star trek mixed star wars and battlestar troopers the one with the big insects.\nPROS: Real time combat system which is a party of 4 that is fun and challenging at the start.\ngreat complex crafting system still don't fully understand synthesis\nGet to change difficulty settings.\nLot's of graphic options.\nLevel up system is good when you level up your party you get to learn new skills with each character.\nthere is a reward system if you do good in combat you ether get bonus exp point, bonus money and other bonuses depending on the way you play in combat.\nRuns at 60 fps mostly can drop somtimes but i had a smooth experience overall better port than ffXIII.\nHas interacting characters from your party that can lead to multiple endings\nCONS: can drop frames mine droped to 50 fps but then went straight back to 60fps and im on a gtx 970, I7 3.20gigs hyper threading to 8 core 16gigs ram ddr3  so not a masive problem.\nCharacters are really childish somtimes but you get this a lot in anime japaness rpgs.\nsynthesis tutorial is a little confusing at the start so your have to mess around with it a bit and learn yourself how to use.", "hours": 81.3, "user_id": "76561198150931046", "username": "snowstorm125", "products": 381, "early_access": false}
