{"product_id": "609150", "page": 1, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2018-01-13", "text": "Good action-y combat system with a full party of usable characters. Has a good story and character types if you can stand anime/jrpg tropes. Characters are nicely designed with a fair bit of diversity in their outfit styles and color schemes. Played this game to completion on the 360 waaay back when, got the international version on ps3 afterwards and now with it's 4k remake on PC it's legacy just keeps holding strong. Game has really stood the test of time. Read through most of the negative reviews, complaints about crashing here and there, haven't had it crash on me yet ^^ and as for combat related concerns it sounds like players that are just used to games holding thier pampered hands. Seriously just git gud m8, combat is fine so long as you aren't a talentless button mashing monkey XD, place your attacks, use your flanking properlly and then feel good about yourself for being able to kick butt.", "hours": 5.3, "username": "Hikari Ryou", "products": 148, "early_access": false}
