{"product_id": "718650", "page": 5, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-04", "text": "I\u2019m really digging this game so far. Being that it\u2019s in Early Access, I\u2019ll update this review as it goes along.\nWho\u2019s this game for? People who like city builders or games like The Settlers, Northgard, or even Majesty.\nIt\u2019s definitely most similar to the recent Northgard, but different enough in theme and gameplay that it could become its own, unique thing.\nThe island gameplay mechanics are fun and interesting and avoid being gimmicky. The economy seems pretty balanced. The graphics are good and the pacing seems good so far.\nThere are some UI issues and gameplay frustrations, like the lack of a zooming-to-mouse cursor option, the lack of adversity for the first hour or so, the lack of factions (currently) and a few other things that I\u2019ll be posting about on their forums when I\u2019ve had more time with it, but these are all things that can be addressed in EA. I have faith based on what\u2019s here already.", "hours": 1.0, "username": "DevildogFF", "products": 336, "early_access": true}
