{"product_id": "512270", "page": 6, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-01", "text": "Absolutley terrible, every single one action outside the jetpack section including your every hand movement is scripted, they might as well have made it a bunch of QTEs, it's a linear rollercoastear with no control, you just put your hand in the right spots and it slides you along the rail. The expirience itself is extremly underwhelming, the earth doesn't even rotate underneath you, it just swapes from day to night with a 3 second animation, the station is badly modeled, your arms clip through everything, and you don't really grab onto the hand holds, you just press the trigger over them and no matter what direction you pull in it just advances the animation.\nMission: ISS using revive is much better if you want a spacewalk expirience, it allows you to explore the station on your own accord, turn yourself in 3d space using your hands (if you turn it on in the options, otherwise you have to use the touchpad) instead of the game doing it for you at pre scripted spots, and it even includes the inside of the station and a bunch of fun stuff floating about to play with in 0g", "hours": 0.2, "username": "CrustMan", "products": 162, "early_access": false}
