{"product_id": "718650", "page": 6, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-02", "text": "There are very obvious flaws with an RTS game that doesn't allow you to control units.\n1. There are no orders. Instead there are goals. These goals reward money to the units that partake in them. Every unit for a goal costs 10 gold. Got an army of 60 units? Be prepared to spend 600 gold per goal.\n2.  After each goal is fulfilled, the units will return home. Be prepared for half of your army to be running in the opposite direction while you are spamming the next goal.\n3. You can't do attack goals on areas covered by fog of war. If your army doesn't move up enough, get ready to be annoyed.\n4. Your army doesn't amass. In fact, they are going to trickle in while the defender kills them off one at a time. There is no way to stop this from happening right now.\n5. Magic has limited range. You attack them? They'll be able to use magic. You won't.\n6. What happens when you are on a very, very large map and two players are very far away from each other? Like on opposite corners of the map? Get ready  to get creative to try and get your army to their base. With limited magic range, you won't even be able to cast anti-fog of war magic to order your units to their base. You'll have to send out flyers to explore. After this, how are you going to get ground units to them? Well, you won't be able to get the islands close enough to even connect to their base because they will be out of range. You'll have to really get creative. I know that after around 20 minutes, I finally found a path that I could use to connect to the last player's base and take them out.\nWhat happens if that last player doesn't develop enough? Get ready for a draw because they won't be able to attack you and you won't be able to attack them ;D.\nI'm not going to mention quality of life things like the UI as this game is early access and those elements can be improved. These things I have mentioned are pretty core gameplay mechanics, which leads me to believe that this is a fatally flawed game.", "hours": 5.3, "user_id": "76561198067954704", "username": "nestharus", "products": 96, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": true}
