{"product_id": "718650", "page": 6, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-02", "text": "Cons:  So much is not done that all I can say is it's early access ... my advice is to wait on it but that won't be popular.  There is no campaign and so much in the tutorial is not said as you play.  And considering you start getting attacked right away almost with no advisor helping to give details,  it can be a bit frustrating.  Don't get me wrong it's not anything that in time can be figured out.  The slowness of response to attacks is madning. .. even if you up the reward.. they just saunter over like nothing is happening.  That isn't even realistic for games much less real life.  That is enough for me to return it if I had not gone over the time req.  And seriously, you have ot reward with gold everything your people are assigned to do except to buildings?  That is just way too tedius and not even fun.\nPositive:  it's rather unique for a builder/age of empires/survival type game.  There is an entry at the start for multiplayer but it is greyed out so that is coming it seems.  The art is pretty cool and the mechanics are refreshing except for what was mentioned above.  I really like how they used the floating island thing and pulling them together how you want to create your world.  i'm looking forward to the changes.  I'll redo the review once I see a few more updates come out or significant changes happen.", "hours": 1.7, "user_id": "76561198013622319", "username": "ishKiia", "products": 219, "early_access": true}
{"product_id": "718650", "page": 6, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-02", "text": "Let's get the negatives out of the way first: Definitely needs some work, but that's what early access is for, isn't it?\nTwo things that stick out to me immediately: There should be the option to scale the UI so that you don't end up with tiny buttons, and there should be an option to not lock the mouse cursor into the window in windowed mode. As someone with rather specific needs out of a game, those particular options are important to have for me, and for accessibility in general.\nIt could also stand to have a pause button to allow you to place flags and such over a wide area, and to allow the player to think over their next move. It's entirely possible that there is such a button and I was simply unable to find it, though.\nNow on to the positive things. This game is very polished for a game from a brand-new studio. The visuals are well-done, the intro sequence is impressive, and the interface is, while not the best I've ever seen, certainly easy to use and I'd have a hard time picking out specific improvements that could be made (though I probably would find my grievances with it after playing for a while longer; but then, any UI is going to have its annoying quirks).\nThe one annoyance I had is that while you have to right click on an island to place a flag, if you want to place a flag on a unit (e.g. to order an attack), you have to _left_ click on the unit. I do hope these will be separate settings when the control config is implemented (you can't change controls at the moment, though there is a space in the options for it).\nAll in all, it's a well-polished, if unfinished, fantasy RTS. What's not to like? Fantasy themed games like this are rare.\n------\nOn to a few other thoughts, of possible improvements: The selection of races to play as feels a little limited. Humans, dark elves, elves, and dwarves (with the latter two being locked at present). I'd like to see a little more variety, particularly in the non-humanoid area. It's a fantasy game; cat-people and lizard-people are practically mandatory! More seriously, some other less-humanoid playable species would be nice. Perhaps a civilization of golems left over from the ancient war that shattered the world, or a varied alliance of beastmen races, from kobolds to lizardfolk to gryphons and centaurs, like Master of Magic had.\nSome more diversity in the existing races would be nice as well. I've been noticing lately just how many games have all white people, and I think some variety in the existing humanoid races would be good to see. Personally, I think the way to do this might be to implement sub-races (think how TES has Nords, Bretons, and Redguards, all of whom are human), or to simply give a random skin color to each unit (or random fur color, scale color, etc, if you add non-humanoid races to the game).", "hours": 1.0, "user_id": "76561198045554762", "username": "Felthry", "products": 194, "early_access": true}
