{"product_id": "637100", "page": 2, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2018-01-18", "text": "Ugh writing this review is gonna be a chore, because if I say something good about this game it's most likely gonna sound fanboy-ish but if I say anything bad about this game I'll be labled as either a \"hater\" or a Classic Sonic extremist.\nWhat to do, hm.\nYou know what let's see how much deep we can go before we can't escape.\nSonic Forces, the game I had high hopes for, only to get 2/3 of my hopes back.\nThe story for starters, it's very lacking. I mostly wanted any form of info on who Infinite is (and even the comics made to explain him do a terrible job at it) or why the Phantom Ruby is in a new shape or why the Chaos Emeralds aren't ever mentioned or why everyone but Sonic is useless, ok I should stop this list before I pass out. But my point is this story fails to tell you much at all.\nNow for gameplay.\nModern Sonic feels about how he should\nyet in 2D his platforming is painful (and he's in 2D about 45% of the game). He has the Colors double jump but they nerfed it for some reason, making it near useless. Enemies are no threat and exist solely as boost fodder.\nClassic Sonic, everything, and I mean everything about him is wrong. His physics have no logic, he's sluggish on the ground but a balloon in the air. Some slopes he can't even walk over but rolling flings him 70 feet above them. His platforming would be challenging and even fun if he controlled properly.\nEasily the best part of the game is the Avatar, also known as Original the Character. Lot's of weapons and clothing to choose from, interesting platforming, and going fast while still feeling in control make him (or her if you make a female OC) the most fun thing in the game.\nI'm just gonna put both soundtrack and graphics together for this, because they're both amazing. Sad to say Classic Sonic's stage themes made my ears bleed though.\nLastly is the DLC problem, as Super Sonic is now paid DLC. Yes the form that was free whenever he was in a past Sonic game is now paid. You don't even get a Super OC, just Super Modern Sonic and Super Classic Sonic. Fortunately the other DLC's are free, but the Super Sonic DLC being paid is utterly wrong.\nDespite what I have said above I do recommend this game, because it redeems itself enough to justify a purchase, but do be warned it contains Denuvo Anti-Tamper. If you are like me and despise Denuvo it would be wise to wait for a sale.", "hours": 29.9, "username": "Green", "products": 40, "early_access": false}
