{"product_id": "637100", "page": 2, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2018-01-16", "text": "You wanna know if this game is good? Yes it is. Wanna know if it is bad? It certainly is.\nThe game is nice looking and all but I feel like it's a huge dissapointment. The game doesn't give you much control of Sonic (or your OC), it constatly grabs you by the hand and gets you to the end of the level. The game has a very linear design to the point where you may even finish it if you let the foward and the boost inputs pressed. The sotry is something that seems that was dragged out of tumblr or deviantart and was lazily put together and the characters dialogue really feels out of place many times.", "hours": 10.9, "username": "Burmecian Dragoon", "products": 344, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "637100", "page": 2, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2018-01-14", "text": "This has easily become one of my favourite games. I really liked the story and the bond Sonic and his new 'buddy' formed during their time together. The graphics and visuals are absolutely stunning, to the point where I sometimes end up forgetting what I'm doing just to look at the backgrounds, and although the stages are pretty short, they're all very fun to play through. I absolutely love the soundtrack, though I might be a bit biased because this is my favourite type of music, I found it fitting to the game, especially the songs that went along with the avatar's stages.\nI love the avatar (although I'm not sure why they're significantly taller than Sonic), creating them and unlocking all the apparel to dress them up with, as well as their stages and gameplay. I did however miss the option to give them a name, even if no one were to actually call them by it. It would have been cool if their name showed up in the rankings instead of the name of your gaming profile (making it possible to search people up... Which is creepy).\nI didn't really see a real reason for Classic Sonic to appear in this game other than to please the Classic fans, but I still enjoyed his stages. Had some difficulties with his controls but it was alright overall.\nI love the Episode Shadow DLC, as well as being able to unlock Shadow for some Sonic stages on the main map. Loved the song remixes he got as well, though I wish his cutscenes would have been included in the theatre, or in his own separate theatre.\nSome of the challenge missions were really difficult to complete, although not impossible. Finally finishing all of them was an incredible feeling, but my heart goes out to the players with less fortunate circumstances.\nAll in all, I really do love this game for everything that it is and I hope everyone else can enjoy it as well!", "hours": 96.3, "username": "Hope & Beacon", "products": 48, "early_access": false}
