{"product_id": "609150", "page": 2, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2018-01-07", "text": "I was hesitant because I heard poor things about it on the board but I'm glad I bought it. It's well worth the cost of the title and the game is pretty massive and enjoyable. There was a few hours I really disliked the MC but it came back around with the introduction of some new characters and plot twists. It plays like a video game, something I haven't felt in a while on PC (hard to explain but true).\nIt's a really good JRPG, the fighting system in the game is one of the most addicting I've had the pleasure of playing as well; you unlock moves by leveling and place them where you want and make them stronger by spending points meaning everything is pretty customizable. You also have the option to make weapons and armor and items yourself (though collecting ingredients for anything decent is a pain and a half) which I assume also means if you put in the time you can make your own little demi-god character. I for one have had no close calls since I gave my main hp boost + auto heal. Whenever I get bored I just switch mains and party layout and vuala.\nI've just been screwing around really collecting stuff and grinding new characters so the story itself has been taking a second seat to that but the story isn't all that bad, it reminds me of some early 2000's anime and the character development is pretty much in your face with the MC and all the gang. I recommend.", "hours": 80.8, "user_id": "76561198050021269", "username": "lunarvida", "products": 159, "early_access": false}
