{"product_id": "512270", "page": 7, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-11-30", "text": "Crappy roguelike. Using the advanced controls is the only way to complete this ~10 minute experience.", "hours": 0.6, "user_id": "76561197972658084", "username": "America's War Boner", "products": 237, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "512270", "page": 7, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-11-30", "text": "The idea of going into space in VR is awesome, but Home definitely fell short.\nThe jetpack-like thing you have to use about 10 minutes in is also very confusing when you operate it, it doesnt seem natural at all.\nThe only real way to move around the ISS is to grab onto handrails. It's a great idea for movement in Zero G but is really rough around the edges.The spacesuit arms are too short, which sucks as a taller person because i cant reach out normally.\nThe final nail in the coffin and the biggest issue though is that when you move your head your body stays in the same place, so your stuck looking forward, fumbling around. i think the idea was to make it more immersive since its probably really hard to simulate being in space, but in the end all it did was detract from the immersion.\nHome does however have so much potential. If the Developer takes a little bit of time to iron out Home's issues they'll have something great. It's just not there yet.", "hours": 0.2, "username": "\u26541ogical\u2654", "products": 130, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "512270", "page": 7, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-11-30", "text": "Ohh how I wanted this to be the most positive review written all year.... But...\nIn the current state of this simulation I cannot recommend it if you want a good VR experience.\nThe arms of your suit are not responding anywhere near good enough to make you believe their actually your arms.\nBecause of this your motion controllers will be far from where your hands actually are in the game.\nAlso, the hands dont interact with the surfaces the way they should. You'll grip half way through objects etc.\nHad these issues been fixed, then I would give this title a huge thumb up even though the play through is just a few minutes.", "hours": 0.2, "user_id": "76561197970893771", "username": "Tomahawk", "products": 95, "early_access": false}
