{"product_id": "734580", "page": 7, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2018-01-03", "text": "Really liking this game so far. As others have said it is Foxhole in first person only with *slightly* less depth to the gameplay systems. It is a very good start and there is definetely enough there to keep you going for a while even though it could do with some more content like more building pieces, squads, automated defenses of some kind, etc.\nThe concept is fantastic. Scavenge and mine to build up your base's defenses or build forward operating bases on the frontline and move your team closer to the enemy base. Build a truck and run supplies for your team. Make ammo for your team. Change the tide of the battle by building a tank and go and assualt the enemy. Repair buildings around your base so you and your team can loot supplies easier. Blow a hole in the side of a building and use it as a sniper's nest. It is really a sandbox game.\nMatches can last from 15 mins to multiple hours depending on how well people are cooperating. The developers are adding stuff quickly and there is a lot of potential for this to be even better. Sure the graphics are rough, but the gameplay is definitely there.\nGive it a shot, it is free. And the DLC is dirt cheap.", "hours": 40.8, "username": "JayBiggs", "products": 136, "early_access": true}
