{"product_id": "718650", "page": 7, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-02", "text": "Only played for a couple of hours but really enjoyed this game.  Well worth the $20-$25 price tag.  Easy game to learn.  I like the unigue concept of discovering and magically binding new islands to your realm.  I cant wait for this game to be finished devolopment so I can unlock all aspects of the game.  My biggest criticism is I wish there was an easy way to see what level each building is at beacuse I find I am constantly clicking on my buildings to see if I can upgrade them.  I guess I will just have to remember what each level of a building looks like.  Now to go find that dragons nest to tame me some dragons...", "hours": 28.5, "user_id": "76561198039663249", "username": "msp.2004", "products": 46, "early_access": true}
{"product_id": "718650", "page": 7, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-02", "text": "Bought this game thinking YES an RTS! Havn't played a good RTS since Warcraft 3!\nHowever this isnt an RTS. you don't directly control your units, you build various buildings without much explaination of what they really do. The resource system all feels a bit weird like you're not sure what you need and why. I played for about 45 minutes and only came accross 2 wild eagles and no actual enemies, meaning this game would be way way too slow for me personally.\nalso a flaw above all else there is no option to set screen refresh rate! meaning if you're a true gamer and play at 144hz, you'll be stuck at 60 and its like cancer to the eye balls.\nSorry not for me, refunded", "hours": 0.5, "user_id": "76561197960863484", "username": "X99MYKE", "products": 37, "found_funny": 3, "early_access": true}
{"product_id": "718650", "page": 7, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-02", "text": "Not bad, still needs a ton of work. It's like Settlers, Northgard and Majesty had a baby. Hopefully with the influx of early access $$$ this evolves more.\nHoping there's eventually something to stop portals from just popping up in the middle of your domain.\nSeems to be some bugs when your economy gets huge. But if you get to the point you likely won anyhow.\nA.I. is pretty useless, they'll put up one good battle if you attack them or when your chains of islands first link up.\nA.I. will try to steal islands you spawn out of magic, you need to be ready to drift them back quickly before they drift to one of their islands and they build a bridge. Once they build a bridge (or start) they island is theirs. Even with tornadoes they simply auto build a new bridge as it gets destroyed, you can't beat the system's reaction time, you likely could vs. another human.", "hours": 9.6, "user_id": "76561198080076366", "username": "PeteyD", "products": 179, "early_access": true}
{"product_id": "718650", "page": 7, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-01", "text": "Bought, installed and before I knew it almost 2 hours went by.  I don't spend much time playing games like this so finding a survival balance of resources is proving to be a challenge for me.\nThe game is fun and I can see many more hours spent playing the current singleplayer.  Looking forward to campaign and multiplayer modes when available.", "hours": 18.1, "username": "P3NGU1N", "products": 69, "early_access": true}
{"product_id": "718650", "page": 7, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-01", "text": "First impressions are good. Very clear store page description on what is offered so far. Played 2 hours so far no crashing/bugs. Would like to see a pause option/slow time in a future patch.", "hours": 3.8, "user_id": "76561198005669750", "username": "Possum", "products": 166, "early_access": true}
{"product_id": "718650", "page": 7, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-01", "text": "I'm fairly picky about my RTS games. I dislike clickfest games, games that try to disguise poor AI by throwing hordes of enemies at you, and games that require high levels of unit ability micromanagment to succeed. I'm happy to report Driftland has none of that.\nUnit numbers are small and you actually don't have direct control over your military units. It uses a system similar to the Majesty games where you place reward markers down where you need things done and can prioritize them by adjusting the size of the reward.\nI've recorded some gameplay playing as the humans:\nThings I like:\nNot so crazy about:\nNo tactical pause: I prefer single player games that allow me to pause the action and look around occasionally. The only way I have found to pause the game is to call up the main menu and then I can't interact with anything. However, the pace of this game is slow enough I can live with this.", "hours": 6.6, "username": "Gen Curmudgeon", "products": 793, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": true}
{"product_id": "718650", "page": 7, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-01", "text": "From what I've played, the game is good. A new take on the RTS genre with it's island mechanic. A far cry from the same old static landmasses in every other RTS game.\nGame runs well, despite some jittering at times. But its Early Access, so I will forgive it.\nAll in all, I recommend it if you like RTS games.", "hours": 0.6, "username": "ThatShamanGuy", "products": 105, "early_access": true}
{"product_id": "724520", "page": 1, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2018-01-04", "text": "Well, there was no sense of direction in the intro so I was left very confused. The music doesn't seem fitting either... maybe it might be part of the \"satirical\" nature of the game.\nThe method to travel to locations in the World Map is strange, but at least somebody tells you. Oh, and when I transitioned back to the World Map through a transport pad at a different location - yeah the player sprite messed up.\nHowever, I was willing to start the game over again to see what it could amount to.\nSo, I did. But... I gave up because I don't know what to do. I don't know what was the point of this game...\n:/", "hours": 0.2, "username": "Elyswer", "products": 41, "early_access": false}
