{"product_id": "637100", "page": 3, "page_order": 19, "recommended": true, "date": "2018-01-12", "text": "Everything everyone has said about the physics is true.\nI wondered, how can some people describe classic sonic being heavy and clunky, and others describing the exact opposite? Well, it's true. There were moments where he handled like Stephen Hawking with the parking brake on, and other moments where he took off like Usain Bolt if you swapped his Splenda with crack.\nI'm going to be perfectly honest here. I'm a university student and for one of my projects, I chose to make a 3D platformer. Now, bear in mind I had no idea how to do this, it was outside my realm of experience. Despite this, and despite my rather short development time, I came up with physics and character control that was objectively better than what Sonic Team accomplished here. My first playable debug build objectively had a more realistic approach to gravity and momentum than this nightmare.\nThat's not only embarassing, what's worse is these people had access to the source code of Generations and other boost formula games where the physics was done correctly. I don't believe the engine has changed so this c*ck up is inexcusable. These people literally had every tool to get it right and failed. I wouldn't trust them to make ice cream without starting a house fire.\nIgnoring the physics for a moment, another thing, the stages are really linear. You can't claim to offer different ways to move through a stage by putting one identical set of floating floor panels above another, that's the platformer equivalent of a soviet apartment block.\nMoving on, the stages are way too short. I'm in no way a fast person, when I drive people call me Windows Vista because I take 6 years to get anywhere and inevitably crash. That being the case... why are modern sonic's levels taking a minute? I know the speed means stages are larger than they appear but Sonic Unleashed made every daytime stage a minimum 4 minutes for the average player. That was a decade ago. What are you people doing?", "hours": 0.4, "username": "Wimblebimble", "products": 59, "found_funny": 3, "early_access": false}
