{"product_id": "718650", "page": 8, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-11-30", "text": ">>>edit 3\n70 hours in the game and still really enjoying it<<<\n>>2edit updated the review a bit\nalmost 50 hours played still liking the game very much :)\nand added a gold guide below :P\nand it's 1 of the better early access games out there so don't let that hold you up with buying it ;)\nand it is worth every penny so don't wait for a sale ;)\none of the devs reads everything on the forums even responds in the weekends <3\n>>\nwell it's fun to play\nfell in love with it just by watching the trailer before it was launched\nand i did get in touch with one of the devs he even made me more excited <3\nso i had a hard time waiting for release day i wanted to try it out so badly ;)\n>and o boy this game delivers what it promises<\nthe enemy needs to get a bit more aggressive\nafter that it will needs some more modifications all around\nit already a lot of fun ;)\nit did crash a few times thx to the auto save you don't lose progress\nso you don't need to get frustrated if it happens :P\n>1smal review update<\nplayed it for 30 hours still really enjoying it\nreally like it how buildings upgrade and change\nits nice that the other races have completely different looking buildings\ni really like the large map so many islands you can get its wonderful\nthe freedom of moving the isles around a really great concept <3\npossible to play against 5 ai players at this point of the game.\nalso a nice thing that your heroes get exp and lvl up its small things like that that really pull me in <3\nthe game really is a fresh air in its genre\nit's similar to a lot of other games at the same time very unique\nand it simply looks amazing\ni have tried a lot of different games lately\nno game stands out as this one\nit yust launched a few days ago so it can only get better\nthe devs realy read the forums and respond\nso yeah i going to try out every update, i think i have a hard time stopping to play the game so i wont mis a thing :P\n>>>>edit4\nwell first update is out\nreally like the speed up buttons they added<<<<\nand i really want the badge of this game :D\nso i hope they add 1 ;)\n>>> i really recommend it <<<\nyou won't waste your money on it\ni also made a guide for ppl that have a hard time getting some gold ;)\n<<<i will update this post in future\nand add more context to it over time>>>", "hours": 89.4, "username": "hamsterbryan", "products": 726, "early_access": true}
{"product_id": "718650", "page": 8, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-11-30", "text": "A great game. It was on my radar for quite some time, and I wasn't dissapointed. It remainded me a lot about Northgard, which is nice because the game didn't just coppied it's competitor. A very good combination of nice RTS mechanics and stunning visual design. (Drifting the islands is a very nice touch by the way)\nDefinetaly recommend it.", "hours": 3.9, "username": "Painblade", "products": 226, "early_access": true}
