{"product_id": "609150", "page": 4, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-23", "text": "This game is awful.\nI have been a long time fan of Star Ocean since the SNES, played throught the SO on PSX and other consoles too.\nThis game is just tediously awful.\nThe good:\n-The combat system, even though is not a great experience, it made the game entertaining.\nThe bad:\n-very limited storage, you can only carry 20 items at a given time, and that's not enough since you will be burning mana and hp like crazy fighting enemies.\n-mediocre, very mediocre storyline, god how awful can it get (I won't know cause I stoppled playing after 15 hours!)\n-characters are all forgettable, they were really lazy writing these characters\n-camera sucks\n-walking through the in-game-world is boring\n-towns and cities are all forgettable, look dead, are boring\nThe horrible:\n-dungeons take HOURS to complete, and they aren't even fun. every single dungeon in this game is a tedious grind with very tedious, dull objectivs/puzzles to work on while you are at it, all of while you are perpetually spammed by encounters and chased by enemies. dungeons in this game are absolute cancer.\n-music is dull, uninspired\n-the grind to lvl feels unrewarding and uninspiring.\nAll in all, stay away from this game. It's such a disappointment.\nI want my money back too...\nUPDATE:\nI stand by every word I wrote on this review. Additionally, if you want to play a great game with excellent character development, amazing combat system and great storyline, do play Tales of Berseria.\nTales of Berseria is everything this game should have been and more.\nI hate to say this about one of my favorite franchises of all time but this game should be destroyed and no mark of it left behind, ever, so people forget about it quickly.", "hours": 14.7, "username": "corgizilla-aficionado", "products": 57, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
