{"product_id": "609150", "page": 4, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-19", "text": "I love this game.  I love the remastered version.  So many incredible hours spent.  Don't let the Steam hours tell you anything.  I mainly play offline.  To me this is just what JRPG should be but I can not recomment this game, at least in its current (and unfortunately probably last) version.  The game current crashes to desktop without warning, making you lose potentially hours of play time.  Learn to save, some might say.  Can't.  This game still uses save points and sometimes those save points are scattered pretty far.  Or maybe you've talked to your companions about whats going on, then boom, lost it all because of the CTD.  As it stands this is game breaking.  Literally.  There is no work around I've found.\nI've made sure to report this but have yet to hear anything from the developer and I'm unfortunately not the only one who has this problem, just check the forums.  If this is fixed I'll be the first to change my review and give 2 thumbs up but right now I have to sadly shelf this one.  :(", "hours": 21.0, "user_id": "76561198052353098", "username": "mypony89", "products": 28, "found_funny": 2, "early_access": false}
