{"product_id": "609150", "page": 4, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-19", "text": "Actual Review:\nThe characters were more likable in Star Ocean 3 and that isn't a very high bar. The previous game had a much more even cast of masculine and feminine characters. This game only has two masculine characters, 6 variations of feminine characters and a cyborg that wishes you only think of him as a common electrical appliance.\nThe crafting system isn't as good as the previous title. The combat system? It's ok. I like this series combat system more than the Tales series and this game still holds to that but...\nThis game fluctuates between really bad and bizarre in its story. At least with Star Ocean 3, the story was coherent for about two thirds of the game before falling apart. This game just fell apart right at the start. **spoiler**\n\nThis review ends to talk about Lymle, the fourth party member.\nLymle Phi Sucks Rant:\nI am not sure what the design idea was to include the character, Lymle Phi, I am assumming it was an attempt at adorable. But she is creepy, forced, and miserable in every cutscene. The way she was introduced, and so early on in the game (about 2 to 4 hours in), is awful. The whole sequence of events was awful. From here on out, she will be in every cutscene adding the most awful cutsie-wootsie dribble to every occassion that just trumps everyone elses awful dialogue. Here is an example:  Edge \"The universe is in peril! We have to plan what to do next.\" Lymle \"Look I drew with crayons on the deck of the bridge, kay\". Every cutscene, similar dribble. **spoiler**\nStar Ocean 3's Roger Huxley was a much better character that filled a similar trope to Lymle Crapbasket and on top of that, he was optional. The game didn't force you to go on thieving raccoon person adventures with Roger to prove he was the bigger man in his village to his own seperate antagonist. But you could. The game offered an amusing juxtaposition of a character trying to prove he was grownup by doing a bunch of little kid dares to prove how brave he was. But with Lymle, no, you have to watch that toddler bit woven into EVERY cutscene after you get her. Also, Roger had the mentality of a 10-12 year old and his character bios says he is a 12 year old. Spot on. Lymle? Her bios says she is 15, which is 2 years older than the de jure age of consent in Japan. Her mentality? 3 year old. Her actual physical appearance? 6 year old. Screw you Japan.\nConclusion:\nI was curious to see if this series got any better after 3. Looking up the initial sales made me think it might have been good but wow, the story isn't even fun as a B-movie night idea.", "hours": 30.1, "user_id": "76561197967777612", "username": "Exsoit", "products": 339, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "609150", "page": 4, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-19", "text": "This 9 year old game has more to offer than almost every game that has come out recently.  The combat is amazing, the story is good and the animations are awesome compared to games these days. There is TONS to do after you beat the game and none of it is DLC.\nThe camera does take some getting used to but is absolutely NOT a problem at all. Especially if you use a controller.\n10/10 - I Recommend this game to anyone who enjoys RPGs / JRPGs, a good story, or if you enjoy grinding end game content.\nI applaud anyone who has completed 100% of this game because it is ridiculous to do. (I have done it years ago and now working on it again.)", "hours": 147.4, "username": "Kraglord", "products": 11, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "609150", "page": 4, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-19", "text": "Consumer Alert!  Addictive.  Play with caution!  One of my favorate Play Station game series from a time when YOU where a kid.  This is a ported game UNLIKE most.  Smooth.  NO BUGS.  NO CRASHES.  Played this game using my PDP hardwired controller (which I use on my XBOX One S mostly) and everthing worked perfect.  A beautiful Sci-fi themed RPG game with an excellant real-time battle system.  Charater stat and trait development system rated excellant.  Interesting story plot line.  Great graphics for those of you who value such sissy stuff.  Tons and tons to play.  Playe 3 times already and will play more (later).  Love and Peace to all!", "hours": 184.4, "user_id": "76561198302728949", "username": "AncientGamer", "products": 222, "early_access": false}
