{"product_id": "725020", "page": 1, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-07", "text": "Welcome to the uncurated garbage dump of the gaming world: Steam. The Steaming pile. This feels like a bad freeware Windows 3.1 game. Awful controls. Awful menus (sometimes the brighter option is selected, sometimes it's the dimmed one! Developers, this is an old lesson: Please put arrows beside menu options.) Fonts have all kinds of aliasing problems. The game is ugly as sin, with gameplay to back it up.\nThis is coming from someone who was addicted to maintaining leaderboard supremacy in the local arcade on Ms. Pacman, so maze games should be up my alley!\nI would also like to point out that the only positive review of this game belongs to an account that owns only one game: THIS ONE. Hmmmmm...\nriu525\n1 products in account\n1 review\n2 People find this review helpful, 1 person finds it *funny.*\nI challenge you to find a laugh in the review other than the fact that it's a blatant abuse of the Steam platform. People used to learn how to make games with Armor Games and on Newgrounds: free flash games. Man, I have some fantastic gaming memories from those sites! Now they want you to pay ten bucks for their horrible experiments.", "hours": 0.1, "username": "Clone", "products": 1425, "early_access": false}
