{"product_id": "748520", "page": 1, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-31", "text": "I bought a Gameboy in the early 90's sometime when it was released in Australia. It came with Tetris and I played it a lot until I got one of those cartridges that held a pile of games from someone whose father worked in Japan.\nTetris on the Gameboy was fun, addictive and cool. Tetris 27 years or so later in VR sucks\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665 it's not fun, it's not addictive and it's certainly not worth 13 \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665ing dollars.\nJesus, people complain about FO4 VR costing $60, this is what you get from indie devs for $13. Yeah 100 or so hours in FO4 VR for $60 or 20 minutes of boredom for $13. \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665 you if you complain about paying AAA price for an AAA game without it this is what we are left with. Overpriced tech demos with no interest in playing.\nLucky I got it in a bundle though and I still feel cheated.", "hours": 0.2, "username": "@Dicky Rambo", "products": 2251, "found_funny": 2, "early_access": false}
