{"product_id": "609150", "page": 5, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-19", "text": "I had played this game rather extensively on the XBox360. It was, and still remains, my favorite game. I had played it over 150 hours, beat the normal game multiple times, and grinded on every achievement that I could if only because I wanted to. The story is really good, and though I will definitely not spoil anything, I did end up crying more than once throughout the course of the game.\nThe only thing I have to say about the PC version is that I would recommend playing it with a controller. The keyboard is a bit difficult to work with, especially for someone who knows how to use the controller better for this set of game mechanics.", "hours": 2.2, "user_id": "76561198381845141", "username": "Grimmolina", "products": 103, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "609150", "page": 5, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-18", "text": "After playing the other Star Oceans, I was excited to see this get ported to PC since I do not own a PS3.  Overall, this is a surprisingly solid port without the usual weird glitches from porting console games to PC that I've usually experienced in the past.  This might be due to the fact that it was remastered but I couldn't say for certain.\nThe Game itself:\nStill follows the same generic JRPG formula of building your party with a typical quest to save the world/universe.  The dialogue is slightly above average and being able to turn on Japanese voices was a huge plus because Edge's and Welch's voices were driving me insane.  (Welch sounds like Lil from Rugrats to me)  If I had one major complaint about the game it would be the horrible camera during battle and the semi-automatic style combat.  Once you get used to the combat it's not so bad, but it doesn't feel as good as say the Tales series of games which use the same Action Battle System.  As for the camera, well, switch it to fixed in the Settings and it's not as bad.\nLove how the game gives tiny bits of fan service with Reimi's butt during her victory animation, you can tell this is made in Japan...", "hours": 84.7, "user_id": "76561198020729018", "username": "ZeroGman", "products": 286, "early_access": false}
