{"product_id": "609150", "page": 5, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-18", "text": "Gameplay is good. Got to play it on playstation before.\nBut the big but comes now, which is really sh it optimization. Game is running like 4 times the speed. They dont even care to fix that problem. Shame on you, really. And this from an japanese company. You should be ashamed.", "hours": 53.7, "user_id": "76561198062586099", "username": "Wanderer", "products": 209, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "609150", "page": 5, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-18", "text": "Finally a Star Ocean game on Steam, thank you !! I pumped about 500-600h into this game back in the PS3. If you like JRPGs, this is definitely one of the best you can find on Steam. The combat system is amazing, great soundtrack, a complete crafting system, decent character customization options, and plenty of side stuff to do (side-quests, battle trophies, data collection...).\nThe story is its weak point but only because the ending is a bit weak in my opinion (until very late in the story it's pretty good though), but when you start playing the post-game content you'll soon forgive them for it. Chronologically this is the earliest game in the series, so it's great for people who are new to the franchise, and there is a Dictionary in game that will expand the lore, if you're into this sort of hybrid fantasy/sci-fi (imo it's awesome).\nThe port runs very well, even though I have a modest laptop, I only experience some fps drops during blindside animations in bosses (not bad for an integrated GPU) and so far I haven't experience any crash/freeze or similar. Technically near perfect as usual with tri-Ace games, with almost instant loading times which are just a blessing.\nIn summary, buy this game, you'll definitely get more and better content than the price tag would suggest. And please Square-Enix remove the 4K Full HD Blah blah from the title, it looks ugly, and I get on my knees and beg you to please also port all the previous Star Ocean games (don't bother with 5, it's not representative of the quality of a Star Ocean game, or a tri-Ace game), and also the 2 Valkyrie Profile games and Resonance of Fate. It's a shame those masterpieces are lost in the ether of past-gen consoles, the world deserves to see those games on PC, where they will last for much longer (hopefully forever).", "hours": 95.4, "username": "Random Target", "products": 526, "early_access": false}
