{"product_id": "609150", "page": 5, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-17", "text": "I loved this game on PS3 and playing this remastered Full HD steam port has been great,despite the time that has passed from it's original release Star Ocean the Last Hope is still an amazing game.\nJRPGs with real time party based battle system like the ones from the \"Tales of\" series are a real treat and this games is  remarkable representative of the genre.\nOverall this game's awesome and i reccomand it to everyone.", "hours": 87.0, "user_id": "76561198160868511", "username": "Strayed Lynx", "products": 573, "found_funny": 2, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "609150", "page": 5, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-17", "text": "This game is a dumpster fire, I bought it after many saying it was better than SO 1 and 3. I'm still trying to find out what flavor paint chips they were eating when they said these lies.\nI'll start with some positives:\nThe port is fine, long as you don't have anything higher than a 60hz monitor\nIt looks nice, I never played the original version but visually it looks very nice (usually)\nOkay, onto negatives:\nThe camera is\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665 in combat it zooms in on you when you attack someone but zooms in SO much that you can't see anything happening around you, and since the enemy AI usually goes after whover you are using, it means you are just asking to be flanked, and yes I know you can switch the camera to zoom out but who even thought zooming in was a good idea in the first place?\nUsing characters during combat is a \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665ing mess, it does this awful semi lock on feature that allows you to hit what you are aiming at, sounds good, right? Well it would be if your character didn't stop the moment you hit a button to attack, what I mean is their animation is static, so say you are attacking someone and they decide to run after someone else, well you are just stuck there looking like an idiot as your animation plays at as you attack the air, and since there is INPUT LOGS (meaning the game remembers what you pressed even during an animation so it plays after the current one is done) you could be attacking air for another 2 or 3 animations leaving you completely exposed, now you could argue that is down to not mashing a button and I agree but when I'm fighting an enemy I expect them to fight ME and not just have ADHD and go somewhere else.\nThis game is not friendly to any sword character, there are a ton of flying enemies that you can only hit with a single upward attack which is halfway through your combo cycle, so all your melee units are useless in these situations unless they have symbology or an art that allows them to reach said flying enemies. You could always switch to someone who uses a bow but that's one useful unit vs 3 other worthless ones.\nRemember when I said that the game looked good? It does from afar, when you get really close to the character models, you start to see some very obvious seam lines in the character's faces depending on who you are looking at, I don't know if it was this way in the original or it's just the HD textures but they all look so doll like that it is impossible to not notice.\nTLDR; Good port for those with 60Hz monitors but the game's combat mechanics are so bad that it makes it a chore to play. Play SO 1 or 3 instead.", "hours": 6.9, "username": "Salty Skramz", "products": 299, "found_funny": 2, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "609150", "page": 5, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-17", "text": "Despite negative reviews this game does appear to work perfectly for me. I have what would now be considered a low end rig.\nGameplay seems fun and I am enjoying the story and characters so far. Very good value for money have spent alot more on games that are much worse.\nI would recommend this title to someone who wants a \"new\" RPG to play.", "hours": 9.5, "username": "zraktor", "products": 160, "early_access": false}
