{"product_id": "734580", "page": 10, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-26", "text": "There are quite a bit of people playing this game. It's kind of like when you put H1Z1 and a Team Deathmatch mode together.\nThe main mode you will probably be playing the most is where you have to destroy the enemys base. You can also loot buildings for loot like weapons, gas for your vehicles which you can craft with other items you find and food. The inventory works fine except i wish you could drag things around and equipt guns while you were looting a bag or something. You see when you loot a tent and find a gun you can only click on it once to move it to your inventory and then you have to exit the tents loot menu and then go back into your inventory to then click it again to replace it with your currently equipt weapon.\nThe games map looks quite good although i think the map is a bit too big for the ammount of people playing at this stage. When the game grows in popularity and there is hundreds of people on one server the map would be great, but right now with only 20 people some lobbies it's kind of boring walking all the way over to the enemys base just to shoot a couple people and then die and restart the whole process of walking down to their base. When there is lots of people playing I can see walking over to the middle of the map and having to push through all the enemys. That would work great with the map. It does look great though.\nThe vehicles. There are quite a few and you can counter them with bazookas or just your plain rifle. I would like to see more weapons and attatchments, right now it's kind of hard to aim at the other players that are far away from you with the default iron sight. Maybe for now just add crafting for 2x scopes or something because of how far the enemys are when you are shooting at them.\nNow. The soldiers. At first you play as a nazi so I'm guessing this game is based around WW2. The characters are quite small in game I would say increase the height and they do look pixelated. Weird considering that everything else in the game looks pretty fine. I would say that the characters bodies need some fixing up althought that might not be a priority at the moment.\nI think it would be nice if there were certain places you had to be to craft things like vehicles, because at the moment all you need is some crap and fuel to craft one. Maybe you should need something more to craft something of this scale maybe a mechanic shop.\nThere are different roles you can have on the team when you join, but you have to be certain levels to use the different soldies and right now the different roles only have different weapons and an extra thing that you would start off with. Maybe keep that the same but change the item that they start off with to work more with the role they have chosen to take.\nThis game shows great potential and I can see it being popular on steam sometime in the future if things like what I have mentioned are fixed and maybe change the UI? I'm not a big fan of the in-game UI it looks wird. I dont know maybe some people like it. I would maybe change the positioning of some of the things and make them easily viewable. Maybe put the map in the bottom right corner and have the ammunition above the health in the other corner. The place you can see what guns you are holding is pretty good. Maybe change some of the graphics on some things, not a big fan of how the map looks.\nYou can build thigns aswell like walls and chests although there is only one type of wall you cna place down and only one chest you can craft it is a thing that should be looked into. Its a cool idea being able to craft you own cover, but it needs to be executed just right, lots of games try this and do it wrong. There is also sniper towers you can build, you do need to rank up first... not sure this is a good system, they are essentially giving the experienced players an even bigger advantage to them already having played the game way longer than the newer players. I dont things that the things you can craft should be behind a level that you are forced to rank up to. If you are able to find the parts necessary to build the vehicle or sniper tower you should be able to. Giving the experienced players better things to work with is not a good way of implementing a new system like this.\nIn conclusion I think some things need to be tweaked and then we'll be having a ball.\n7 PIXELS OUT OF 11 PIXELS.", "hours": 0.4, "username": "sbondog", "products": 314, "early_access": true}
