{"product_id": "731230", "page": 1, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-04", "text": "It's Snake.\nAnd the snake doesn't follow an apple, but a pomegranate. For some reasons it doesn't make me take screenshots but you can see the images in the game store page.\nBasically, the whole 1\u20ac game consists of a blue snake on a green field, chasing red pomegranates and sometimes white flowers (or biscuits or Idk what, the graphics are so Commodore-64 that I can't distinguish anything).\nThe only thing I can say is that, if the snake is simply a palette swap of the green field turned blue, those aren't apples but pomegranates.\nThis is an occasion for adding something interesting in this review - one of my favourite singers, Mark\u00e9ta Irglov\u00e1, debuted in 2011 with an awesome album entitled Anar and entirely drawn by an Iranian-American female illustrator called Nahid Hagigat. Anar (\u0627\u0646\u0627\u0631 ) means actually \"pomegranate\" in Persian and the cover art depicts a hand-drawn pomegranate. Yeah, the album is some really awesome pop and the pomegranates in this game are exactly the same as that cover art.\nOk, really, there's nothing else to say about this game.\nProbably Snake is one of those games which have no copyright, since we used to play it really for months on our Nokia phones at the high school ('cos back in the days when I was a teenager well cell phones simply didn't exist xD).\nThis one is simply a red and green colored version of Snake.\nYou can not do anything.\nNo remapping of the keys (only directional keys work), no options, no music, no levels. It's the Snake you all played on your phones fifteen years ago, probably not copyrighted and so completely plagiarized and copied without a single difference (apart from the pomegranates that aren't clearly apples).\nAnyways, as a liberal conservative guy, I admire the developers. They added 3000 achievements and managed to smuggle somehow an already-made game, sell it for 1\u20ac (ok, 0,10\u20ac on discount, not that high if you take into account how much life costs here in the richest regions of Europe..) and make profits every day.\nBy the way, achievements pop randomly. I have tried to be stuck at 25 points and I was at 250 achievements unlocked with no reason.\nFor the review's sake anyways game-wise it's obviously an abysmal negative vote.", "hours": 5.0, "username": "Helevorn", "products": 781, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "731230", "page": 1, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-11-24", "text": "Right, you might look at this game and think to yourself  \"Hey, I loved Snake as a kid, I might buy this game\". If you buy this game expecting your generic snake clone than you're bang out of luck kid.\nThis. Is. A. Masterpeice.\nThe difficulty spike is harsh but fair and the enemy you face is yourself and time. How deep is that?! This is life in a nutshell.\nBUT WAIT! THERE'S MORE!\nUnder the simplicity of the game lies a brilliant thematic story; you are lucifer morningstar and you are attempting to destory the apples of eden to gain profound knowledge to reclaim his place in heaven...through sheer force.\nThe more apples you eat the more powerful you become until you take over the mortals world and then Heaven.\nPlus theres loads of achievements for those capable of obtaining them, though it is extremely difficult to get even a handfull of them.", "hours": 13.6, "user_id": "76561198276224940", "username": "Thomas", "products": 18, "found_funny": 12, "early_access": false}
