{"product_id": "234820", "page": 1, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-11-24", "text": "This utility makes it fairly easy to backup drivers and to search for new drivers & updating.\nI've had this software for quite a while and for a couple of years had used it about once a month or so to check for new drivers.\nBut then after upgrading to a new computer system (about 7 months ago as I write this review) that runs Windows 10, I had forget about it for a while. Then I noticed that there was recently a big update for it, so I just used it to update some outdated drivers that it found (around a dozen) and I would say that my system is running even more smooth and stable now.\nI also like the Device Monitor which gives current stats on things such as usage (Temps, Utilization, Speeds, etc..) of the Processors, Display Adaptor (graphics card), Motherboard, Memory and Disk Drives.\nThe Desktop Backup feature I found to be quite useful too. If you end up having a lot of desktop icons (like I do), and if you've ever played a game that perhaps it crashed or didn't exit properly and then to find your desktop icons all scattered out of place, then it's really handy to use this software to restore your desktop icons to their posistions from a backup you made (try to remember to use this software to do a desktop backup occasionally, perhaps after adding new or rearranging desktop icons).\n~\nIf you're looking for a software that helps to make it fairly easy and convenient to backup and update drivers and can save you a lot of time, then I could recommend getting Driver Fusion. In some cases you may notice an improvement in your system's stability and performance after updating some drivers (and some drivers in which you may not have even known otherwise were way outdated or that newer / better drivers were available for some things).", "hours": 9.0, "username": "Mystix", "products": 857, "early_access": false}
