{"product_id": "609150", "page": 6, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-16", "text": "The game itself is amazing, and undoubtedly you'll enjoy playing through it. My only complaint is that there are some performance issues that I've come across. Blindsiding massively drops my FPS and I have yet to determine why, and if you have a high refresh rate Monitor, you'll be unable to play it in fullscreen as the game speed is effectively doubled. Other than that, the game is completely worth the purchase.", "hours": 40.3, "compensation": "Product received for free", "username": "Bastion", "products": 57, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "609150", "page": 6, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-16", "text": "I don't understand, this game get bad review because some people don't have good enough computer to run this game, no sound, or they can't play with a controller.\nThis game run perfectly on my laptop:\nIntel Core i5-2450M 2.5 GHz\nRAM 8GB DDR3\n500GB SATA 5400rpm\nNVIDIA GeForce GT 630M 2GB DDR3\nWindows 7\nNever crash. Sometimes when starting this game, you have to re-assign the full screen option. The only lag I found is when you're at Purgatorium and the secret door open animation plays.\nFor controller, you can use x360ce. Works with any controllers.\nPros:\n- Great graphic, with great FPS. Even though I'm using middle-class laptop\n- Love the battle system. Enhanced version of Till The End of Time\n- Crafting, Private Action, Battle Thropies, ship furnishing\n- Great music from Motoi Sakuraba (Tales series, Golden Sun, Valkyrie Profile)\nCons:\n- The story and characters is not good enough compared to Second Story and Till The End of Time.\n- I don't like the english voice acting (I had to switch to japanese voice)\n- Yeah. Doll looking characters.", "hours": 93.7, "username": "haskav", "products": 21, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "609150", "page": 6, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-15", "text": "Great port that I've been running maxed on my middle-of-the-road system (i5-4590/GTX 960/10gb RAM/Windows 10).  Much speedier load times than the console versions and you get all the aesthetic options from the PS3 version of the game, which means you can ditch the unnerving 3D portraits and horrific English voice acting straight away.  The game runs at 60fps and there's a robust selection of graphics settings to play around with.\nSadly, the game still sucks beacause of:\n- Creepy anime sex dolls vaguely emoting every trope under the sun at each other!\n- tri-Ace's inability to develop a game that doesn't have annoying pacing issues - hope you enjoy being railroaded into talking to every NPC, grinding for levels and inventions to get past unreasonable difficulty spikes and wandering around aimlessly at regular intervals!\n- A god awful racket of a soundtrack by Motoi Sakuraba that's so bad it actually tarnishes my memories of the preceding games' music!\n- The worst characters in the series!\n- Since it cannot be stressed enough, the WORST characters in the series!\n- The worst writing in the series (handily unseating the previous champ, Till the End of Time)!\nAt least the post-game content is decent and you get four person teams back, right?  Not sure why SE thought The Last Hope was the best introduction to the series for Steam users, but look at it this way: no matter which installment comes out next, it'll be an improvement.  Maybe grab this one on the cheap during a sale.", "hours": 12.8, "username": "Reinveil von Megabee", "products": 727, "found_funny": 6, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "609150", "page": 6, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-15", "text": "I wish I could recommend and rate this game a good one, as I loved the original...\nBut this remaster however, has an issue, the intro had sound, but the titlescreen had no sound what-so-ever...\nThen I started a new game, the intro where Edge talks had sound, but surprise! There was no sound in game what-so-ever...\nSo I changed settings, restarted, varified game files and such to no avail... Still no sound.\nUntil this game gets a patch to fix it's issues, I can't recommend this remaster...\nIs it a bird? Is it a plane? NO! It should've gone to \"Bugsmashers\"", "hours": 0.3, "user_id": "76561198023990941", "username": "Solus White", "products": 251, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "609150", "page": 6, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-15", "text": "I wisht hat I could give this game a psotive review, because the game itself is great. But, don't bother trying to play this through Steam. If you're wanting to use a DS4 controller to play this then good luck getting it to work. If they could only have fixed this issue then my rating would have been different.", "hours": 18.7, "user_id": "76561198281800595", "username": "Soyboy McCoy", "products": 39, "found_funny": 2, "early_access": false}
