{"product_id": "609150", "page": 7, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-13", "text": "I bought this title swiftly in hopes that Square-Enix is encouraged to bring the rest of the series to PC. Nothing more.\nI owned this on the 360 previously. The combat was solid, which is bread and butter for a Star Ocean title. The music matched the overall familiarity of the series. Here, there is an obvious improvement to the graphical quality. That said, everything else falls apart. Even if I try to approach it as an individual game it is not worthwhile from the aspects of characters, story, and cohesion with the rest of the Star Ocean series.\nI reiterate: I am here as a Star Ocean diehard. I want the rest of the series on PC. I recommend it for those like me. For everyone else, it will all be about the combat.\nRead a long-form review here:", "hours": 101.2, "user_id": "76561198034350556", "username": "zerohourseraphim", "products": 97, "early_access": false}
