{"product_id": "609150", "page": 7, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-13", "text": "Like most people, I had issues installing this game. It's a shame a functional installation wasn't prepared for the launch, but considering how optimized this game is, I couldn't be happier making it work.\nI run this game on a i5 2600k, 560ti 1g. It works at FULL FPS. I even tried it on a 10 year old laptop and it ran TOO WELL for my specs.\nOnce working, this game is flawless, even on a \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665 pc from WAY back. I've bought this game for xbox360, ps3 and now the pc. The pc version is by far the most stable, the most LENIENT and OPTIMIZED version of this game. Everything runs MAGICALLY well.\nThe gameplay is the gameplay, nothing's changed. It's star ocean 4. The plot is good, but the presentation of it is not. It's a weaboo game, tuned to the max, but if you can ignore that, you'll LOVE the environments, the bosses, and most importantly, the FIERCE battle system. You can pull off some crazy\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665if you put effort into it.\nMost new people wouldn't know it, but this game should have been the first in the series, because that's what it is. So if you're worried about playing all the other games before this, don't be.\nBuy this game to support Tri-ace. I'm sure square enix didn't give 2 \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665 bout this release, but tri-ace put a lot of effort, on a tight budget, to make this amazing game.\nStory - 2/10\ngameplay - 10/10\nDEM GRAPHIX - 8/10", "hours": 18.2, "user_id": "76561197987580459", "username": "Total Lag", "products": 37, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "609150", "page": 7, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-12", "text": "Favorite JRPG series ever finally on Steam. 10/10 will play forever again.", "hours": 52.1, "username": "JacobTehAwesome", "products": 350, "early_access": false}
