{"product_id": "609150", "page": 8, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-11", "text": "I feel very nostalgic playing this again in 2017. This version is full of bugs right now but lets ignore that for now. Back in 2010 I bought this for the xbox 360 to satisfy my jrpg needs after finishing tales of symphonia to hell. I thought there were too many cutscenes at first and I couldn't really get into the story so I let my friend borrow the game for a while. He told me, \"Jackey, you didn't buy a game you bought a movie\". He was right. This game is a wonderful movie and I ended up loving every second of it. The battle system is very tales esque, not quite as good but pretty up there. The characters are very likeable. The story is pretty good. Buy this game.\nAlso just Monika.", "hours": 17.6, "username": "Bioburn", "products": 174, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
