{"product_id": "609150", "page": 8, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-10", "text": "TL:DR Proceed to Pros and Cons (just buy tales of destiny 1 & 2 for PS1 that has more content)\nMy review is based on Universe Difficulty which is equivalent to Hard mode, was able to unlock it by using a friend's save game so I could have almost complete encyclopedia. Oh, be prepared to fix the resolution issue for about 2-3 hours that I think they purposely left so you won't be able to refund after fixing it. Go for KALDAREN'S FIX (forgot the name)\n**Do note this is in my own opinion and experience, but still I beg you to BUY THIS GAME and share my suffering. This game is by far the one disappointment for me and because of that I'll think twice before purchasing future square enix games from now on as this game feels like a Chinese Bootleg of \"Tales of Franchise\"**\nThis game is a Remaster of a previous star ocean, and yes SQUARE ENIX. So, take on the adventures of:\nA Pasty White Dude that has a hair where all the budget went to and gets stronger by with the power of friendship and love.\nA generic anime tsundere girl that acts all irritatingly cute every time and gets her\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665camera focused every battle after winning.\nA green gay elf boi that dances in the battlefield.\nAnother generic child girl that also acts irritatingly cute and dramatic who is overpowered.\nA middle-aged megaman whose rockets miss  90% of the time because it hits the ground and the wall behind him.\nAn Emo elf boi that wields a scythe. (well yea coz he's emo it's a requirement)\nOH MY GAD Another generic elf that is over-sexualized and every battle win focuses on you know where. Her Feet, where else?\nAn Angel.. i'm soo done.\nA Cat.. jfc, really? a cat... (She's a trap,btw)\nOkay so, be prepared to face the walking simulator of MMORPG sized maps with little enemies and treasures to be found as you'll be walking, dashing and walking for 2 hours because save points are that far apart in search of a cute for a disease that turns you into stone then after that into a raging generic lizard boi. (yes... it turns you to stone first and after that into a gecko, really square enix?)\nAs you delve into the immerse over-dramatic, repetitive acting and dialogue that takes 30minutes of poker-faced characters talk about how they wish they could've helped that guy, how they could've done better again and again then you'll skip it to go into another cutscene that just does the same routine in a different room AGAIN AND AGAIN so you skip it and they do it again on the first room! So you skip it and now you don't know where to \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665ing go, so you google it and find out you're just gonna go to a town somewhere or a planet and talk about the same sh*t again then you mash the action button because that's all you're really gonna do... mash it for 60 hours and you'll finish the game.\nYou know what I'll just say the pros and cons to get it over with:\nPros:\nSays 13 hours steam in-game hours but my save time hours is already at 40+ hours haven't found any pros yet. Oh wait, I guess it has good graphics and apparently that's where all the budget went and Reimi's\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665.. it is a remaster after all.\nCons:\nSave points are very far apart, be sure to have at least 1-2 hours to play the game.\nBonus Boards aren't carried over if you die and/or load you lose it all.\nMMORPG sized maps that will have you walking most of the time.\nCamera isn't properly adjusted to your actions, so if you were to walk into a small corridor/pathway. Well.. goodluck.\nUnnecessary and over-dramatic animations of opening doors and/or going into a different room\nCutscenes that take forever just to talk about the same thing over and over for about 3 or more cutscenes again.\nJuggling (air and ground) Mechanism. Apparently only applies to the enemy side they can juggle you forever but you can't do the same to them, after successfully juggling up to 3 hits they become invincible for some time but doesn't aply to you. So if it's you alone vs 4 enemies once one of them hits you and you stagger don't expect to be able to move. But if it's 4 of you against 1 enemy left you'll spend minutes chasing him down because that enemy won't do anything other than run around and you're unable to stagger him due to that mechanism.\nTargeting System. You can only target what is closest to you, even if you change target pressing start button it will return to the closest after a few seconds so hitting what you want is messed up and you end up getting the aggro of every enemy instead.\nAggro/Threat Ration. Okay so this is both a con and an exploit. Apparently Aggro only applies to the character you use regardless of their damage. Use your weakest character to hit a boss even if dmg is 0 until the boss aims for you after that run around the battle area while you fiddle with your phone and let your ranged unit that does 1k normal dmg and 3k on a crit hit the boss' back(which is most boss' weak point) because f*ck that character that hurts you right and before you know it. You win.\nResolution Issue. Game started being in a 4K resolution and you can't minimize it because you're unable to see it in your computer screen so you end up wasting 2 hours just to look for a fix and before you know it you can't refund it anymore. YEY!\nEDIT:\nPros:\nYeap. still nothing.\nCons I forgot to add before\nSkills Set\na. WHY DID YOU GIVE A HEALING AND SUPPORT MAGIC THAT COST A LOT OF MANA TO THE ONE CHAR WITH LOW INT AND MP?!\nb. WHY DID YOU GIVE TAUNT SKILL TO YOUR HITTER WHO HAS LOW HP AND DEF?! FOR WHAT IS THE PURPOSE?!\nTerrain and other obstacles.\nA small stone blocks you while a medium sized boulder is something you can pass thru. just wow.\nA plant that allows you to pass thru while another plan that looks exactly the same sometimes is considered as an obstacle.\nQuests. Do you remember those irritating fetch quests from MMORPG games? Yea? Well you'll do it with this game from start until new game+. Only difference is in this game it'll be planet to planet distance and would take a minimum of 30minute walk or more... yea i'm sure it's more than that.\nDifficulty. Heck doesn't matter what difficulty just spam X and you'll win even boss battles. OR do what I do due to the weak targeting and aggro system the game has.\na. Use the pasty white boi to get the aggo then let the boss focus you and make sure the wall is behind you so your archer \"DOES 3k dmg\" from the back and being ignored.\nb. Or use the overpowered midget that does 0 ranged dmg and run around while you have 3 ranged unit that 'DOES 3k dmg EACH\" from the back while being ignored.\nAmbush System. You need to let mobs chase you so you can chain them up for bonus exp and bonus board which is very difficult because they'll chase you for just barely 2 seconds then after ignore you for more than 5 seconds while going back or opposite of where that mob chased you.\nSkills. or more precisely \"lack of it\" to be more precise. At level 20 you only get 2 usable skill.\nCombos. Upon trial and error. There is no combo to this game other than spam action and your skill which is LT/RT(3x). The only variety of hits you get is:\nAttack Variety for short distance.\nAttack Variety for  long distance.\nAttack Variety for an arial enemy.\nThat's about it. Tilting the analog in any direction doesn't matter.\nBlindsides or Dodge. Is the only unique sh*t this game has which only works for regular enemies. Won't work on bosses coz they all have AoE and you'll get hit either way furthermore, Old Megaman Dude flies to the heavens above when he blindsides but still gets hit either. I guess the hitbox remains on the ground instead of wherever your character is.\nRepetitive Voice Grunts. If your character levels up, wins a battle, gets hit or uses a field skill just has one for everything not unless you swap between japs and english from time to time which is what I do to remove boredom and sometimes I just do sound Off and Music On.\nRepetitive sounds for sound effects. Yea just that doesn't have variety.\nGame size is 50GB. All went to Hair", "hours": 12.3, "username": "Larania", "products": 643, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
