{"product_id": "609150", "page": 8, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-09", "text": "Not The best game in the series but still enjoyable nontheless.\nfor those debating if they should buy it due to bugs i did a full walkthough including post game dungeons.\nI found no game breaking bugs that make it unplayable performance was better than i expected for a port.\nfor those that have high end sound based cards over 48000hz you would want to turn it down to 48000 or else the game will crash after it's set the game is fully playable. Until they provide a proper patch to address the issue\nThe story is not it's strong suit but the combat can be more than a little addicting with blindsides etc. One can also engross themselves in the high ammount of side quests and bonus monsters one can find in the field. With the battle trophy system it's important to actually try to get at minimum 50% per character to go past the origional level cap\nOverall it's a really fun to play game decent graphics fun combat system and overpowered item creation (tho its use isn't immidiate)", "hours": 36.7, "user_id": "76561198247471126", "username": "Deathscythe432", "products": 21, "early_access": false}
