{"product_id": "708340", "page": 1, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-10-10", "text": "First Look Video:\nThis was kinda fun and goofy in a cartoonish way. The notion of a Shark invading the land is great. You essentially just rove around wreaking havoc and eating the town. Its got a fair bit of potential with the ability to purchase upgrades, weapons, appearance modifiers and more.\nCurrently there's not a ton to do in the game. I got tired of it in around 10-15minutes of exploration. But I think it has potential to be a pretty fun game full of little mini games, upgrades, and possibly new unlockable environments.\nI would say the biggest barrier to entry currently is the conrols. They seem more akin to something you'd see in a dog fighting sim, rather than a game about flopping around as a shark and eating people. I would say that could use some simplification.\nOtherwise I found this reasonably fun. Would recommend it. Though again theres not a ton to do in the game yet. Go ahead and watch my linked video if you'd like a first hand look at what the gameplay is like.", "hours": 0.6, "username": "Larry Chupacabra", "products": 881, "early_access": true}
{"product_id": "708340", "page": 1, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-10-08", "text": "For my full LPR just follow the link.\n\nThere was a lot of hate in the comment section leading up to this games early access release, and I get it, Steamers are burned out with the string of bad releases and ripoff Unity games. I really liked the artistic design I saw on display with it's exaggerated polygonal style, took the dive and bought it. Good game, all the basics are pretty squared away and it's got the makings of a really good game. The dev just needs to sharpen up the controls (mostly the camera really), clean up a few glitches (falling through the map), and add some missions/objectives. This is one to watch if unsure, and buy if you like this style of game and want to support devs who are actually trying in a time when it seem like fewer and fewer care to.", "hours": 1.5, "username": "EELectric Productions", "products": 736, "early_access": true}
