{"product_id": "335070", "page": 2, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "text": "The new off-road track Buggyland Fuencarral, Spain has been released for the 2017 VRC Worlds and is now available as dlc on Steam.\nBuggyland will host the 2017 VRC Worlds events for 1:8 nitro and electric buggies and for the popular 1:10 electric short course trucks.\nAlso the highly anticipated 1:8 nitro on-road GT3 class is now available on Steam. This new class will make its debut on December 3rd with the VRC Worlds event at Cincinnati, USA.\nBoth products are available as DLC's, for Lifetime All-Inclusive members the new content will become availble to them automatically (to be sure, do a 'Full check' when the Updater has started).\nEnjoy the new GT3 class and Buggyland, and the 2017 VRC Worlds.", "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "335070", "page": 2, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "text": "Yesterday the 2017 VRC Worlds kicked off with 3 events on 2 new tracks which are now released.\nThe 1:10 short course trucks 13.5T Spec is the first class to race on the brandnew Buggyland Fuencarral track located near Madrid, Spain.\nRallyX kicks off at the new RallyX 3 track which has been added to the RallyX car and tracks pack which now contains a total of 8 RallyX tracks!.\n1:10 Nitro sedans Spec race at the Cincinnatti on-road track, 1:8 nitro sportscars and GT3 Worlds events are to follow later.\nThe 1:8 nitro GT3 class is now also available, this class will make its first appearance during the 2017 VRC Worlds.\nThe new content is immediately available for VRC Steam Lifetime All-Inclusive members.\nDon't miss out!\nVRC WORLD's A-MAIN from last year:\nhttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=HtxDFMqpM_o\nBuggyland trailer:\nhttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=kM_ZV9sxnLo\nGT3 trailer:\nhttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=MrklSOlGJnQ", "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "335070", "page": 2, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "text": "\u00a0\nThis new class offers a different 1:8 nitro on-road racing experience, easy to drive and loads of fun. The chassis is based on the well-known 1:8 nitro chassis but equipped with a front and rear differential and thus rear and front brakes, a slightly less potent .21 engine and fitted with special Super Soft rubber tires, this chassis handles quite different than the 1:8 nitro prototype class, ideal for super close racing.\nhttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=MrklSOlGJnQ\n\u00a0\nThe new GT3 class will be released middle of November and will have its very first event at the 2017 VRC Worlds starting December 2nd.\n\u00a0\nDON'T MISS IT - BE THERE...", "early_access": false}
