{"product_id": "234820", "page": 4, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-03-26", "text": "tl dr;\ncons\ndoes not work as intended - it did not detect any \"updated\" driver for my hardware but other rival software did.\npros(?)\nachievements\n+----------------------------+\nHealth check: still display some junk available drivers even after filtering only WHQL drivers. It cannot even match 'Provider' name to increase reliability which is potentially risky for the average user.\nDevice control: tried to backup some drivers and it saved an .inf file. after that, I've try to install but it did not recognized the backup.\nDevice monitor: seems pretty nice but does not work, it did not display anything besides some incomplete hardware parameters\nDriver cleaner: works for specific manufactorers, it lists some popular brands. Well, it worked as intended, as the test machine was Intel based I've chosen to detect registry keys wih 'AMD' keywords and removed them, very simple.\nDesktop: backuped my '0 icons desktop', weird.\n+----------------------------+\n'Treexy' has added me in friends list recently, let's see what they want to talk", "hours": 8.2, "compensation": "Product received for free", "username": "\uff24\uff41\uff2e\uff59\uff41\uff4e", "products": 1740, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "234820", "page": 4, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-03-06", "text": "After 6 months of abandonment, Driver Fusion Premium has been updated. New GUI, new drivers, it's finally useful again. Just have to hope the developer doesn't go AWOL again...", "hours": 62.4, "username": "Solarisfire", "products": 789, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "234820", "page": 4, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-02-05", "text": "OLD REVIEW:\n\"Updates\" to older drivers on Windows 10.\nNEW REVIEW:\nSince the 5.0 update it's finally working. The new interface is pretty and the new polished features are awesome. Thanks Treexy for not abandoning this, glad you came back.\nNow I would definitely recommend it to anyone looking for a simple and quick solution to update all their drivers.", "hours": 13.1, "username": "Valk", "products": 115, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "234820", "page": 4, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-02-04", "text": "OK, so Ill wait until the new version becomes available to review as I cannot use it anymore because I forgot my password and will have to wait until fully integrated into steam. I cannot activate the product again with a different email.\n****Use to be an awesome app for updating a new PC build or any PC for that matter, but I paid 40 dollars for someone to steal my money and quit updating it. Developer should be found and jailed for theft or steam should be found accountable.", "hours": 9.1, "username": "LazyCakes", "products": 43, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "234820", "page": 4, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-01-21", "text": "Just received an email from support and, basically they are working on the problem with Windows 10 Anniversary update.\nThey suggested a work-around:\n\u2022  Click Windows menu and click on \"Power\" button\n\u2022  Hold SHIFT key and click on \"Restart\" (or Update and Restart)\n\u2022  At the next screen, click on \"Troubleshoot\"\n\u2022  Click on \"Advanced Options\"\n\u2022  Click \"Startup Settings\"\n\u2022  Click \"Restart\" and the PC will reboot\n\u2022  Press number 7 for \"Disable driver signature enforcement\"\nWindows will now restart normally and Driver Fusion Premium will work.  Tested successfully on my PC, running Windows 10 Pro, 64 bit.\nChanged my review to reflect the work-around.  Have patience and the Treexy team will get this all sorted out.\nOld Review:  It used to be really great but the developers have appeared to abanoned it.  Windows 10 drivers will not update.  Don't waste $40 on this!!!\nEDIT:  I have sent an email to\nand am awaiting a reply.  I'll post it here when (or if) I get one.", "hours": 8.3, "user_id": "76561198028187030", "username": "milesohtoole", "products": 96, "found_funny": 2, "early_access": false}
