{"product_id": "741770", "page": 1, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-11-24", "text": "Santa's Vacation is a little bit of early Xmas fun. It's probably going to be more enjoyable for young ones, and may even help them learn how to use a mouse and keyboard and how to interact with a videogame. It's certainly bright, colorful and has a little charm of its own. Older gamers may still find a bit of challenge there - however - the gameplay niggles on repetitive and re-using former levels with one additional change isn't a particularly great development standard.\nBut for what it's worth, how it looks, plays and feels - for that ever impending time of year - it's a-ok in my book.\nReviewed in The Steaming Pile #2:", "hours": 0.4, "username": "markymint", "products": 152, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "741770", "page": 1, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-11-22", "text": "I'll be honest: I only bought this game because I saw that it had just come out today, November 22, 2017, and that it had no user reviews. Since it was so cheap, I decided to buy it and write the very first review. As I write these words, I see no other reviews of this game. If it's not, and someone somehow gets to it before me, I don't really care.\nThis game isn't really worthy of a paragraphs-long epic on how terrible it is. It's more of just a kinda mediocre, confusing, hard-to-control holiday cash grab game. If your kid super super wants to buy it, like, okay, whatever. There are better games out there for 8-year-old Susie that have more passion and effort put into them.", "hours": 0.4, "user_id": "76561198101768806", "username": "Writer Of Books", "products": 41, "found_funny": 3, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "609150", "page": 9, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-09", "text": "Don't really know how I found this game fun back in the day, the combat is all the same. Other then that the story isn't bad.", "hours": 0.7, "user_id": "76561198011065990", "username": "Fugnuk", "products": 208, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "609150", "page": 9, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-09", "text": "Played another game of the series on PS2 (Till the end of time) and enjoyed every minute of it. Playing this on PC, super fun - though the game has some compatibility issues, still works and can be configured so all good.\nThe only major flaw with this game is the inability to target enemies, which can drive you mad - but once you get used to that flaw, you can work around it.", "hours": 4.9, "username": "Poctim", "products": 199, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "609150", "page": 9, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-08", "text": "Wow, I really enjoyed this game! My first time playing any of the Star Ocean games.\nStory... I was surprised at how invested I had gotten into the story. I'd say that although some of the characters are lacking in development and relevance, you're main roaster is pretty nice. ( Wish there was a bit more time for us to get to bond with them.)\nWithout saying any spoilers, I would say I enjoyed the journey more than the actual ending of the game. I felt that unsatisfying feeling when the game came to it's close. ( Maybe due to the fact the game's story felt short or maybe due to the game simply not checking those boxes I had hoped it would by the end.)\nGameplay and graphics...\nAlthough I wouldn't say the graphics are timeless, I would say they are pretty easy to get use to. The character models are nice and their eyes are very expressive, which I really enjoyed.\nI had no issues with the port apart for some minor lag when opening doors during a particular dungeon and the start of a fight. The lag was quickly resolved and did not cause further issues during my play time.\nThe fighting system needs some adjustment. I would recommend trying other characters and not sticking to Edge. I feel there's probably a better character out there to play as.\nWARNING, These bosses don't mess around, you better be ready!\nAlso friendly reminder, there's no menu save and save spots are far apart. So Save when ever you get the chance.\nOverall... I would say it made for a very enjoyable experience. Personally, I feel this is definitely a game to pick up and try out. As long as you can get passed the bump that is the battle system, It's really great.\nThank you for allowing me to play this game via steam, really enjoyed it. Definitely will pick up this game again in a few months.", "hours": 36.2, "username": "hiya_dollz", "products": 71, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "609150", "page": 9, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-08", "text": "One of the best non-turn based Rpgs out there. Only thing negative I would have to say is that some of the cut-scenes can drag on far too long. Aside from that though it is one of the best rpgs out there.\nPros\n+Very long story\n+Fun combat\n+Great items\n+Fun dialouge\n+2 Bonus dungeons for post-game\nCons\n+Characters can look doll-like\n+Some cut scenes are crazy long\nIf you like rpgs at all buy this game.....", "hours": 59.3, "user_id": "76561197968376621", "username": "rivet\u2122(>.<)", "products": 261, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "609150", "page": 9, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-08", "text": "This is my 1st time playing any star ocean game, so for me it's pretty good. It took me an hour to get through the opening tutorial so if you've never played this game before and would like to possibly return it if you don't like it, then don't waste time with it and get right into the story.\nI will say the learning curve is a bit different as I've played lots of Square RPG's back in the day but times have changes from 2d Final Fantasy games to Star Ocean.\nThe only real issue I have with the game is the resolution, sure it supports 4k monitors but I have an 34\" Ultrawide 1440p Monitor. The game does not have a resolution 3440x1440 so I Can't even run it at full screen, do you have any idea how annoying that is playing on such a big monitor with 2560x1080 resolution.\nThe story is ok, I can't stand the main character in the game he seems like a whiny punk ***** if you know what I mean, hopefully it's just this short phase after a certain event but god, it's awful. I played in English up to this point but i've since switched to Japanese voices and it's a much better experience for me personally as I am an avid Anime watcher, this makes it bearable to deal with the terrible voice acting *english voice actors*\nThe price for the game is pretty nice, I know i've gotten my monies worth from the entertainment but I don't see myself going to 100% the game if thats an option let alone replaying it on a harder difficulty.\nIf they issue a 3440x1440 resolution I'd be much happier though.", "hours": 19.9, "username": "sLpFhaWK", "products": 160, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "609150", "page": 9, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-08", "text": "I own the installment of the seires for my PS2, and seeing this on steam was a real nice sight to see. Never owned a PS3 so I finally got a chance to play this!\nIt's a fantastically remastered game in terms of graphics, although some of the animations seem a tad unnatural and twitchy, it's very aesthetically pleasing to look at. That combined with combat mechanics (that I haven't quite mastered) from the previous installments that fans loved makes this game a very nice treat.\nIt's not perfect, however. Let's start with that camera, I find it extremely awkward to switch my right hand from my keyboard and my mouse constantly, which is a must due to the way the camera is aranged (using the arrow keys for camera adjustment and ENTER and BACKSPACE to interact with your surroundings, and attack/jump in battles). I digress, after making the mental adjustment and training yourself to switch your right hand to the mouse for battles, the game is a lot easier to play.\nOverall, the 2.5 hours of current gameplay lead me to conclude that this game is a definite steal for $19 and is worth a chunk of your precious time.", "hours": 5.0, "user_id": "76561198202533320", "username": "Jougi_Yoshi", "products": 2, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "609150", "page": 9, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-08", "text": "Star Ocean - First Departure and Second Evolution for PSP are some of my favorite RPGs, and The Last Hope doesn\u2019t even come close to the charm those two games had.\nSure the combat is great in this one and has lots of mechanics to keep you busy.  But there is lots for me to dislike about this game in the fanchise.\nEveryone's faces just look creepy when playing this remastered version.  This game was just not meant for 4K.  Luckily I couldn\u2019t see their creepy eyes when playing the muddied low res PS3 version.\nThe animations and camera outside of combat are nausea inducing which makes exploring an absolute a pain. Even with depth of field and motion blur turned off their was no way for me to change camera speed or the terrible camera \u201cfloatiness\u201d to alleviate this issue.  The camera will keep moving for a good second after you let go. Also character movement is unresponsive in and out of combat since it takes them time to begin their walking animation.\nI don\u2019t really know what else this game has to offer because I only played a decent 5 or so hours on the ps3. Why I bought this game? Who \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665ing knows. It's not worth it with much better rpgs out there.", "hours": 0.3, "username": "Long Dong Never Die", "products": 944, "found_funny": 2, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "609150", "page": 9, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-08", "text": "I'll get to my header title in a bit, but here are my pros and cons for this game.\n1. The graphics were remastered.\n2. Myuria and her right bouncing tiddy.\n3. Myuria and her left bouncing tiddy. (Her left tiddy is covered up a bit because of the shawl she wears. Therefore, her other tiddy gets a higher ranking from me.)\n4. A fluid combat system that is easy to learn but deep enough to satisfy those who like the tough difficulty settings.\n5. Myuria and her mini skirt. (Gotta love the occasionally lecherous camera angle when Myuria gets to do the battle pose.\n)\n6. Item invention is less annoying in this Star Ocean than it was in Till the End of Time, but that's not saying much.\n7. The game is resonably priced for what it is.\n1. DO NOT Alt-Tab in this game. Just don't do it.\n2. There can be hours between save points.\n3. The \"bonus board\" must be one of the most frustrating inventions in game design history. If you like to play as a melee character, the \"bonus board\" will have you using all the profanity you know...loudly and often.\n4. The game has many moments where you can't backtrack to other places you have been before due to the story.\n5. I guess the game does have a story, but the cutscenes are mostly meaningless. Some are cringe-worthy.\n6. The cast of characters leaves much to be desired. I couldn't get into the characters back in the PS3 days, and I can't today.\n7. The English voice acting was particularly sterile in this Star Ocean. If that sort of thing bothers you, at least you do have Japanese voice and English subtitles.\n8. Oh great anime god in Nippon, please save us from Welch! >.<\n9. Where is my post-game save file? No, seriously, where did it go? As it turns out, I don't care enough about the game for me to play the game after Edge & Co. save the pangalactic community, but it's still annoying that my post-game save file disappeared.\n1. The game has grinding points built into the game, but it doesn't bother explaining where those are. If you guess wrong on the grinding points, you may end up loading a save file many hours of gameplay backwards.\n2. Some of the grinding points will have you spending a ridiculous amount of time at those points because the astute gamer figures out that better rewards per hour of play can be attained only at those certain places in the game.\n3. The game intends on the gamer playing until level 250 to fill up their skill masteries, and it is up to the gamer to figure out what to do with the seemingly epic mismatch between skills to master and available skill points. And since a character respec option does not exist, the astute gamer's best option remains to amass a large quantity of skill points, save the game, then try investing in one skill. Then reload the game, invest in a different skill, try it out on some enemies, and so on.\n4. When can and when should the gamer go back to the previously-visited planets to open up the elemental-magic-locked chests? This game secret is completely unnecessary and adds nothing but frustration to the game.\nIf you are still reading this review and you have not yet played the game but you will do so soon, take my advice and use all 20 save files. Stagger your saves like a crazy person. You'll thank yourself for doing so.", "hours": 51.9, "user_id": "76561198085941437", "username": "sawanoguchi", "products": 453, "found_funny": 3, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "609150", "page": 9, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-08", "text": "One of my personal favourites, even when it came out years ago.\nA lot of story but still fun and the grind isn't that bad or necessary depending how you play.", "hours": 60.2, "user_id": "76561198053205483", "username": "Chicken Nugget", "products": 127, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "609150", "page": 9, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-08", "text": "I love this game on the ps3 but for some reason my game is bugged and its running at like X4 speed. The game is running faster than the audio and cutscenes overlap\n*edit** upon doing some research, if your monitor has a 144ghz and your frame rate exceeds 60. The game's frames will play at an excellerated rate which exceeds the audio and user inputs. Resulting in an unplayable game. There are fixes to make the game playable, but that requires you to limit the game to 60 frames. Why play a PC game if you can't use your PC to full capabilities?\nGreat game. Poor port. Whats new?", "hours": 0.9, "user_id": "76561198028398465", "username": "BigDiehl", "products": 96, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
