{"product_id": "378860", "page": 1, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2018-01-15", "text": "I am not sure why I have read so much hate about this game. I'm sure it's because I enjoy single player and have not experienced the bugs that are probably more prevalent in multiplayer (online). I am a big Assetto Corsa fan and I enjoy this just as much if not more. The handling is on par with Assetto with my Logitech G29 but there is so much more content. Assetto Corsa is like a half game to me with the current car and track selection. This is the full racing simulator I have been yearning for ever since I fell in love with the half game, Assetto Corsa. Graphics are slightly better than Assetto also. Some of the cars handling feels more genuine than others but they are all at the very least pretty good.\nGameplay: 9/10\nGraphics: 8/10\nSound: 9/10\nContent: 10/10\nCareer (Single Player): 8/10\nAI: 8/10\nRealism: 8/10\nMultiplayer: No personal interest (N/A)\nOverall: 9/10\nI am sure the frustration that others are having in multiplayer has lowered their scores. If you are a single player racer like me, this is a solid racing simulator.", "hours": 14.4, "username": "JonnyC2244", "products": 43, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "378860", "page": 1, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2018-01-15", "text": "The best racing simulator I have ever played was Project CARS, however that became second best ever since I played Project CARS 2. Project CARS 2 has a much better menu, more cars (including licensed Ferrari and Porsche cars) and more tracks. Not to mention it offers a larger variety of weather settings, including winter and snow. The game looks awesome and runs surprisingly well on the same hardware that I ran Project CARS on. I am not a competitive player and like to play mostly quick races with the AI, using various cars, weather settings and racks, for fun and relaxing.", "hours": 6.9, "username": "FlaviusI_TM", "products": 380, "early_access": false}
