{"product_id": "602160", "page": 1, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-26", "text": "Alchemy Defender VR, did TreeView Studios brew up a blast or did it turn out to be pretty vial?\nPuns aside, it's somewhere in the middle. I found alchemy Defender VR to be pretty mediocre.\nThe Tower Defense mechanics are decent. Placing towers was slightly troublesome when placing near edges as the button press/release when placing the tower caused the placement to jerk. Rushed tower placements either meant a very sub optimal placement or failing to place the tower entirely.\nThere did not seem to be any sort of creep to tower relationships. IE mortar counters slow groups, Ice counters runners etc... There were simply 3 towers. A low damage, a utility and a high damage.\nThere was no upgrade system for towers. How do you make a TD game without the ability to upgrade your towers? That's half of the game...\nI would have liked to see more variety in towers and enemies. The TD aspect really needed to be fleshed out.\nThe first person combat aspect was just bad. Enemies died at the slightest touch of the melee weapon. I could stand still and enemies would walk into the weapon and die. This is just unacceptable in any VR hack and slash. It's bad. Stop doing it devs.\nThere is only one form of locomotion and it didn't work all that great. The only locomotion option is teleportation. Even so, I often found myself stuck in a location I could not teleport out of unless it was a considerable distance away. I can normally use either teleport or trackpad but I love having the option. This just felt clunky.\nBalance was also an issue. Early game my towers were often not enough making me scramble to use all my combat abilities. Late game my towers were enough to handle everything and I rarely needed to go into combat mode. There needs to be a better balance here.\nAs I started with, Alchemy Defender VR was simply mediocre. Their attention was split between the two game modes and ultimately not enough love/polish made it into either side. It has some good ideas but ultimately the execution falls flat. It's not without hope but it would take significant updates to get this game where it needs to be to recommend.", "hours": 1.4, "username": "MasterGamingVR", "products": 363, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
