{"product_id": "602160", "page": 1, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-07-26", "text": "This is a tower defense strategy game designed from ground up for Virtual Reality. In Alchemist Defender VR, you assemble your defenses whilst overlooking a village environment from above and can then change your perspective simply clicking to jump down into the environment if you wish, to engage in direct first person combat (a feature that is similar to Out of Ammo). Throughout the game you defend a door using the handheld weapons which include a hammer, pistol and bomb, and and also three available tower weapons known as Canon, Frozt and Mortar. The latter can be purchased as you can afford based on your gold count which you can increase, and placing them strategically on turrets, continuing in this manner through oncoming waves of enemies for as long as you can survive. There are a variety of enemies, and the game gets harder as you progress with more and more oncoming enemies with each wave. The graphics are great, the environment is beautiful and super detailed as is the animation. However, the gameplay is limited at this stage, and so it can become quite repetitive. Although you would expect some repetition because it is a tower defense game, there isn\u2019t enough content at the moment to justify the price point, and so I feel it is good as a simple tower defence game but overpriced for what it actually has to offer at this stage in terms of gameplay. I think this game has a lot of potential though and could live up to the price point in the future if it is developed further, so I am looking forward to playing it again in it's prime. Suggestions include more weapons, upgrades, a changing or additional environment, more enemies, and enemies with different levels of difficulty or a more strategic way of doing battle with certain enemies. However, I have been informed since my video review that there is already plans for updates such as these, and some may have now even been added since my pre-release beta review video.", "hours": 2.0, "username": "JadeKVR", "products": 449, "early_access": true}
