{"product_id": "602160", "page": 1, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-04-30", "text": "Awesome, the best tower defense game in VR.... You can teleport down to the battle field and use short range weapons in first person ...really beautiful environment...you must see to believe....this game is fun...its a must play for those with VR....Game has been updated and UI is much better now,  Game used to have 2 levels or stages with lots of incoming waves  and it was really hard to beat...but the game balance has been modified and stages have been increased to 4, but each levels attack waves have been shortened to 10 waves so its much easier to beat..which I am not sure if its a good thing...", "hours": 6.5, "user_id": "76561198329163766", "username": "JABBA", "products": 97, "early_access": true}
{"product_id": "602160", "page": 1, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-04-10", "text": "Fun! Blends god mode with first person combat which is something we haven't seen often before. It really adds to the immersion of a tower defense VR game. If you're interested a video explaining its features:\nRight now it only has one map to play, but to be able to complete it you can play for about an hour and of course since its early access, more updates and content are coming. What I really like about Alchemist Defender is that you can build your strategy in god mode and watch your cannons do its work or help them by using certain weapons to combat the monsters in first person mode. This game can get quite hard to complete after a couple of waves and you'll definitely need to pay attention or have a good strategy to complete the first level.\nThere are some nice to haves, like I think that a more challenging first person combat mode would be nice.\nI'd recommend this game if you like tower defense games in general. It's fun and a nice change to play in VR. However I do think it's expensive for what's available now in early access. BUT I do hope enough people will be interested so the dev has some support to carry on its good work. Would be awesome to see this game complete with new monsters, weapons and maps.", "hours": 3.0, "compensation": "Product received for free", "username": "Cas (Cas & Chary VR)", "products": 211, "early_access": true}
{"product_id": "602160", "page": 1, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-03-31", "text": "While light on content at the moment (as it is in Early Access), this title make up with its very fun and unique core gameplay. This game blends god mode tower defense and first person combat genre.\nin this game, you'll be trying to stop the rat humanoids from getting to the end point, and there are 2 ways to go about it: build turrets that attack nearby enemies, or you can also cast spell whereby you shrink yourself to first person mode on the battlefield where you can swing hammer or shoot at them. These spells have to be recharged after every use so you will have to alternate both ways to take them down.\nthe graphic is great, and the music is suitable and good too. One sorely needed element is the upgrading system and more maps, but they will be added in future updates.\nthis game has got a solid gameplay foundation. when it gets more contents, it will no doubt be one of the best VR games releasing these past months.", "hours": 2.9, "user_id": "76561198015339281", "username": "Arthands", "products": 581, "early_access": true}
