{"product_id": "602160", "page": 1, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-03-30", "text": "You have what can be a great game, the mechanics are great, the tower building, the first person combat system, the enviroment its all great but alot needs to be added, i do feel the price is abit high for what feels like 1 level of enemy waves (18 waves), but i do recomment because i do see what it can be. What needs to be added ~~> Bosses, more levels with the enviroment changing, different classes maybe for the first person part and upgrades to the current defences. i know some of these things are already plan on future updates so i am excited to see what this game becomes", "hours": 1.3, "user_id": "76561197977268135", "username": "code2quest", "products": 80, "early_access": true}
{"product_id": "602160", "page": 1, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-03-30", "text": "Wow, really beautiful looking, entertaining and unique VR Tower Defense Strategy game! Jumping into a first-person view and battle the enemies is just awesome! Check my pre-release gameplay video and you will understand what I mean:\nHere are my thoughts:\nWell, Alchemist Defender VR really surprised me. I have never been a big fan of tower defence games so far to be honest, but if you do all stuff right in a Virtual Reality game, its like a whole new genre! With immersive gameplay, beautiful graphics as well as environment, and also this first-person perspective you can jump into any moment during gameplay, Alchemist Defender does something totally new and unique!\nStarting off, the graphics (made in Unreal engine) are stunning. The sounds and background music are pleasing and perfect for this type of game. Main menu is cool with lots of stuff you can interact with, just like you expect from a VR-game. Well, so far I have nothing to complaing about, and I have played this title for more that an hour now.\nThe \"miniature world\" that you see from above is super vivid, colorful and detailed. You begin by building some towers, turrets and cannons before the waves of evil Rat-Humanoids arrive. The same second it starts, you realize this is going to be intense. So intense that your towers are not enough, so you grab your hammer or a pistor, teleport yourself into the world and start a battle on your own in first person view :) And it gets more and more busy for every wave, at the same time as the game gets even better!\nHonestly, the first moment you \"slide\" into the frist person perspective is one of the coolest VR experiences I have had so far. I really can\u00b4t describe it, its just super-immersive!\nAnyway, the gameplay is nice, the level of difficulty is increasing and after around 8-10 waves things become really serious. I think this game is a challenge even for the most skilled tower-defense gamer out there.\nWhile playing Alchemist Defender VR without capturing the gameplay (as I did in the video above), the game runs very well on my GTX 980 Ti and I could probably add some supersampling to get it even sharper, so even thou the graphics are stunning, you still dont need a beefy PC I guess.\nI will update this \"review\" as soon as I have played more and especially when more content gets added later on. But for now, I can truly recommend this VR game to everyone - try it and you won\u00b4t regret it!\nCheers\nMartin, SweViver", "hours": 1.1, "username": "SweViver", "products": 244, "early_access": true}
