{"product_id": "234820", "page": 5, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-12-17", "text": "This used to be a handy tool that worked well for updating your drivers. Unfortunately, this software no longer functions correctly for users on Windows 10. Indeed, at this point it appears this software has been abandoned entirely. And what use a tool that keeps your computer up-to-date, which itself is not up-to-date?\nIt has been over a calendar year since there was any activity on the developers website or any of their social media accounts. The developers own external forum has been wiped and is 'migrating to another forum'. Here on Steam, the last post made by the developer was in July. If there are any plans to revive this software or rectify its Windows 10 dysfunction, they are being worked on\nquietly.\nI would not recommend purchasing or using this software in its present condition.\nUpdate, Dec 2017: Whilst it is great to know this software has been updated, for much of 2016 and 2017 no-one who had upgraded to Windows 10 anniversary update and beyond could use this software. During that time there was not one communication or response from the developer here on Steam.\nI appreciate that recent updates have restored service to Windows 10 users, but trust is an important thing with software like this. I find it difficult to overlook a considerable period of time where I could not use this software and the developers were notably absent.\nI can only hope other users will have more positive experiences in the future.", "hours": 4.5, "username": "TM", "products": 210, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "234820", "page": 5, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-12-14", "text": "I rarely review products...\nI originally came accross the free version of driver fusion while running Leschcat's drivers on a Lenovo gaming laptop.  I would use it for clean installs and the free version still works great for that.  The paid for version offers a lot of functionality that I helps keep my laptop up to date with drivers (which can be a PITA on a laptop).  I think it's worth the cost.", "hours": 3.3, "user_id": "76561198001833126", "username": "Heph", "products": 57, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "234820", "page": 5, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-12-05", "text": "Was fantastic with Windows 7 and Windows 8 however I do not recommend using it with Windows 10 it seems to offer it would dated drivers from previous windows families not recognizing that the newer driver numbers are smaller as they are part of Windows 10 but I would fully recommend you purchasing it if you're running on any other version of Windows", "hours": 27.6, "user_id": "76561198063674856", "username": "Reaper of the Grimm", "products": 229, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "234820", "page": 5, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-11-30", "text": "After a big patch for windows 10 this program didn't work for a while and like many I was upset about this having just bought the program back then. This year it's been patched and is back to working wonderfully for me. Good job Treexy. Thank you.", "hours": 4.3, "user_id": "76561198002812713", "username": "Puzzled Panda", "products": 143, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "234820", "page": 5, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-11-11", "text": "Worked great, until Windows 10 anniversary update. now it's just a wast of space in my library. No support from devs, no patches. Contacted steam for refund on this scam product....no dice.\nEveryone who owns this should flag it as broken, maybe that way steam will pull it, or pressure the devs to fix.\nEdit:   After recent update I decided to reinstall and give it another try.  All seemed well until I actually let driver fusion try and install updates. It failed to install about 10 updates and at the same time wiped all network adapter drivers from my system. This signed me out of driver fusion and would not let me continue.  After performing a system recovery, I managed to get the adapter working again.\nI will NOT be reinstalling this software again. And my negative review stands.", "hours": 9.9, "user_id": "76561197991474244", "username": "BADGER", "products": 257, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "234820", "page": 5, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-11-10", "text": "It's comfortable when you absolutely don't know how to update drivers. Otherwise it's basically useless. I don't see how Driver Fusion Premium beats Windows Update.  I've just installed new drivers for Intel HD and Realtek Card Reader on my laptop, which had been published already a year ago (ouch!) by not-the-fastest-publisher DELL (ouch-ouch!). Neither driver was known to Driver Fusion Premium. Also, I have two \"Unknown devices\" while the software finds 0 missing drivers. Even the latest-greatest feature to disable auto-update of drivers in Windows 10 can be accomplished without the Driver Fusion Premium, directly in Control Panel of Windows (it's a bit hidden, but Google will quickly help you find it).", "hours": 1.8, "user_id": "76561197997113915", "username": "actaxob", "products": 48, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "234820", "page": 5, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-10-31", "text": "This is more of a driver cleaner now than a driver updater.  It no longer searches for the latest drivers.", "hours": 10.6, "username": "roxzon", "products": 249, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "234820", "page": 5, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-10-22", "text": "Worked great when I first bought it about two years ago. But now, driver update is totally broken on Windows 10 after anniversary update. It sais I have out-of-date drivers and want to \"update\" them with older drivers than what I already have installed. See tons of people with the same issue and no recognition from the devs. Last public post on their social accounts was back in 2015. Not sure if they have abandoned the application. Anyhow, if you run Windows 10 I would not use Driver Fusion until the devs fixes these issues.", "hours": 5.9, "username": "iNQUAM", "products": 1118, "early_access": false}
