{"product_id": "734580", "page": 15, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-17", "text": "After giving another shot this game I have to say that I've may be a lil bit wrong, HOWEVER this game has A LOT of work to be good.\nFirst of all, maps... Well... Map...\nIt's just one and the same map, but big (way too big) with multiple villages. And it can easilly get boring. Maps should be smaller, but designed to easilly find front line and enough wide to flank.\nThis game for sure need more maps, for example city map (Stalingrad? Maybe something like that).\nSecond thing are Game Modes.\nWe have TDM (Team Deathmatch)- okey, it's fine, but players a lot of time don't focus on main objective and just rush to factory to craft a tank, which will be destroyed faster than they'll build it.\nAlso we have BAS (Base Assault) - okey, BUT there's one mayor problem, which is how far Factories are from base. Before players will gather resources to build one enemy will fix base (which is completly stupid in my personal opinion and makes this mode almost endless). Also this makes more players to focus on defend Factory then Base (and about Assault I'll not talk).\nFor this game Conquest mode (multiple capture points), Attack & Defence and King of the Hill (one capture point) will be best and enjoyable to play (and more avaliabe servers with or without crafting/vehicles).\nNext thing are glitches and bugs. Here's some I've been already noticed:\n- Hitbox (not every hit counts, not every 100+DMG shot kills)\n- \"Delete\" button, which completly broke interface, but turn into something like a slow spectate mode.\n- Compas, which is ultra broken and it's impossible to tell any location for friendly.\n- Map (M), also requires some tactical positions (for ex. A-10, F-5, etc.)\n- Alt+Tab sometimes work, another time will broke game (to be correct, it won't allow to come back)\n- Scope in Sniper Rifles feels funky. It's too easy (it should move a lil bit), yet not always accurate (not every direct hit in the cross will hit there) and it should have better zoom (well... It's a sniper, not DMR). This should also a lil bit rebalance this weapon, since a lot of players is saying that is OP.\n- Bazooka & Panzershreck are quite annoying. I know how they should be used, but moslty players just run with them, destroy all buildings or fight the players. I actually have no better idea than delete this class (or make it premium) and just let these weapons randomly spawn.\n- Double (or multiple) press F5 will broke interface.\n- Minimap needs an \"always visible\" objectives, so players won't be run around to find the front line.\nAnother thing are the game settings, which are really poor and don't even allow to set own bind keys. For example I'd love to play on higher settings, but that blure effects annoys me and makes everything much more less visible.\nAlso some players (and I) noticed that day/night time zones are not that great. Just hard to feel it really. And that sun's brightning, especially at morning and evening... Just blinds completly.\nAlso I've noticed at least two regular players that cheat in this game. Let's be honest, it's impossible to kill someone with a hammer from 220m while shoting an APC or Tank...\nAnother thing that is missing is Prone (laying on the ground). It actually would be good for this game.\nDynamite has (in my opinion) quite small AOE, so as bomb it's designed to blow the sht out (buildings, vehicles, tanks).\nSometimes I see that APC can penetrate walls and buildings like a paper, which is completly stupid compare to how single APC can destroy entire infrantry.\nAnd for last I hope for a better wood cutting, since it allows to create the most basic defences. It's not bad, but it may be better (more wood per hit, faster to cut down tree).\nI hope that's all I've been noticed so far and Devs will notice this. :) Game has a potential, but \"It's a long way to the top if you wanna Rock n' Roll\" (AC/DC). :V\n* Update! *\nAfter a while I'll say NO. Devs forced the game from Alpha to Beta, while it still works like an Alpha game. Still tons of things to do. Beside of small fixes they just add new things (to buy!) instead of truly fixing and upgrading the game. Literally still same bugs and glitches I see in every single match...", "hours": 61.3, "username": "WRG-West", "products": 16, "early_access": true}
