{"product_id": "609150", "page": 10, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-07", "text": "As a previous owner of this game on the Xbox 360, i aready know i love the game itself and its combat mechanics, crafting and research the differences between this version and the older one are the graphics, and synthisis system.\nGraphics\nat first i didnt notice any difference between what i remembered and this but after going back to watch a cutscene on youtube that i missed can instantly see how much it has improved, if thats something you look for in games this is definatly an improvment.\nSynthisis\nLater on in the game you gain the ability to combine items to creat better ones passing along their traits to create gear for how you want. but they have made some changes to how it works so that you can't make completly OP gear, for example you used to be able to create a weapon with 4 lots of exp +20% on them so that you could equip everyone in your group with such things and get an over 700% exp boost to rocket up in the endgame. this is no longer the case in this version (and the ps3 one too apparently)  you can no longer get rid of, leftover traits meaning best for exp you could do would be gear with two attack +1 boosts and two exp +20%, the attack boost is negligable and just in the way but no longer a way to clear it out halfing the potential of gear you could create and making it harder to be tidy or conservative when synthisisng.\nDespite these i would definatly recommend picking up this version if you don't have access to a xbox 360 its a great game and it takes ~50 hours for the initial campaign, but there is so much more to it. if you like this game then check out the 3rd game, till the end of time which takes place after this.", "hours": 79.6, "user_id": "76561198038209093", "username": "CATman4L", "products": 315, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "609150", "page": 10, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-07", "text": "Already played it back on the XBOX and PS3, now gonna play it again because i really love this game.\n+Lots and lots of content, especially for completionists\n+Fun combat system\n+Good and increasing difficulty\n+Loveable characters (at least for me)\n+Cool and challenging bossfights\n-Some of the achievements are quite hard to get and will take a lot of time\n-Some cutscenes can't be skipped, which is quite annoying if you're on your second or third playthrough\n-AI of teammates is frustrating sometimes\nAll in all a really good game that will keep you entertained, a must for JRPG fans!", "hours": 45.3, "user_id": "76561198367218421", "username": "SuXXeZZ", "products": 7, "early_access": false}
