{"product_id": "609150", "page": 10, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-07", "text": "Its been some years since the XBOX version and later the PS3 version was released. The first time I plated this game it was on a SD screen and I put it away for almost half a year. When I picked it up again and the contrast was bigger I could really get into the game itself. THe game is in a cartoonlike form and the characters are walking cliches. Through the Private Action event (skits for tales players) each character deepens from the 2 to the 3 dimensional.\nLike all star ocean games the story is quite good, but the best part about this game is the battle system. In NO other RPG/MMO I found a more enjoyable system.\nI have played this game maybe 20-30 times to the finish (and the hours upon hours after the finish) and I still find it fun to revisit.\nRight now I havent completed too much of the the PC port, but I am curious whether this is the XBOX port or the PS3 port", "hours": 187.0, "user_id": "76561198122536093", "username": "gerryveraa", "products": 39, "early_access": false}
