{"product_id": "378860", "page": 2, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2018-01-14", "text": "I upgreded from the original as soon as this became avaiable.  I will be as fair as I feel I can in this review. I play with a full PC sim setup. Fanatec clubsport pedals and a clubsport 2.5 wheel base with the BMW wheel.  I also play Assetto Corsa with the same setup. PC2 feels much more realistic than PC. Car control is better and the graphics are better in their subtlety.  In short I generally run the same courses/cars faster in PC2 than in the original version.  While PC2 is an improvement overall, from my point of view it has some serious short comings. In no particular order:\n1) the AI is NUTS with penalties!!!!!  and it is inconsistent. Opponents do NOT get penalized for doing much worse things than I do.  If I loose control and go off I am penalized. Brush a guard rail..penalized. Cut an apex within what would be allowed at an scca sanctioned event...penalized.\n2) Qualifying. I can't for the life of me understand why with the competion factor set at 92% in PC I can consistently qualify in the top 3, more often than not, pole; yet in PC2 I can seldom qualify higher than 12th IF I can even get a qualifying time.  Yet, in the race with cars that were 2-4 seconds faster than me I am consistently able to finish in the top 5 and even occasionally win.\n3) During the race.  I love to race at Bathhurst. HOWEVER....there is a glitch in the game here. Again the best I have been able to qualify is 12th. I am often in the top 5 at the end of the first lap, sometimes the lead. I carry way more speed through the uphill than any one else and am faster everywhere else EXCEPT the back straight. I come on to that straight with a car lengths lead, stretch it to 3 by the over head banner, yet at the end of the straight I ALWAYS get passed or rear ended by the car that wasn\"t even close before. On the flip side of that coin, I can come on to that straight within a car length of the car in front of me and he will pull 3-10 car lengths on me at the end of the straight. This is in identical Mitsu evo's.\nIn general I like PC2 better than the original and my next purchase is an Oculus Rift the next time they are on sale. But PLEAAAASSSSSEEEEE... fix the glithches. At $90 for the top game pkg, we should see a steady stream of updates and fixes. Also as far as addons.. More real world cars. I drive the Evo because it is the only comparable car to my WRX STi. I am willing to bet there are WAY more WRX's on the road than EVO's.  It might be fun to hop in a Lambo or Ferrari but in real life I will never do that. So I want to hone my skills in something that I Might be able to afford. And why are there NO Lotus road cars??????\nI don't know if the developers read these reviews but I sure hope so!", "hours": 30.5, "user_id": "76561198291439426", "username": "politicallyincorrectus", "products": 6, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "378860", "page": 2, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2018-01-13", "text": "Ultimate driver journey? Images in the video of open world rally.\nAbsolute lies.\nSmall amount of cars, bland tracks and AI that follows the exact same lines.\nNot to mention VR. Your hands and dash you can see clearly(gamepad), thats it.\nBlurry mess in front of you. Waste of money. Refund.", "hours": 1.7, "user_id": "76561198041245081", "username": "heshalladdfire", "products": 145, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "378860", "page": 2, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2018-01-13", "text": "I wish I could recommend this game but I can't at this point -- it is just too buggy.  You can't even save a setup after you've modified it fer chrissakes.  Physics are sketchy sometimes.  Graphically it is pretty but damage on cars switches on and off in replays depending on the camera view, there is lots of flickering on all car surfaces, etc etc.  Just a lot of lost potential here.  And what is the fascination with rain in career mode?  Like every other race is a wet race -- come on.  Let us turn that stuff off if we don't want it -- we've paid for the sim now let us customize to OUR tastes.  The developers need to fix a lot of the buggy mess that this game is before I will give it a positive review and recommend someone buy it.  Thanks God I bought it on sale.", "hours": 40.0, "user_id": "76561198004697065", "username": "JPS", "products": 23, "early_access": false}
