{"page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2018-01-15", "text": "If you expect something with good graphics, simple UI and easy growth curve, maybe incremental games aren't a thing for you. Some of the best in the genre have only numbers and names popping on the screen and a very steep learning and growth curve, in comparison ClickRaid presents a very good UI, easy to view all information, it's easy to learn and has good navigation through screens.\nAs a big fan of idle/clicker/incremental games, I've always been looking for one focused on multiplayer, always wanted to play with friends and go pvp or questing together, turns out this game is still crude in that matter but it's mechanics and balance are incredibly well developed. Also, I like the direction it goes taking away the boring part of clickers and making the soft reset automatic for a limited time.\nDespite it's deepness, the game presents itself in a very easy and comprehensible way and it's pace is really fast so, in a few days I've already learned everything the game has in, there's clearly room for mid to endgame content.\nIn the little time I've been playing I've already seen Devs talking to players and taking suggestions ingame plenty of times, I can clearly see the passion in the devs and it's very active development makes me hope it will become better still.\nAs a developer, I tried a few times on my own to make something like this, I can see the work put into UI/UX and also in the engine, maybe because of that it's easy to appreciate the effort put into making this real. Hope they keep up the good work they've been making so far.", "hours": 161.1, "username": "BzuM", "products": 277, "early_access": false}
