{"page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "text": "It's our last community update for the year and what a year it's been! To celebrate we're having the BIGGEST discount for 001 Game Creator EVER and we've also updated the software with a bunch of useful additions/fixes! See details below:\nFrom\nuntil\n,\nis 70% off, with our\nand\nbeing 40% off and our just released\nbeing 15% off! Buy them NOW, while they're at their cheapest!\nhttp://store.steampowered.com/app/347400/001_Game_Creator/\nhttp://store.steampowered.com/app/564680/001_Game_Creator__MMORPG_Kit/\nhttp://store.steampowered.com/app/564681/001_Game_Creator__3D_FPS__Survival_Horror_Kit/\nhttp://store.steampowered.com/app/567360/001_Game_Creator__Point__Click_Adventure_Kit/\nAlongside the sale, we've also updated 001 Game Creator with a bunch of awesome additions and bug fixes. Here are some of the highlights and, as always, you can see the full change log here: http://www.engine001.com/changes.htm\nIt took a while but we've finally added tooltips to all major windows and their respective sub-windows in 001! Our\nwill always have the most detailed explanations but these tooltips should provide users (particularly newcomers) with some much needed help in understanding what all of these options/controls actually do.\nThis crucial fix has resulted in improved smoothness in higher framerate games and has consequently improved the accuracy of Spawns/Timers!\nA new option inside the Game Settings window which allows game timing to be more predictable, resulting in more consistent gameplay regardless of game performance. Essentially, this tells your game that the FPS is always whatever you've set so if there's a hiccup, it'll run the game X number of times until it's caught up. This should help to resolve collision detection issues (Actors falling through floors, doors, walls, etc. when they're not supposed to)\nPLEASE NOTE: If your game already suffers from performance issues, then this setting may make things worse! It's also advised that the \"Minimum Framerate\" option is set to nothing lower than 30.\nBe sure to follow the official\naccount to see new posts every Monday, Thursday and Saturday showcasing the awesome games made in 001! Here's some of the things you've been missing:\nWe'd like to thank all of you for your continued support throughout the year and we hope you all have a happy holiday and new year! We'll be back in 2018 with even more cool updates for 001 Game Creator, so look forward to it! :)", "early_access": false}
