{"product_id": "555600", "page": 1, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-30", "text": "You will laugh within the first 30 seconds of launching the game, and then be amazed at how simple and effective, the control method is, but don't let that simple style fool you, because this is a really cool and tricky western themed shooter.\nYou'll need to 'waggle' in all directions, so that you can take cover and get a bead on the baddies.  The sound is top notch also, with good ol' classic western sounding bullet whiz, and the sound of hooves... just don't look down :)  Dynamite can be abit loud though, compared to the other sound levels.  The music, which amazingly loops forever, and still sounds incredibly good, no  matter how long you play, has a unique electro-westerny vibe.\nGameplay wise, keep moving, and try to master the art of shooting while galloping, but also remember to take cover.\nIf you're seemlingly 'stuck' with nowhere else to go, try looking for Ramp-like rocks, to gallop over.  Some rocks are intentionally impassable though.  This is definitely one to show your VR off, to people, especially if you want them to laugh within the first 30 seconds.", "hours": 0.8, "user_id": "76561197972090300", "username": "Bastardboy", "products": 987, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "555600", "page": 1, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-16", "text": "First time gameplay on the channel:\nHopalong: The Badlands is a fun Western themed FPS game. The gameplay involves shooting bandits such as the notorious Dynamite gang, in your role as the crime fighting sheriff, whilst galloping on your stick horse around scenic landscapes. The game uses free locomotion, and you move using your horse with one hand, and your gun with the other hand to shoot the bandits. The use of the stick horse is a very unique and fun to experience way of implementing free locomotion, and works incredibly well for this game adding to the experience. The gameplay is otherwise typical of an FPS game, but enjoyable as there are several maps to explore, and the game could even be a little challenging at times as you juggle moving on your horse whilst using your weapon, as simultaneously you need to ensure your horses health is maintained by stopping to let it drink water which could be mid-shootout! The voice acting, sound effects and music are well done, and the game is also beautiful in terms of graphics. Overall, an extremely fun and enjoyable Western FPS game, with a locomotion experience unlike any other.", "hours": 0.3, "username": "JadeKVR", "products": 449, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "555600", "page": 1, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-11-26", "text": "What a great game. It looks nice, it's responsive, the VO is very good (not too repetitive) and the maps are very clever. Lots of nooks and crannies. I feel like the aiming is a bit off at times especially shooting from a distance, but it could also be that other games are too forgiving. Not sure, but with unlimited ammo you can just keep shootin' and eventually you'll nail someone! I hope that this game gets a lot of attention and maybe even multilayer at some point.", "hours": 1.0, "username": "CoolHandDuke", "products": 67, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "555600", "page": 1, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-08-05", "text": "I simply love this game.   It has a novel locomotion method - and I freaking laughed my rear off constantly the first time I played it.   It's got a bit of a challenge, voice overs are fun....the game is just fun.\nI didn't find the movement nausea inducing, but I'm not prone to it.   I'm sure, like other games, your mileage will vary.", "hours": 1.6, "user_id": "76561197967715028", "username": "CQCoder", "products": 604, "early_access": true}
