{"product_id": "555600", "page": 1, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-04-08", "text": "Hahahaha!  That is really all I can say.  The locomotion in this game is genius.  Probably not a game I'll keep coming back to, though it is a good workout if you don't cheat.\nSo the way you move in this game is by pretending you are a 6 year old kid riding a broom while pretending it is a horse.  You do this by either doing the Monty Python Horse skip:\nor by hoping up and down in place.  The faster your skip/hop the faster your horse runs.\nWatching someone play this game is quite entertaining as they look ridiculous.  Playing the game also is ridiculous because in the game you are holding a stick with a stuffed horse head on the end of it, so you know exactly what you look like to those watching.\nThere is some risk of motion sickness here.  I found that when I stopped the horse, I instinctively leaned backwards and if I was going particularly fast it would sometimes almost cause me to fall over.  Also, when riding the horse down a slope it can be pretty jarring and I found myself again leaning backwards.\nI recommend only playing this if you have a bit of space.  It is _really_ easy to get immersed into the game and not realize that you are hopping off towards a wall.  The VR chaperone is still there of course, but if you are close to a wall and then stop your horse in the middle of a gun fight it is easy to lean backwards into the wall.", "hours": 0.3, "username": "Micah", "products": 285, "early_access": true}
