{"product_id": "378860", "page": 3, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2018-01-13", "text": "*NOTE* This review is exclusively about the single player experience. (I am not much of an online multiplayer kinda guy)\n6/10 - I will start with what I liked. Graphics are great, the car feels solid, and the track feels like it should. Overall it should be a great sim/sim-cade.... key word SHOULD. Unfortunately, in their drive to make realistic cars, they failed in other aspects.\nI tried to love this game, but SMS seems to be ignoring major AI flaws; or they are incapable of fixing them. This makes singleplayer virtually unplayable. The AI is completely blind to where you are on the track, and will not even tap the brakes to avoid hitting you. I will even try taking as much of an outside line on the track as possible to avoid being nailed and low and behold... I get rammed in the side by a kamikaze dips#!t.\nIf someone from SMS is reading these reviews, please try to be more transparent about what is going on with your AI team. Is there work being done to improve this? When can improvements be expected?", "hours": 118.7, "user_id": "76561198080782075", "username": "p_b_irish", "products": 144, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "378860", "page": 3, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2018-01-12", "text": "Don't even think about buying this unless you have a wheel and/or pedal setup. This is not a game, it's a simulator. Seriously! It's GORGEOUS, the graphics are BEAUTIFUL and the realism, accuracy, framerates are all superb, and the Competative License system is a great tool to keep jerks out of multiplayer who only want to play bumpercars, but it's SO DAMNED PRETTY that you'll spend over the time limit that Steam gives you for refunds!\nI've made it work with a Saitek yoke and rudder pedals, and it's really quite a joy.", "hours": 6.6, "username": "Perchlorate", "products": 18, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "658160", "page": 2, "page_order": 10, "recommended": true, "date": "2018-01-16", "text": "The interface is a mess at first sight, but if you look beyond it you got yourself a captivating incremental game !\nDev is active every day both in developping the game and interacting with the community, he mostly makes daily small changes but since the two weeks I started playing the game evolved nicely and always in a good way. Seeing suggestions you made be implemented in the game within the week feels awesome compared to some other game where your sound suggestions are ignored for years.\nEvery once in a while you have seasons that last two weeks with small tweaks in the rule to keep it fresh and where everyone starts square one to give you a fair chance and trigger that competitive fiber in you. (Progress is added to your normal game at season end)\nNow the core of a multiplayer incremental is the community, and this game got a very good one! All chat is always there to help you out and cheers you up. No bullbleep where Clans / Guilds are needed to compete and the top ones ask you to wake up at night for some Clan Bosses, here it's only to talk in guild and have fun.\nAnd fun in this game I'm having lots of it, looking forward to see the game evolve even more and play along =D", "hours": 396.9, "username": "Xhell", "products": 504, "early_access": false}
