{"product_id": "378860", "page": 3, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2018-01-11", "text": "TL;DR Its a really really really really really good racing game, but its quite great (yet)\nFirst off i should start by saying that im writing this review without having any kind of experince with other simulation racing games\nI was quite nervous about getting this game tbh, i had played the first PC on ps4 and loved it, but the reviews i had ready said the handling was diffrent which made me uneasy, i'll fully admit to having only played around with the forumal 1 games as well PC and GT so my expreince with simulation racing was near non existent, but i wanted to at least try this game and if i didnt enjoy it i could simply write it off as a donation to an ambitious game dev studio, but to my suprise and delight i found the handling learning curve to be quite shallow and after an hour or 2 i had a good feel for a couple of cars and tracks, now, alot of that you could probalbly put down to FFB (which btw is without question or hesitation the best FFB i've ever had in a racing game, but as i stated, this is my first sim race game so bare that in mind as you read it)\ntheres a fanstatic collection of cars and tracks, i've read some reviews claiming theres not enough, but IMO theres more than enough to sink your teeth into, ive played around with it for over 80 hours at the time or writing this and i've only raced with about 40% of the cars and tracks, also keep in mind that with each new dlc they realease will add to the count of cars and tracks, the only slight critisim i have, and it is very very slight, is that i found the car/track selection screen to be a little bit cluttered and untidy but its hardly a game breaker and after a few hours you'll get used to it.\nThe physics absolutley blew me away, the ways diffrent cars handle in diffrent situations on diffrent tracks left my jaw laying on my desk, without doubt the best physics in a racing game ive ever played, but do bare in mind this is my first expreince with a racing sim\nthe weather effects in paticular the rain are fantatic, the way puddles form on parts of the track and stay there during the race is quite impressive, and the added element of danger from them really puts you on edge knowing going through them could cost you the race.\nin terms of graphics i was less excited, don't get me wrong its a very very pretty game, and i love the fact they have included diffrent lighting for diffrent tracks at diffrent times, and the photo mode really can bring out some stunning pictures, but i wasn't blown away by them, i found myself admiring the physics and handling more than the beauty of the game, it should be noted that it looks better than PC1 if you want to compare it with something.\nIt must be said however that AI Need some work, recent patches have helped but its still along way off being fantastic, i found the AI in formula 1 2017 to be more enjoyable to race against, the AI in PC2 seem to have to two settings which are \"friendly sunday driver\" and \" Lewis Hamiltion harbouring every female menstreal cycle on planet earth\" they will either wave as you pass them, or kill you dead instantly for having the nerve to appear in their mirrors\"\nthere are sliders for both AI difficulty and agression but to be it would of been simpler to just have the one slider that controls all, settings the ai diffilculty to max but the agression to low just seems to make the diffilculty slider redundant in my expreince.\nthe career mode is very well thought out this time, and you have a progression ladder you can follow rather than the \"do any racing dicipline you like\" from PC1 i like the structrue to it in PC2 it gives it more of a career feel rather than a series of exibtion races.\nOn a final note, i will add if you are thinking about getting this game, i would highly advise getting a decent FFB steering wheel (i have the logitech g29 and it felt incredible with this game) but when i tried using an xbox controller i really struggled with the handling, this game is geared more towards a wheel more than a controller, not that that is a bad thing by any means, and i can only imagine how this game would feel with the serious $1000+ racing setups you see on the net)", "hours": 118.6, "user_id": "76561198098107035", "username": "ChillBlastGaming", "products": 92, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "378860", "page": 3, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2018-01-11", "text": "over 100 bucks and I can't get my t80 to work with it ... how are you supporting this wheel on the ps4 but not on the PC??? It's common knowledge that it's pc supported and they even have the official drivers out on the sight labelled as t80 PC drivers now. PLEASE FIX ASAP, this game is way too expensive to be missing support on this common of a wheel. I'd be more sympathetic if this was a brand new wheel, and an old game but this wheel is already supported on the PS4 with at least decent FFB from what I understand. And @ around 100 bucks this is a great budget wheel that I expect to see a lot of beginner or budget players using. Will absolutely edit this with an actual review when I can play it properly :/", "hours": 56.5, "username": "Gibson", "products": 76, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
