{"page_order": 27, "recommended": true, "date": "2018-01-14", "text": "No matter what you can read this is one of the best exclusively online only TCG (Trading Card Game) you can come across.\nIt's a really good alternative to Magic the Gathering (I play both Hex Online and Magic in the real world)\nThe game mechanics are really close to MtG but the developers totally understood what is it the play the game virtually and added mechanics that you cannot even imagine to have with real cards.\nLike all the TCG you can argue about is price, but it's all depend on how much you are willing to cash in for the joy how playing the game. A good alternative to real money is that if you really like the game and commit yourself to it you can with a very low money investment build some decent decks Be it by farming fopr gold and then buying cards for the free in game currency or if you're confident enough on your abilities try to cash in via the draft. i'm not a good drafter but I have some friends that where able to build some more than decent deck and get there hands on powerfull cards just by buying very few platinum (in game real currency) and rolling in the drafts.\nLike all TCG you have a variety of format for you to play, Draft, severals constructed rules formats. My only cons to this is maybe the lack of a more casual one because once you hit the PvP you can feel the competivity and challenge that come with the game.\nBut what this game has that Mtg doesn't is a very nice PvE environment that allows you to play for fun, for farming and some nice rewards, even some rewards that can be very usefull in PvP.\nThe developers also try to make all  they can to add events to made the game always going forward. You have of course the classic option of tournament where you can cash in real money, hollydays events with special PvE cards and new game formats like the incomming siege.\n+\nA very well done TCG\nA huge variety of formats for everyone to play\na challenging and  yet pleasant PvE\nThe possibility to play the game for almost for free be it with your skill in the drafts or by spending time farming gold.\nLots of differents cards and mechanics allowing for a wide variety of decks (even if in some case some decks or cards just steal the show and become a must play)\nThe champion mechanics that adds some variety on how you play your cards.\nLess expensive when you invest real money than most of the other TCG I came across specifically MtG\nA really active player community.\nActive developers when you come across a bug.\n-\nLike all the TCG some cards or deck  become must play if you want to success. Righ now if you didn't get your hands on the runebind (10$ real money) card you were missing the most important card and add a hard time competing at a high level.\nThe PvE that doesn't grow fast enough.\nLack of a more casual environment. When you start playing in the constructed format you can feel that most players aren't here for the fun. If you can't find friends to play it for fun it can be hard on beginners or casual players.\nConclusion :\nFor me a veteran Magic player, Hex is one of the best TcG I have come across. If you're ready to start playing a TCG I highly recommend this game.", "hours": 1205.0, "user_id": "76561198031281473", "username": "minute_of_decade", "products": 104, "early_access": false}
