{"product_id": "656740", "page": 1, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2018-01-07", "text": "As you level up, you get a multiplier that decreases your cash rewards. So you spend a level making a little number increase, finally get to the end of the level, and then that number gets decreased by two thirds.\nIt'd be fun if that didn't\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665me off and make me want to quit at the end of every level. It's the most discouraging system a grinding game could possibly have.", "hours": 3.1, "username": "Grayson", "products": 347, "early_access": true}
{"product_id": "656740", "page": 1, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2018-01-05", "text": "Cosmonator is the only shoot-em-up on Steam that caught my eye. While it looks like a simple shooter at first glance, it offers a nice variety of customisation on how you want to outfit your ship which almost every other shoot-em-up lacks or makes the upgrade mechanic extremely linear.\nPros:\n- Large amount of upgrades\n- 4 pages of spells for you to pick, ranging from lasers, summoning ships to fight with you, missiles, bombs, fireballs, etc.\n- Great pixel art\n- Excellent boss and enemy variety\n- Excellent stage variety, a lot of stages have their own theme such as fighting through asteroid fields, avoiding laser mines, or engaging large swarms of enemies.\n-  Big fun factor with all the stuff you can outfit your ship, it really forces you to make choices and plan what to get now or later.\n- Caters to a large amount of playstyles due to the amount of spells and upgrades available.\n- For a shoot-em-up it surpisingly has deep mechanics in regards to how well you can tactically deploy your spells or how you outfit your ship\nCons:\n-Passive upgrades needs to be more fleshed out with more variety, lacks the decision making compared to the spell upgrades. Suffers from being too linear like its competitors.\n- Crashing bug when playing on low particle setting. (Already being addressed by the devs)\n- Color Palette is somewhat dull, most colors are dark and muddy.\n- Leveling system punishes the player bit too much by reducing the amount of money you receive at each mission", "hours": 18.2, "user_id": "76561198002920899", "username": "Slewey", "products": 55, "early_access": true}
{"product_id": "656740", "page": 1, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-09", "text": "I haven't completed the game yet but in it's current state it's a pretty good game. The game is complete, it just need to polish some details.\nPros until now 12/9/2017:\n- Better than Galaxy Squadron EX Turbo (not a bad game), for me atleast.\n- Lot of customization and different ways to play it.\n- Replayability.\n- Has a global success rate on each stage (all players of the game included). I love it.\n- Has lot of spells and you can have a full arsenal of them.\n- You can play a level as many times you want, you get extra money by beating a stage the first time and beating it again with a 75%+ health bar.\n- You get money even if you lose on a stage.\nCons until now 12/9/2017:\n- The stages colors look a little too dark, specially on the first levels.\n- No keys customization.\n- Not as many passive upgrades as upgrades spells have.\n- The rank system is kind of penalizing. You get less and less money by getting more money and in turn you level your rank up, but you kind of gain the same amount of money that you always do (around $500) by beatting the stage once and a second time with a 75%+ health bar. I don't know yet if the rank has a limit, but I gaining a 3.5% of the total money by now.\n- It need more quick keys (like Q, W, E), if you want to have a full arsenal of spells, because cyclying spells is hard when you have too many.\n- Auto-cast needs to have a priority list.\nI don't have any regret on buying this game to be honest. I think the money is well spent at full-price (and I usually buy games at super low prices).", "hours": 103.3, "username": "Stardragon EX", "products": 310, "early_access": true}
{"product_id": "656740", "page": 1, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-05", "text": "This retro space shoot-em-up is an instant classic. I would say it is THE successor to Space Invaders!\nCosmonator is hecticly action-filled and fast-paced, with loads of awesome enemies to fight and bullets flying everywhere.\nThe replayability is high, with challenging difficulty settings, interesting levels, and tons of great weapon and spell customization options for your ship. The rewards (and spending power) scale down as you get stronger, making your customization choices important. I feel as though I have improved my reflexes and gained several IQ points playing this game!\nI love the boss fights, the excellent music and the thrill of finally beating a level that has thwarted me for hours!\nEdit: Finished on Normal mode - started again immediately on Hardcore. This game is super addictive!", "hours": 35.3, "username": "Dartanian", "products": 58, "early_access": true}
{"product_id": "656740", "page": 1, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-02", "text": "A great game, despite being cataloged as early access, the game already provides excellent content.\n(A quick overview of the important aspects of the game)\nGAMEPLAY.\nExcellent, it's fast, with precise controls and the screen is filled with enemy bullets, each enemy has its own attack pattern, the bullets are mostly small which leaves a lot of room for the player to dodge.\nThe game has a deep customization with elements of rpg which gives a great variety when choosing the improvements for our ship and also keeps you constantly making decisions about what skills to use when planning attacks.\nExplosions everywhere,awesome boss battles and has a old school vibe(which i like).\nGRAPHICS.\nDark environments with bright colors and great pixel art work.\nThe backgrounds consist of many layers which gives a feeling of 3D, moving objects in the background, particle effects, everything is very detailed and with a lot of diversity in its design around its 40 levels through its 4 worlds, to which we can navigate on the map\nMUSIC.\nA killer sci-fi dark futuristic soudtrack, with a unique track on each level.\nIt has a great variety of dramatic and atmospheric themes, others with a touch of trance, electronic or downtempo, mixing everything a little like minimal, dnb or even dubstep, the result is simply amazing, in addition to the sounds maintain a certain tone,(the best soundtrack I've heard this year),\nIn conclusion, we have a perfect game in my opinion, with great content and a good challenge, I would say that it is my 2017 goty. It exceeded my expectations even though it is listed as early access.", "hours": 51.3, "username": "\uff2b\uff25\uff2c\uff21\uff14\uff12\uff10", "products": 603, "early_access": true}
{"product_id": "656740", "page": 1, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-11-22", "text": "A lot of love went into this game and the devs are continually adding to an already feature rich experience. Bear in mind, it is tough as nails, although there are easier difficulty options. Bullet patterns are fun and varied, same with enemies and their abilities, not to mention your own customisability. You may often find yourself exclaiming in surprise as the npcs trick you into making a move that leads to your demise. Navigate the space wisely as these alien invaders will outsmart you!", "hours": 10.3, "compensation": "Product received for free", "user_id": "76561198045162570", "username": "Snirps", "products": 93, "early_access": true}
