{"product_id": "609150", "page": 12, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-05", "text": "This game is fun and it is more enjoyable on the PC than the PS3.\nI noticed the other reviews that mention some technical problems with the timing.  The timing can be messed up in full screen mode, but there is an easy, free way to fix this.  Set your desktop and the game to the resolution that you want and use windowed mode.  Then use the AutoHotKey script to set it to full screen windowed mode.  This will make the timing perfect and looks just like full screen.  The timing can be adjusted in this mode with CheatEngine which is the main advantage to having it on PC.  Now I can run it at 200% speed while exploring since it is too slow at default speed.  With a hotkey, I can easily set it back to 100% speed for battles.\nThere is already a setup in the Big Picture mode for using the PS4 controller and it works perfectly without having to remap anything.  Just write down where the ABXY buttons are since these at the symbols used in game for button prompts.\nIt is also much easier to read the text on the pc screen since my TV is not huge.", "hours": 82.1, "username": "elbeeno", "products": 1284, "early_access": false}
