{"product_id": "609150", "page": 12, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-05", "text": "I remember playing this game many years ago and I enjoyed it a lot, it's got cringy anime trope stuff that JRPGs have, the annoying character that you decide to not use because you hate them, just the way I like it.\nI like the story for the most part, exploring different places, and I like the battle system with the freedom of movement and ability to switch between characters. What's even better is you can selectively mute specific characters so you don't here them say the same annoying garbage over and over again! I wish more games had that.\nMy only issues are mostly technical stuff, there's issues with frame rates in certain situations in cut scenes where when the scene changes it stutters, and for some reason when on the Calnus I have bad frame rates, otherwise it runs well enough. Also wish it had the fullscreen borderless (I think it's called that) option. I think if they fix those things, then this game would be excellent and I'd have no complaints.", "hours": 68.2, "user_id": "76561198076318440", "username": "Grackle", "products": 56, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "609150", "page": 12, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-05", "text": "Dont get me wrong i love last hope but i rather have star ocean till the end of time hd remaster for pc  this is sec but  cant be help i still give this game 8/10 an it still fun to play", "hours": 26.3, "username": "Twinmage", "products": 135, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "609150", "page": 12, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-05", "text": "Broken port.\nGame runs at twice the speed in fullscreen. The game also crashes nonstop. This alone is not worth getting the game for, at least until they fix it.", "hours": 0.7, "username": "Gilbertify", "products": 138, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "609150", "page": 12, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-05", "text": "My specs: Intel core i7-6700k Skylake @4.00ghz, Win10 home x64, 16 gb DDR4, Nvidia Geforce GTX 980 ti.\nThe nostalgia is real!  I love this series and racked up nearly 400 hrs on the ps3.\nThis remaster is beautiful.    Although I'm only playing it 1080, the constant 60 fps is amazing.  This is a port done right.\nSure, there were alot of bugs in the original and somewhat cleaner \"International\"versions, this one seems more complete and no bugs so far 2 hrs in.  Controls feels good and more refined to what I remember.  Battle is fluid and soo much more control to command each character.\nBest thing is there is virtually no loading / transitions between areas and battles.  I highly recommend this to any avid JRPGer looking for a long and fun game.\nIt's a steal for the price.  I intend to put another 400 hrs into this great game!", "hours": 63.6, "user_id": "76561197973296052", "username": "Yagami2K", "products": 66, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "609150", "page": 12, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-05", "text": "I have over 1500 hours on this game on 360, the fact this some how snuck up on me as a remaster was amazing to say the least, instantly bought it and downloaded it. After the first 90 minutes 100% worth every penny if you love the Star Ocean series, looks super crisp and Star Ocean in 60FPS is just amazing, the combat feels SO much better than on console just so smooth.\nPLEASE KEEP RELEASEING PC PORTS SQUARE ENIX!!!!", "hours": 34.2, "user_id": "76561198027826977", "username": "BongMaster", "products": 36, "early_access": false}
