{"product_id": "609150", "page": 12, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-05", "text": "Poorly optimized port in some areas, specifically with how the frame rate doesn't work with higher res monitors. Even when you change your own resolution... the game does seem to give you a headache. In fact the motion of the whole game seems to give me nausea, which I don't remember at all on consoles, so something clearly went wrong in the remastering.\nAlso has Denuvo.... nuff said. For an almost decade old game that's 20 bucks, it's unnecesary, and it's a complete lack of appreciation to paying customers, who for the most part are probably double dipping on a game they already paid a price for years ago.", "hours": 1.1, "username": "bladechild", "products": 131, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "609150", "page": 12, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-05", "text": "I was hoping for the longest time this would come to PC and it did.\nHere's to hoping for more PC ports of the Star Ocean series.\n(My review won't contain spoilers)\nIts a JRPG so you already should know what to expect from the dialog. (I felt like it was a little sappy)\nBesides that:\nThe story is pretty solid. It draws you in and makes you want to learn about the characters and the world they live in. It also gives you a look behind what happened prior to the very first game on SNES and the Second Story.\nCombat is fun, its definitely a more refined version of what you saw in the previous series. The boss battles are pretty hard but thats true for any Star Ocean game.\nYou get a wide range of party members each with different specialties and attacks.\nThe graphics are nice to look at. It wasn't full on \"cell shading\" anime style and honestly that was welcome. The cut scenese are very well done too. Fair warning: the cut scenes are very long.\nThis one actually ties into the rest of the series and there are head nods to the other games and its lore. I really liked that.\nI would reccomend this game for anyone who is a fan of the series and for people who enjoy a good JRPG once in awhile.\nThe price is more than fair and that was awesome that they did a discount for the launch; albeit a small one.", "hours": 54.2, "username": "stupidanimeface", "products": 427, "early_access": false}
