{"product_id": "410380", "page": 3, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "text": "Welcome to a round up of the week. We have lore and spoilers and tournaments, oh my!\nFrostheart shattered and Hogarth fell\n, but his story doesn't end there. Read what happens next in our latest lore article: Twilight Judgment\n.\nAnd that's not all\u2014this week we revealed not only our upcoming keywords\nbut also our five new champions\n! If you haven't already, you should totally check out these articles by\ndesign lead Corey Burkheart. The nights are getting colder, and it is good to be prepared!\nSpeaking of preparation, remember that\nand\nwill be rotating with the release of\n. This means that these cards and champions will no longer be legal in the Standard constructed format. They will, however, remain legal in our Immortal format. If you are unfamiliar with how rotation works in HEX, please check out this article here\n.\nAnother thing that will change when\nreleases is that our exciting Kismet's Draft mashup will go back into the vault. If you still haven't gotten all of the six beautifully animated sleeves\nfrom this event, be sure to join the draft queue soon! Remember, every three match wins will get you another sleeve, so the next one is just a few wins away.\nWe announced our latest tournament offering: Fight Night HEX (FNX). FNX is a Standard Rock tournament which will take place 4 times a week on two different days. Rock is a constructed format where only commons and uncommons are used. No rares or legendaries are allowed. You can still use any gems and champions from the Standard format. Read all about it here\nor on the HEX Primal website\n.\nThe new and improved HEX Primal Immortal Championship series\n(ICS) was this last weekend, and people turned up in droves! It's exciting to see everyone enjoying our Immortal changes. Congratulations to those who placed!\nIf you missed all the action, HEX Primal also cast the tournament. You can check it out on our website.\nAs part of these new ICS capstone events, we are also drawing door prizes for the bottom half of the bracket. These lucky players will also get a Rune Ear Hierophant AA!\nCongratulations once again!\nSpeaking of awesome tournaments, the end of our current ladder season is fast approaching. Our ladder will roll over midnight Pacific, October 31st, so if you are aiming to be a star and join our Cosmic Crown Showdown\n(HEX's bimonthly $5,000 cash tournament) make sure you climb as high as you can. The top 64 players from limited and constructed will be invited, so be prepared. Our next Cosmic Crown Showdown will happen on November\n. Only a chosen few can write their name in the stars!\nOthers make their mark in different ways. Today, InfamousNeo and our stream team are finishing up the last day of annual Charity Stream! Help make this a fantastic close to four full days of charitable giving by visiting them\nand showing your support\n.\nIn honor of the charity stream, we will be granting everyone with an account by October 29th the 2017 Charity Sleeve! We will also be granting the stylish Diamond's Favor AA as well. This event has continually showcased the best side of our community. In these final hours, let's show them what we're made of once again!\nWhen HEX transitioned back to us from Gameforge, everyone's authenticator was desynched from their account as we are no longer using the Gameforge authentication system. If you have (or would like) an authenticator on your account, please make sure it is enabled. You can do so by going to \"Account\" on the HEXTCG.com website, logging in, and clicking \"Enable.\" We use Google Authenticator, so you will need that installed on a device of your choice as well. You can log in and check your authenticator status by clicking here\n.\nThis weekend is your\nto nab our Orchi-Notion and Massacre AAs. The format this month is\n. Tournament times are as follows:\nThe HEX Bash\nand HEX Clash\nare back once more! Saturday and Sunday, starting at 8am PT (Timezone Conversion\n), you have another chance to prove your mettle and walk away with cash and exclusive prizes! Will you end up a proud owner of fine cosmetics like last week's Bash\nor Clash\nwinners?\n\u00a0\nJoin us this weekend and find out!\nFor full details on prizing, please check out our tournament pages here\nand here\n.\nPlease note: if you happen to have technical issues with the Clash or Bash events, our support team requests that you submit an output log from that same day along with your ticket. This is essential, not only to ensure your ticket gets resolved in a timely fashion, but also to help us prevent similar problems from occurring in the future. Output, error, and crash logs can be found in the HEX: Shards of Fate program install folder on your machine.\nis aptly named. As Cory Jones has teased a few times, most recently in his charity stream opening interview\n, a major character will die over the course of this new set. Who could it be? How will they die? Make sure to put your predictions in the forums below. And\u2014OHH #$@$!! Could it have anything to do with these?!\n\u00a0\nThat's right, the otherworldly entities from\nwill all be animated! You can check them out on our website.\nThis includes our first ever\n, Entity Unknown!\nThere's so much more on the way, so stay tuned here and on social media for more\nspoilers as we gear up towards release.\nSee you in the battlegrounds~\nGot any questions? Want to chat with other players? Then discuss this article in our Forums\n! You can also follow us on Twitter, Facebook, our YouTube channel, or enjoy regular streams on our official Twitch channel\n.", "early_access": false}
