{"page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2018-01-11", "text": "Way of Defector is fascinating. You are helping North Korean defector escape through China, and together you go on an emotional journey where you feel responsible for this real-life inspired person's survival.\nThe game is far from perfect though, and the decision to make every outcome determine by a dice roll ranges from mildly irritating to screw this game. The writing could also use work, and there are a certain amount of weird and overly 'gamey' moment that seem very out of place.\nHowever, if you can look past all of that, then you will find a game that is like nothing else you will have played before.\nFor the full review please visit here -", "hours": 4.1, "username": "Neodyminium", "products": 305, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "410380", "page": 3, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "text": "Welcome to a round up of the week. We have lore, spoilers, tournaments, and more!\nis approaching fast, and the updates keep on dropping. Not only did we have a PS4 client patch on Thursday\n, but\nlead Corey Burkhart also walked us through the new \"drop\" resource cycle\nwe can look forward to in set 8. Resources are the foundation of a good deck, and these are spicy enough to ensure we can stay warm in the cold winter to come.\nAnd as long as we are dropping knowledge, we also had two new lore articles this week. On Wednesday, we revisited the underdogs of the arena\n. These are the teams that seem doomed, who can't seem to catch a break. But, that doesn't mean their stories shouldn't be heard. Losing teams, we salute you!\nThen today, we introduced the enigmatic Void Star in our latest short story,\n. This lore piece really gets into the head of this latest member of the Cult of the Nameless City, so buckle up and try to stay sane. It's going to be a bumpy ride.\nFinally, we have a few quick reminders. First, our exciting Kismet's Draft mashup will go back into the vault come\nrelease. If you still haven't gotten all of the six beautifully animated sleeves\nfrom this event, be sure to join the draft queue soon! Every three match wins will get you another sleeve, so the next one is just a few wins away.\nSecond, the Sunsoul Phoenix and Hero of Legend Collector's Decks will be leaving the client for good with the\nrelease.\nMake sure to stock up now if you want any of these beautiful alternate arts, sleeves, or animated cards, because these beauties will not be returning to the store. This is your last chance!\nOur Season 5 Cosmic Crown Showdown\nis happening this weekend! This $5,000 cash tournament will pit our best players from last season\nin both constructed and limited together in an epic clash for prizes, glory, and cold, hard cash. The action starts November\n, starting at 9am Pacific\n, so be sure to save the date. We will see you all there!\nThe HEX Bash\nand HEX Clash\nare back once more! Saturday and Sunday, starting at 8am PT (Timezone Conversion\n), you have another chance to prove your mettle and walk away with cash and exclusive prizes! Will you end up a proud owner of fine cosmetics like last week's Bash\nor Clash\nwinners?\n\u00a0\nJoin us this weekend and find out!\nFor full details on prizing, please check out our tournament pages here\nand here\n.\nPlease note: if you happen to have technical issues with the Clash or Bash events, our support team requests that you submit an output log from that same day along with your ticket. This is essential, not only to ensure your ticket gets resolved in a timely fashion, but also to help us prevent similar problems from occurring in the future. Output, error, and crash logs can be found in the HEX: Shards of Fate program install folder on your machine.\nFinally, while you've come across the Twilight Host\nand their new mechanic Verdict\nbefore, this next spoiler should give you a better sense of their power. Walking the balance of two worlds, we are excited to introduce the Arbiter of Twilight:\nThis spiritual judge will turn all your Verdicts into Ancient ones. What exactly does that mean, you ask? Take a look!\nNow, whenever you Verdict, your opponent will be forced to choose from these powerful effects instead of the normal ones. Talk about a tough sentence! How do you find this sweet new legendary? Be sure to share your verdict in the forums below.\nAlso, don't forget to stay tuned here and on social media for more\nspoilers as we gear up towards release.\nSee you in the battlegrounds~\nGot any questions? Want to chat with other players? Then discuss this article in our Forums\n! You can also follow us on Twitter, Facebook, our YouTube channel, or enjoy regular streams on our official Twitch channel\n.", "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "410380", "page": 3, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "text": "Welcome to a round up of the week. We have lore, spoilers, and more!\nis approaching, and the Frost Ring Arena tournament is really heating up. Teams are at each other's throats, and not everyone will make it out unscathed. Check out the battle between the Pack and the Luminaries here\n. And, if you haven't already taken a peek, the Blightbark Court entered stage-right today\n. Be sure to check these pieces out for all new story bits and some upcoming cards!\nAnd that's not all\u2014this week we pulled back the curtain and took a look at how HEX cards are made. First, we had an excellent article by our very own Corey Burkhart which walked us through the design of a card\nfrom the start of an R&D file to the end. Then, Art Director, Tyler James introduced us to an amazing artist\nwhose work appears in our upcoming set. Then, to top it all off, we had another dev stream where Tyler did a little work of his own\n! Pretty sweet, right?\nOur 5th Ladder season of 2017 has come to a close. Congratulations to our top 64 players\nfrom both constructed and limited! You will each get an invite to our Cosmic Crown Showdown\n(HEX's bimonthly $5,000 cash tournament). This next Cosmic Crown Showdown will happen on November\n, starting at 9am Pacific\n. Be sure to save the date, and we will see you all there!\nFor the rest of us, it's climb time. Ladder season #6 is fresh and new, and there are all-new exciting new cosmetics to collect:\nEarn those stars and grab your copies today!\nThe HEX Bash\nand HEX Clash\nare back once more! Saturday and Sunday, starting at 8am PT (Timezone Conversion\n), you have another chance to prove your mettle and walk away with cash and exclusive prizes! Will you end up a proud owner of fine cosmetics like last week's Bash\nor Clash\nwinners?\n\u00a0\nJoin us this weekend and find out!\nFor full details on prizing, please check out our tournament pages here\nand here\n.\nPlease note: if you happen to have technical issues with the Clash or Bash events, our support team requests that you submit an output log from that same day along with your ticket. This is essential, not only to ensure your ticket gets resolved in a timely fashion, but also to help us prevent similar problems from occurring in the future. Output, error, and crash logs can be found in the HEX: Shards of Fate program install folder on your machine.\nBy now you've read today's lore article, right? No? Okay, give it a quick gander\nand then come back. It's alright, we'll wait.\nSo now that you know some of the major beats coming in\n, let's talk a bit about story. HEX's digital nature lets us do all sorts of pretty innovative things. Much of that you see everyday when you play with the cards themselves. Our R&D team puts a lot of love into crafting an incredibly rich and unique experience. But, part of the exciting innovations we can bring relate to story... and art. Because things are digital, as our story evolves, we are able to have key characters evolve too. Thus, we have a secret champion change to announce for our\nroster. Puck and Balthasar are no more. Instead, we now have Balthasar the Elegist:\nThe death of a dream is a truly painful thing.\nStay tuned here and on social media for more\nspoilers as we gear up towards release!\nSee you in the battlegrounds~\nGot any questions? Want to chat with other players? Then discuss this article in our Forums\n! You can also follow us on Twitter, Facebook, our YouTube channel, or enjoy regular streams on our official Twitch channel\n.", "early_access": false}
