{"product_id": "378860", "page": 4, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2018-01-10", "text": "Coming from other sims such as Race 07, Asseto Corsa, Dirt Rally, etc. I have to say that PCars2 is one of the most FUN sims out there, however it isn't necessarily the best sim out there.\nIs it a sim though???\nPCars2 is probably the best middle ground between a hardcore sim and an arcade game out there. From a driving standpoint, most cars are fairly easy to handle. As such things like heel toe downshifting, rev matching, and car tuning are all fairly easy. Every car has a distinct feeling and every track feels and looks real.\nWhat about features???\nTime trials is by far my favorite mode. If you love racing others for world records on tracks this game logs it all. It's a great challenge to beat another person's time and you don't have to worry about actually \"racing\" other cars. Career mode is challenging at times if you want it to be. Adjusting the AI can make it even more of a challenge. Online racing is eh, not many lobbies exist and if there are it might not be a track or car you want to race with. Also the penalty system seems to be a bit broken, with you being heavily punished for cutting corners or making contact. If you are simply looking for online P2P racing, this is NOT your game. That corner of the market has been claimed by AC, rFactor, and iRacing.\nWhat about graphics???\nExcellent, simply excellent.\nAnd sound?\nGreat, as well.\nPhysics?\nOn most tracks the physics are fine, but sometimes cars will act wildly when they go airborne on certain tracks. This can be annoying.\nTracks and Cars???\nThere is such a wide variety of tracks and cars. All of the world's top tracks are included so your favorite track is most likely in the game. Fun road courses and rallycross tracks are also included. Dozens of cars are in the game, and if you are into GT racing, then this game has your favorite car most likely. The vintage cars are a unique challenge as well.\nVerdict-9/10\nUnless you are a super hardcore sim racer or a only-race-online type, this game will probably be your favorite racing game out there. In my eyes it is only rivaled by Dirt Rally which is in a different class of racing anyways.", "hours": 20.9, "user_id": "76561198049575798", "username": "Maverick018", "products": 96, "early_access": false}
