{"product_id": "410380", "page": 4, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "text": "Welcome to a round up of the week! We have our official PS4 release date, Kismet's Draft, and more:\nOn Wednesday we announced a special new draft format\nfor your enjoyment. Kismet Drafts, a special event using curated packs of cards from sets 3-7, is out now! Enjoy some of the best HEX has to offer, hand picked by our R&D team for maximum wackiness. As if that weren't enough, every third match win will award one of 6, beautifully animated sleeves\n! They are exclusive to this mode, so jump in today and get lucky!\nIn our original announcement, we also gave the full card list for these special Kismet Packs. It turns out Kismet is fickle and has some slight changes for maximum fun. Here they are!\n!\nChampions and Gems have also been changed to Standard Legal. These tweaks add a few new viable archetypes to this wacky, mashup format. It's exciting, and we can't wait to jump in and start playing with you guys later today.\nGood news! We have passed the Sony submission process for our PS4 client, HEX: Card Clash. We are super stoked! We also have an official release date\u2014Tuesday, October 17th. This is pushed back slightly from the 10th so that Sony marketing wizards can go to town, but it is a date we can now hang our hat on. This client is the result of some incredibly dedicated work by the team, and we can't wait to release it into the wild.\nWe are setting sail! Say good by to the Coastline Battleboard on Friday, October 13th at 10am Pacific. In its place, we will have the squee-worthy Boat Battleboard:\nSea your opponents cower in fear before this mighty board. If you've ever wanted to be a pirate, you'll soon have your chance. For now, pick up that Coastline Battleboard if you haven't already so you can have a matching pair. We're shoving off, and it won't be back for some time.\nThe HEX Bash\nand HEX Clash\nare back once more! Saturday and Sunday, starting at 8am PT (Timezone Conversion\n), you have another chance to prove your mettle and walk away with cash and exclusive prizes! Will you end up a proud owner of fine cosmetics like last week's Bash\nor Clash\nwinners?\nJoin us this weekend and find out!\nFor full details on prizing, please check out our tournament pages here\nand here\n.\nPlease note: if you happen to have technical issues with the Clash or Bash events, our support team requests that you submit an output log from that same day along with your ticket. This is essential, not only to ensure your ticket gets resolved in a timely fashion, but also to help us prevent similar problems from occurring in the future. Output, error, and crash logs can be found in the HEX: Shards of Fate program install folder on your machine.\nOur friend Robb Mommaerts is doing a Kickstarter to raise funds for a gorgeous collection of his black and white illustrations.\nRobb Mommaerts's work has appeared everywhere from games, comics, to children's books. But with your help, for the first time ever, they will be collected in one beautiful place. If you enjoy whimsy coupled with fantastic detail, then you should definitely check this out!\nSee you in the battlegrounds~\nGot any questions? Want to chat with other players? Then discuss this article in our Forums\n! You can also follow us on Twitter, Facebook, our YouTube channel, or enjoy regular streams on our official Twitch channel\n.", "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "410380", "page": 4, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "text": "Welcome to a round up of the week! Our latest spoiler season begins, exciting tournaments grace the horizon, and more:\nIn the north, teams from all over Entrath battle for their heart's desire. Drawn by Hogarth's empty whispers they fight to the death, unknowingly fueling his escape from Frostheart and the spirits which bind him to the Frost Ring Arena. Yet as Hogarth approaches his final victory, Lixil draws near, called by the giant sapphire to end his life.\nWe are thrilled to announce that the spoiler season for our 8th set,\n, has officially begun! We are kicking it off with a lore piece about the moment Lixil and Hogarth finally meet\n. But there is so much more to come, so be sure to stay tuned here and on social media over the next few weeks. We're gearing up, and it's going to be a blast! Winter is on its way.\nPart of this next set will be revisiting the teams we know and love from\n. What better way to prepare than by reading up on this action with The Librarian Collector's Deck? Available now in the in-game store, this deck shows the creepy side of the Cult of the Nameless City in fully animated glory\n. Be sure to grab your copy today!\nSpeaking of creepy-crawlies, the masters of the night have arrived with our latest Kismet's Reserve Pack:\nIf you want cards that really raise the stakes, this pack is right on point. For 15,000 gold you will get one of these batty delights:\nKismet's Vampire Reserves are available in-store now, so go on and suck them all up! They'll only be there for a limited time.\nHaunted Harvest is finally here\n! Join us today through November 3rd for this spooky holiday, and walk away with some exclusive sleeves, alternate arts, and an all new PvE card. Yum!\nThe new and improved HEX Primal Immortal Championship series\n(ICS) is starting off with a bang\non\n. For this Sunday only, the ICS capstone tournament will have no ticket cost as part of a transition to our Immortal Weekly qualifying system\n. With hundreds of dollars of HEX Primal store credit, packs, and the all new AA Rune Ear Hierophant up for grabs, you should definitely hop on by!\nThe HEX Bash\nand HEX Clash\nare back once more! Saturday and Sunday, starting at 8am PT (Timezone Conversion\n), you have another chance to prove your mettle and walk away with cash and exclusive prizes! Will you end up a proud owner of fine cosmetics like last week's Bash\nor Clash\nwinners?\n\u00a0\nJoin us this weekend and find out!\nFor full details on prizing, please check out our tournament pages here\nand here\n.\nPlease note: if you happen to have technical issues with the Clash or Bash events, our support team requests that you submit an output log from that same day along with your ticket. This is essential, not only to ensure your ticket gets resolved in a timely fashion, but also to help us prevent similar problems from occurring in the future. Output, error, and crash logs can be found in the HEX: Shards of Fate program install folder on your machine.\nWith all this sweet news, we mustn't forget that the Charity Stream\nis starting next week. You won't want to miss this five-day long mega stream! Not only will we be raising money to help sick kids, but there will be prizes, giveaways, some dev appearances... not to mention your favorite streamers will be putting on a fantastic show over on our official twitch channel\n. The fun starts Wednesday, October 25th, so be sure to mark your calendar. Full details can be found in the charity stream's official forum thread\n.\nSee you in the battlegrounds~\nGot any questions? Want to chat with other players? Then discuss this article in our Forums\n! You can also follow us on Twitter, Facebook, our YouTube channel, or enjoy regular streams on our official Twitch channel\n.", "early_access": false}
