{"product_id": "410380", "page": 5, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "text": "Welcome to a round up of the week! We have our next Exalted player, a reminder to transfer your accounts if you haven't already, and more:\nOn February 20, 2017 Gameforge and HEX Entertainment announced that HEX Entertainment would again be responsible for publishing HEX: Shards of Fate in addition to its development. Since then, Gameforge has generously kept its servers open to aid players in transitioning collections to HEX Entertainment servers. However, on\n, Gameforge will be closing their servers for good. To ensure that your collections are transferred safely, if you haven't previously transferred\nThe Cosmic Crown Showdown is\n! Join Hacky, Snake, and Neo on the official channel\nas they cheer on the top 128 players\nfrom last season's ladder. With a $5,000 dollar prize pool, packs, and the coveted cosmic sleeve on the line, you don't want to miss it. The fun starts at 9:00 AM PT on September 9th (Worldclock\n). See you there!\nThe Coastline Battleboard is in stores now! Don't bury your head in the sand, come sea the latest in battleboard bling:\nLet's celebrate the end of summer with a splash! It's time for some real fun in the sun.\nThe HEX Bash\nand HEX Clash\nare back once more! Saturday and Sunday, starting at 8am PT (Timezone Conversion\n), you have another chance to prove your mettle and walk away with cash and exclusive prizes! Will you end up a proud owner of fine cosmetics like last week's Bash\nor Clash\nwinners?\nJoin us this weekend and find out!\nFor full details on prizing, please check out our tournament pages here\nand here\n.\nOur second Exalted player this year is someone who has continually helped build the community. There is very little out there that he hasn't had his hands in at one point in time. He made some of the first HEX videos around, streams constantly, and has many podcast appearances to his name. He even made his way to our first ever HEX Invitational. All that would be impressive on its own, but this person was also instrumental in bringing to life our yearly charity stream tradition. This charity stream has been a rallying point for the community, and with his (and your) help, we as a community continue to raise truly impressive amounts of money to help sick kids. It is for this reason that we are happy to announce that InfamousNeo is this year's Community Exalted:\nYou've inspired us to be greater than the sum of our parts. You continue to bring us together, both on and off stream, which is why we are pleased to grant a vanity card in your honor. Thank you so much for everything you have done for HEX and the people who play it.\nSee you in the battlegrounds~\nGot any questions? Want to chat with other players? Then discuss this article in our Forums\n! You can also follow us on Twitter, Facebook, our YouTube channel, or enjoy regular streams on our official Twitch channel\n.", "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "410380", "page": 5, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "text": "Welcome to a round up of the week! We have our final Exalted player for the year, new VIP Alternate Arts, and more:\nWe are looking for a few more dedicated and passionate individuals to join the HEX team for the Visual Effects\nand Technical Artist\npositions. As you know, we like to pull from the community whenever possible, so if you have the skills and experience to help make fantastic things for our players, you should definitely check this out! Follow the above links or visit our careers page\nand submit your resume today.\nOur VIP Alternate Arts are rotating next week. This upcoming VIP Sealed tournament will be the first time you can get your hands on the beautiful but deadly AA Massacre and AA Orchi-Notion!\nNow you can dream stompy, ramp dreams with a stylish Orchi-Notion. One should always dream big, am I right? If that much cuteness isn't lethal, you can finish the job with the ultimate dragon breath. That Uruunaz doesn't mess around! With his help, you can answer your opponent's troop swarms with a \"wide\" smile of your own. Join our VIP program and prepare to win your own beautiful AA copies next weekend.\nYou can learn more about our VIP program here\nor by visiting our VIP FAQ\n.\nOn Tuesday, Corey Burkhart joined us once again for a Watch & Ban List\nupdate, where he announced some pretty big news. On Monday, September 18th at 10am Pacific, Lazgar's Vengeance will be banned from the Standard Format.\nLazgar's has been deemed too restrictive for the current meta, so in the interest of promoting archetype diversity, it is going to be removed. Banning a card is not something we do lightly, but we feel that this decision will create a better constructed environment for everyone to enjoy. For full details on the team's reasoning on this announcement, be sure to check out Burkhart's full write-up\n.\nCommunity member CoachFliperon has been creating excellent PvE content on his own for some time. Now he is looking to jump-start this passion with a group of like-minded individuals looking to build a bigger PvE community. If you've ever thought about creating guides, decks, or videos about HEX's campaign, you should definitely read his thread\nover on the HEX forums. Even if you just want to hang out with others who've been bitten by the campaign bug, the thread is worth a look. CoachFliperon is giving away a veritable\n. Come help name the group and get involved for some of the\nhe is giving away!\nThe HEX Bash\nand HEX Clash\nare back once more! Saturday and Sunday, starting at 8am PT (Timezone Conversion\n), you have another chance to prove your mettle and walk away with cash and exclusive prizes! Will you end up a proud owner of fine cosmetics like last week's Bash\nor Clash\nwinners?\n\u00a0\nJoin us this weekend and find out!\nFor full details on prizing, please check out our tournament pages here\nand here\n.\nPlease note: if you happen to have technical issues with the Clash or Bash events, our support team requests that you submit an output log from that same day along with your ticket. This is essential, not only to ensure your ticket gets resolved in a timely fashion, but also to help us prevent similar problems from occurring in the future. Output, error, and crash logs can be found in the HEX: Shards of Fate program install folder on your machine.\nOur third and final Exalted this year is someone who joined our community relatively recently, but whose impact has been felt deeply in that time. They have been a tireless proponent of the game from the moment they joined and have continually striven to help others play at a competitive level. This player writes extensively, whether it is articles covering the latest constructed tech or programs for displaying decklists just a little bit easier, and they have even compiled resources for players looking to break into the constructed scene. As if that weren't enough, they also find time to stream regularly to showcase exciting new decks and help move the meta forward. For this unwavering outreach in the constructed realm, we are happy to announce that Jeff Hoogland is this year's Exalted Player:\nYou entertain, inform, and help make HEX constructed easier for everyone to pick up, which is why we are pleased to grant a vanity card in your honor. Thank you so much for your insightful play and extraordinary commitment to showcasing what HEX has to offer.\nSee you in the battlegrounds~\nGot any questions? Want to chat with other players? Then discuss this article in our Forums\n! You can also follow us on Twitter, Facebook, our YouTube channel, or enjoy regular streams on our official Twitch channel\n.", "early_access": false}
