{"product_id": "347400", "page": 3, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "text": "With our\nfinally released, we're now back into the full swing of things! A new version of 001 Game Creator (v1.018.008) is now available on Steam and is packed with tons of new content and bug fixes.\nAs always, you can see the full change log\nNow let's go over some of these changes, shall we?\nWhat better place to start than with the first thing you're greeted with upon opening 001 Game Creator. In an effort to make 001 a little more user-friendly, we've tweaked the New / Open Game window to be more streamlined:\nAdditionally, we've cleaned up the main toolbar by removing the icons for Legacy Settings (now called Advanced Game Settings), Visual Settings and Startup Menu Settings. These options are still available in the main menu, as always, and are also now accessible in the Game Settings window too:\nNormal Mapping and Material Editing are now available for Sprites, having previously only been available for Tile-Sets, giving you access to custom shaders across the board!  They work the same way too! Simply select \"Normal\" from the \"Mapping\" drop down menu to add/edit your Sprite's normal maps. To edit materials, just click the \"Edit Material\" button next to the \"Graphic Scripting\" button to open the Material Editor:\nThis new Actor Graphic Option allows you to create fixed animation speeds, which is something that several users have been asking for. Essentially, this option allows you to specify the frame rate at which the Sprite animation plays at, regardless of its speed.\nWe've updated 001's Debugger with a new \"Performance\" section that lists slow triggers and collisions. We hope this extra feedback will prove useful to those looking to optimise their games for the best possible performance!\nPathfinding (used by AI and for \"Walk to...\" type events) has been greatly improved, resulting in a lot of fixes to issues that have plagued users for some time, including characters teleporting into or getting stuck in nearby collisions.\nAnd lastly, a small but very useful Field option that allows you to create overlaying Fields without them obstructing selectable Fields underneath them!\nAs we mentioned last time, we've created an official 001 Game Creator\naccount where we've been sharing all of your 001 game creations! If you're on Instagram then please feel free to follow us for new posts every Monday, Thursday and Saturday! If you're got a 001 game you'd like us to showcase, then don't hesitate to get in contact with us!\nWe hope you enjoy the latest version and all that it has to offer. We're still working hard on our planned Point & Click Adventure Kit and so, with that said, here's a small parting gift from the team...a little sneak peek:", "early_access": false}
