{"product_id": "347400", "page": 3, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "text": "After a long wait, we're pleased to announce that our\nhas finally launched on Steam!\nhttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=-MNdHHsKv3o\nThis DLC Kit provides users with a variety of 3D assets including 9 weapons (both firearms and melee), over 40 environmental objects, male and female arm rigs, 4 zombie enemies, 2 soldiers (male/female) with outfits and 2 room kits that include floors, walls, doors and trims.\nUpon starting the game, players will start in a test room where they can get suited up and choose between two doors. One leads to a zombie-invested nightmare whereas the other challenges players to solve puzzles in order to progress.\nIn addition to the launch of our new DLC Kit, we've also updated 001 Game Creator to v1.018.007 which is required to ensure our\nruns correctly but also comes with a bunch of general bug fixes, performance optimisations and small additions.\nTo see the full list of changes, please check our our change log here: http://www.engine001.com/changes.htm\nWe've also recently launched an official\naccount for 001 Game Creator that we're using to share screenshots of your 001 game creations - with new posts every Monday, Thursday and Saturday! Be sure to check it out to see some of the amazing stuff that's been created with 001 Game Creator!\nWe'd like to thank you all for your patience in finally getting this DLC Kit released. There were numerous delays but in the end we've created something that we think you'll truly enjoy and 001 Game Creator itself has benefited greatly also, as many of the recent performance optimisations were made thanks in part to this DLC Kit!\nOur next community update won't be until the release of our last of three planned DLC Kits, the\n- which we aim to have ready before the year's end. We hope you're looking forward to it! :)", "early_access": false}
