{"product_id": "410380", "page": 6, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "text": "Welcome to a round up of the week! We have an action packed weekend, a call for more community translators, and more!\nThe first ever HEX Bash is\nSaturday at 8am PT! If you haven't already done so, be sure to get your brews ready to rumble. There is a $1000 prize-pool and red hot cosmetics on the line\n.\nAlso, be sure to tune into our official Twitch channel\nbright and early as Hacky and Pentachills cast this exciting event.\nIf Immortal is more your style, the HexPrimal Immortal Championship Series\nis also running this Saturday! Today is your last day to grab the 20 tickets you need to qualify, so don't delay.\nThis free tournament offers some pretty fantastic prizes!\n*Contains 1 copy of all cards of a set chosen by HexPrimal.com\nProve your mettle and have your name ring out today! The HexPrimal Casting Team will also be covering the event in style over on the HexPrimal Twitch channel\n, so be sure to stop on by and say hi.\nThe HEX Clash\nis back once more! Sunday, starting at 8am PT (Worldclock\n), you have another chance to prove your mettle and walk away with cash and exclusive prizes! Will you end up a proud owner of these fine cosmetics like last week's winners\n?\n\u00a0\n\u00a0\nJoin us this Sunday and find out!\nFor full details on prizing, please check out our tournament page here\n.\nThar she blows! The Sea Festival in-game holiday is only one week away! Be sure to log in on the 18th to receive a holiday exclusive sleeve! Special Alternate Arts and Campaign goodies will also be available to those willing to venture into troubled waters. Scout out the details\ntoday!.\nOur community translators have been hard at work, and we couldn't be more pleased! Our current members have been working behind the scenes to bring great improvements to our foreign language clients. In fact, their work has been going so well that we are looking to expand the program. We are putting out a call for Community Translators with a focus on\n. Please send applications to dinotropia@hextcg.com with the subject \"Japanese Translation Application.\" Be sure to tell us a little bit about yourself and include any past experience that would make you a good fit for this role. We're looking forward to hearing from you!\nSee you on the Battlefield~\nGot any questions? Want to chat with other players? Then discuss this article in our Forums\n! You can also follow us on Twitter, Facebook, our YouTube channel, or enjoy regular streams on our official Twitch channel\n.", "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "410380", "page": 6, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "text": "Welcome to a round up of the week! We have ladder rollover, Exalted announcements, and more!\nIt's that time again! Our current ladder season is almost over. On August 31st, at 11:59 PM Pacific\n, the 2017 Ladder Season #4 will come to a close. This means you have one week to climb to Cosmic and get the AA Gallant Spearcliff animated sleeve.\n\u00a0\nAt rollover, our best players from both the Constructed and Limited ladders will also receive an invitation to compete in the Cosmic Crown Showdown!\nThere, our best players will duke it out with\non the line. For your chance to be a star, make sure you climb that Cosmic leaderboard. Only the top 64 players from each ladder will secure their chance to compete. It's climb time!\nIf you've ever wanted more HEX video content to watch, community members Largashbur and Darkfall have got you covered. With financial support by KingGabriel, Edswor, and BroomBot, they have put together http://vod.hexcompendium.com/. This sweet site is a one-stop portal for on-demand gameplay, tournament, and review video content. You should definitely take a look if you haven't already. Great job, guys!\nThis weekend is your\nto nab our Typhoon Skyshaper and Cryptcurse Knight AAs. The format this month is\n. Tournament times are as follows:\n\u00a0\nYou can learn more about our VIP program here\nor by visiting our VIP FAQ\n.\nThe HEX Bash\nand HEX Clash\nare back once more! Saturday and Sunday, starting at 8am PT (Timezone Conversion\n), you have another chance to prove your mettle and walk away with cash and exclusive prizes! Will you end up a proud owner of fine cosmetics like last week's Bash\nor Clash\nwinners?\n\u00a0\nJoin us this weekend and find out!\nFor full details on prizing, please check out our tournament pages here\nand here\n.\nAs many of you already know, for the past few years we have run the Exalted Program. This program is our chance to recognize community members who have distinguished themselves within our already amazing community. We show our thanks and immortalize these paragons in the form of honorary cards, to represent their lasting impact on the community and HEX itself.\nTraditionally, we have announced that honor to a single person at Gen Con. This year we are doing something a little different. Our community has so many members who do remarkable things for this game on a regular basis, this time we will be honoring\npeople who have helped make our game a better place to be. These Exalted will come from three distinct categories:\n\u00a0\nWe will be announcing these new Exalted over the month of September. Stay tuned to find out who will receive our highest honor!\nSee you in the battlegrounds~\nGot any questions? Want to chat with other players? Then discuss this article in our Forums\n! You can also follow us on Twitter, Facebook, our YouTube channel, or enjoy regular streams on our official Twitch channel\n.", "early_access": false}
