{"product_id": "234820", "page": 8, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-01-04", "text": "One of the only pieces of software ive ever bought!\nThis is a must have piece of software for anyone that owns a PC, i honestly have no idea WTF ive been doing to fix driver issues up untill the point i bought this!\nFixed all my graphics driver issues in less than 30min!\nBuy this, dont even think that it might not work for you! It will!\n11/10", "hours": 29.2, "username": "DrMzInDeC", "products": 49, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "234820", "page": 8, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-01-03", "text": "I tried this out this weekend and had to ask for a refund. The software had several issues with my system (AMD 8320, Asus 990fx board, MSI 960GTX, 16 gb ram and 2tb drive). The first issue had to do with my account creation and login. There is an option button to keep you signed in after your initial setup. Well, everytime I would shut off steam or my computer, it would not allow me to log back into driver fusion the next time around. The account would go back to the Free version and ask me to sign in, which I would spend the next 5-10 minutes trying to do because the software would not allow me too since it mentioned that I was signed in somewhere else, but still not give me my premium account. Not sure, but I think this has to do with having to log into STeam to use this software and it's confusing the program.\nThe second issue I had is that the software would lock up on me when ever I would switch from one tab to another. Each time I used the software, I would have to ctrl-alt-delete to get it to stop cycling. This would get extremely annoying because then I would have to go through the whole sign in issue again each time.\nOn another note, I was quite skeptical of the software's ability to get  me the latest drivers in many areas. I downloaded the most recent Nvidia drivers just before installing this software and each time, it would tell me that my video and sound drivers were outdated and would refer to drivers that were outdated. I also ended up not trusting it's ability to FIX the driver issues as well. During my initial use, I was able to get the scan to work, which resulted in about 586 MB download. After turning off the video and sound drivers, I had around 146 MB to download, which I did do. It took around 10 seconds to download them and another 15 seconds to fix them all as complete. Wow! Talk about super highway! Not really.....I went into my files and found that the same old driver versions were still in place and nothing was done, but the program would show that there were no issues to fix.\nDriver fusion is a good idea, but the implementation is very poor at this time. I would almost have to say that this should not have been released yet and would have been better off in the Early Access stage or beta. Maybe other people have had better luck with it, but not me. My experience in computers is 15 years building, selling gaming computers and servers, along with 10 years of software engineering experience.", "hours": 1.8, "username": "shade1968", "products": 85, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "234820", "page": 8, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-01-01", "text": "Great little software to keep you computer in top driver shape!!  I recommend it.", "hours": 8.4, "username": "UrsusMajorCA", "products": 62, "early_access": false}
