{"product_id": "609150", "page": 13, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-05", "text": "Is there anybody else who decided to buy PS3 the moment he or she saw this game? I saw a glimpse of it on friend's Xbox 360 in 2010 and was charmed with graphics and it's colors. Their suits, environment... Something attracted me there. I spent a lot of time in this game, sold the console long time ago, but couldn't forget it, wanted to play it again. And was very surprised to know about the port. It looked amazing on PS3 but now with all the resolution and details increased a lot, this game looks just like I imagined it should. All the shiny details and reflections in all their glory. I felt the same with Bayonetta port. It's like a dream came true! Oh, and no more loading screens!!! Thank you very much, developers and publishers, my dear Japanese people who made my childhood happy and made this happen! In all my long gaming life I bought very few games in digital distribution shops. This one I felt I definitely want to have, it really is special for me. It has amazing atmosphere and exploration feeling, great music, mentioned stunning visuals/design and combat system and very good scenario. And a lot of neat small things inside like cooking, quest system etc. The only downside of this game is repetetive enemies on every planet. They are the same, only stronger and of different color. This thing is what makes the initially good and fun battle system repetitive and maybe even annoying later in the game and makes all that collection quest boring.\nWorks like a charm on usual 60hz monitor. Looks very beautiful and runs 60fps without huccups on GTX 1050 2Gb, Phenom II 965 CPU and 8Gb RAM, Windows 10 pro. I don't know about crowdy places and close-up graphics, but in the beginning while walking on Aeos and in battles it takes, as Afterburner utility says, around 1 Gb  of video memory and around 6Gb of RAM. Need to investigate further into the game, but I think it's a very good port.\nI saw a small problem with hair shadows on faces but I hope it's nothing to worry about and will get fixed.", "hours": 28.5, "user_id": "76561198057306377", "username": "oldghost83", "products": 7, "early_access": false}
