{"product_id": "609150", "page": 13, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-05", "text": "There's a lot of complaints you can have about this game. But in the end it all comes down to if you like a good Action-JRPG or not. Of course there's your usual anime tropes that can get annoying. Of course a certain feeling of repetitiveness can settle in after some time when it comes to the battles.\nBut IMHO the Star Ocean series is an underrated gem, especially considering its general and this game's specific age. You have a deep crafting system and different characters to control during battles that all require different play styles for you to figure out on your own. It's nice when a game doesn't completely hold you by the hand all the time and most, somewhat seasoned, players can easily find out the things you aren't told directly.\nI haven't had any crashes or problems with sound so far and I'm running it on a Surface 4 (i7).\nSo buy this thing! Jesus!", "hours": 23.7, "user_id": "76561198044820058", "username": "rowdy_no", "products": 63, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
