{"product_id": "410380", "page": 9, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "text": "Welcome to a round up of the week! We have spoilers galore, updated VIP times, Questmas, and more!\nnews keeps coming thick and fast! There's nothing quite like freshly fallen spoilers. First up this week, Corey Burkhart walked us through how one of the major figures from the Cult of the Nameless City\nwas designed. If you've ever wondered how HEX cards get made, be sure to check out his article here\n.\nNext, Ryan Sutherland covered some back-end changes to how commons will appear in packs, introducing our new concept of Core Commons\n. It's worth a read if you like design and understanding how our packs are put together.\nFinally, we had some big news this week! Ryan returned triumphantly to announce updates\nto our much beloved PvE mode\u2014The Frost Ring Arena! This update will bring over 200 pieces of lootable equipment, all new champions, bosses, and an overhaul of the progression and challenge systems in the Frost Ring. Join the teams from\nand battle it out in Hogarth's arena... if you dare!\nOur in-game holiday, Questmas, is upon us once more\n! Grab your favorite decks out of your toy chests and join Entrath in a rousing game of capture the flag. Questmas starts today, so make sure you log in to receive your exclusive sleeve!\nThe second HexPrimal Immortal Championship tournament\nis this Saturday. If you plan to join us on June 17th, you only have one more day to get your 20 qualifying tickets from the HEX Primal Immortal queue.\nRemember, this tournament has some pretty great prizes, including:\n*Contains 1 copy of all cards of a set chosen by HexPrimal.com\nCome for the prizes, stay for some of the craziest card combos HEX has to offer!\nWe have been listening to the community response to our consolidating our VIP tournament times, and we are pleased to announce that we are adding two extra times for our EU and Australian based players. Every month, we will now also offer VIP tournaments on Saturday and Sunday at 1am Pacific. This should provide a morning and evening option respectively for players in those regions. Scheduling times that are convenient for everyone across the globe is a challenging task, but we truly value everyone who enjoys and supports our game. Thank you for all your constructive feedback on our forums\n, and thank you for your continued support of HEX.\nSpeaking of tournaments, the HEX Clash\nis back once more! Sunday, starting at 8am PT (Worldclock\n), you have another chance to prove your mettle and walk away with cash and exclusive prizes! Will you end up a proud owner of these fine cosmetics like last week's winners\n?\n\u00a0\nJoin us this Sunday and find out!\nFor full details on prizing, please check out our tournament page here\n.\nIf you want these exclusive prizes, time is running out! The HEX Clash will rotate with the release of\n, so your weekends are numbered. These will be some of your last chances at the AAA Herofall cards/sleeves or the Wizard Battleboard, so make every tournament count!\nFinally, a cool wind blows from the Hyperborean Mountains. Creatures that the rest of Entrath forgot stir, drawn from their slumber by the battles raging in the arena.\nHow will you use these ancient beasts to achieve victory? Or perhaps more importantly, how will you prevent yourself from being eaten? Let us know in the forums below!\nSee you on the Battlefield~\nGot any questions? Want to chat with other players? Then discuss this article in our Forums\n! You can also follow us on Twitter and Facebook, or enjoy regular streams on our official Twitch channel\n.", "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "410380", "page": 9, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "text": "Welcome to a round up of the week! We have Battleboard rotation news,\nspoilers, a peak at the next Clash AAA, and more!\nThis week we really dove into the story behind our upcoming set,\n. On Monday we revealed that the sentient Frostheart gem is not content to be taken down by Hogarth's ritual. It's looking for a champion, and Lixil may be just what it needs. Read all about the Deathless Gem and the epic showdown that's brewing in the distance\n.\nNext, we gave you some insights into the process that goes into building an exciting fantasy world. Learn more about how we brought color into the Hyperborean Mountains and used specific cards to make Entrath come to life\n.\nFinally, we took a moment to appreciate the underdogs. For every team that takes center stage, there are the teams that must be trampled underfoot. Here are some stories from our Frostheart Failures\n. Enjoy!\nThe Frost Ring Battleboard will be rotating out of the Chark Mart next Tuesday, June 27th @ 10:00am PT. Make sure to nab it in honor of our upcoming set! This is your last chance to stay frosty, so pick it up today. It will be replaced with this hot new Jungle Battleboard:\nGet ready to add some heat to your beats and some spice to your slice. A new board's on its way!\nIf you want to reach for the stars, you only have one week left! On June 30th, 11:59 PM Pacific, our 2017 ladder season #3 will roll over. This means that if you are aiming for a spot in our upcoming Cosmic Crown Showdown\n, or if you haven't finished grabbing your ladder rewards, it's climb time!\nRemember, players who reach Cosmic will get exclusive AAA sleeves to honor their achievement. Grab yours before it's too late. Our next sleeve will be the Gallant Spearcliff you all voted for! Here it is in client\nThis weekend is your\nto nab our new Typhoon Skyshaper and Cryptcurse Knight AAs. The format this month is\n. Tournament times are as follows:\n\u00a0\nYou can learn more about our VIP program here\nor by visiting our VIP FAQ\n.\nSpeaking of tournaments, the HEX Clash\nis back once more! Sunday, starting at 8am PT (Worldclock\n), you have another chance to prove your mettle and walk away with cash and exclusive prizes! Will you end up a proud owner of these fine cosmetics like last week's winners\n?\n\u00a0\nJoin us this Sunday and find out!\nFor full details on prizing, please check out our tournament page here\n.\nIf you want these exclusive prizes, time is running out! The HEX Clash will rotate with the release of\n, so your weekends are numbered. These will be some of your last chances at the AAA Herofall cards/sleeves or the Wizard Battleboard, so make every tournament count!\nSpeaking of the HEX Clash rotation, here is a sneak peak at the AAA items that will be coming your way with\n:\n\u00a0\nThey are feeling a little shy at the moment, but each one of these are beautifully animated by our artists. If you are looking for tasty ways to jam up your opponents, we've got you covered!\nFinally,\nis going to bring a full bounty of new tools to build your decks with. You may have already seen the Ice resource cycle\nspoiled by InfamousNeo earlier in the week, but that's not all!\nis going to bring back some old favorites, like our uncommon dual-shard cycle:\nAnd it will bring some cool new surprises. Here is a rare resource that will come with our latest set:\nWhat new decks will you build with this increased flexibility? Make sure to let us know in the forums below!\nSee you on the Battlefield~\nGot any questions? Want to chat with other players? Then discuss this article in our Forums\n! You can also follow us on Twitter and Facebook, or enjoy regular streams on our official Twitch channel\n.", "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "335070", "page": 6, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "text": "We release on Friday 28th 3 new DLC packs:\n- VRC PRO Branded cars and components Deluxe\n- VRC PRO European On-road tracks Deluxe\n- VRC PRO International Oval On-road tracks Deluxe\nThese 3 new VRC Pro packs are great addititions for your VRC game. The 'Branded cars and components' pack adds 12 cars and nearly 250 branded components to your collection and gives you access to all the branded high performance cars and parts in VRC, like from Associated, Kyosho, Tamiya, Serpent, Xray, Proline, AKA, Tekin to name just a few.\nThe 'European' track pack adds 8 high speed r/c race tracks to your track collection. The best of the best European tracks. A must for the die-hard on-road racing fans. Onroad R/C tracks don't come any better than in Europe!\nThe 'International oval tracks' add 4 great high speed ovals to your track collection. These ovals are part of existing on-road tracks you may or may not already have in your track collection, like Lostallo, Osaka, Sao Paulo and Keitune. If you are a 'left-turn only' addict don't miss on this pack. VRC organizes 3 NASCAR series in 2017 which use these tracks! Get them and join the action!", "early_access": false}
