{"product_id": "410380", "page": 13, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "text": "Welcome to a round up of the week! We have client improvements, a bonus Release Weekend, and more!\nWe had our release celebration last weekend... but what about a SECOND one? We know that some of our delays impacted our international players and we want to make sure everyone gets to enjoy the full Release Weekend experience. That's why we decided to open up one more weekend of Release Weekend format fun. Starting\n, you can once again compete for exclusive alternate arts in our special Release Weekend formats. The event will follow the details laid out in our first Release Weekend Announcement\n.\nThis\nonly format will close on\n. Enjoy!\n\u00a0\nOur engineering team has been hard at work improving the stability of our client and ensuring that everything is in tip-top shape. You can see patch notes\nfor a fix we implemented earlier this week. Here is another round of improvements:\nWe are committed to providing the best digital TCG experience out there and will continue to improve the client wherever we can. See you on the battlefield!\nOur Cosmic Crown showdown is this weekend starting Saturday at 9am PT (Worldclock\n)! Our top ranking players\nfrom the season will compete for their share of prizes, glory, and $5,000! We can't wait to see what brews some of our best players are putting together. Good luck and have fun to all our qualifiers!\nGot any questions? Want to chat with other players? Then discuss this article in our Forums\n! You can also follow us on Twitter and Facebook, or enjoy regular streams on our official Twitch channel\n.", "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "410380", "page": 13, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "text": "Welcome to a round up of the week! We have another patch, tournament updates, and more!\nOur engineers can't stop won't stop bringing you awesome updates and fixes. You can check out the patchnotes from our latest round right now\n.\nThis is another quick reminder that our Forest battleboard will soon be rotating out of the Chark Mart soon! If you haven't picked it up already, you have until Monday, March 27th @ 10:00am PT when the brand-new Canyon board will take it's place:\nIf you want a cool forest shade to slay your opponents under, don't delay. A new board's on its way!\nThe HexPrimal Immortal Championship Series\nis only 3 weeks away! Make sure you are jumping into the HEX Primal Immortal Queue to get your 20 tickets to qualify.\nThis tournament has some pretty great prizes, including:\n*Contains 1 copy of all cards of a set chosen by HexPrimal.com\nProve your mettle and have your name ring out today!\nThe Arcanum Vault is opening it's doors once more. Check out the FiveShards announcement\nfor some fan-lore and details on how to pick up this wicked alternate art:\nBattle it out for prizes and glory, all for free!\nThis is your chance to nab some Lazgar's Vengeance and Ripple of Janai'ngo AAs. The format this month is\n. Tournament times are as follows:\n\u00a0\nYou can learn more about our VIP program here\n. We know, there's just so much to do in HEX right now! It can be hard to keep track. Here is a quick recap of all our upcoming events:\nYou can always check out the latest schedule by visiting our forum calendar\nor upcoming events list\nas well.\nDo giant death mechs make you all tingly? Well, you're in luck! Our friends at Cryptozoic have partnered with WETA Workshop to bring you an epic smackdown in the megapocalypse.\nIf you enjoy tactical boardgames and wicked miniatures, head on down to WETA Workshop's Kickstarter and give it a gander. It's pretty awesome!\nGot any questions? Want to chat with other players? Then discuss this article in our Forums\n! You can also follow us on Twitter and Facebook, or enjoy regular streams on our official Twitch channel\n.", "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "410380", "page": 13, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "text": "Welcome to a round up of the week! We have game updates, a new AAA card, and the start of our HEX Clash:\nAnother day, another opportunity to make HEX even better! Here\nare the latest round of fixes. Most notably, our Art team has stepped things up a notch\u2014The Herofall AA is now a AAA card\n!\nWe also had Corey Burkhart join us for some quick comments about the HEX Ladder. You can read all about it here\n.\nWe are extremely excited to announce the start of our weekly 1K tournament series! The HEX Clash will begin this Sunday,\n, and continue\nstarting at 8am Pacific\n. Top placing players will receive a cut of the $1000 pool as well as a rotating selection of Sleeves, Alternate Arts, and Battleboards that will change with each set release. For example, with\n, these lovelies will be up for grabs:\n\u00a0\nGorgeous, right?\nFor full details on prizing, please check out our tournament page here\n.\nNero Jinous, one of our official channel streamers, has offered to share his Clash journey with everyone! Be sure to tune in\nabout 15 minutes before the Clash starts for some pre-game hype! He will be doing HEX-themed games and some limited exercises between rounds, so it should be a party.\nSee you all on the battlefield this Sunday!\nGot any questions? Want to chat with other players? Then discuss this article in our Forums\n! You can also follow us on Twitter and Facebook, or enjoy regular streams on our official Twitch channel\n.", "early_access": false}
