{"product_id": "734580", "page": 19, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-11", "text": "When I first saw this game I thought it is some crappy game made by some crappy developers\nAfter just\nof playing I already knew pretty much everything about the game.\nAfter just\nhour I really started liking the game and thinking it is really fun.\nAfter just\nhours I already bought 3 DLC's to support the developers.\nThis game is awesome and has a very big potential, it's only been out for a few days but I can already tell that the developers are awesome guys, they listen to the community, when someone reports a bug it is immediately fixed.\nI also love that you don't have to be a high level or have a lot of DLC's to be \"good\".\nThe stock weapons are godlikely, I love them, I prefer them over any machine guns.\nI also love that you can get anything for free, all of the weapons are spawnable and not so hard to find, the airdrops are also godlike including ton of weapons, ammunition and materials.\nThe only thing that I would consider *Pay To Win* is the Tank DLC.\nYou get the best tanks in the game which are far superior to the non \"Pay To Win\" tanks.\nBut to be honest they also cost much more resources to make so it isn't really that big of a deal, also they are pretty easy to destroy, just find a bazooka or panzerschreck and boom.\nYou could also destroy them with AT-grenades or AT-mines which are easy to find and craft.\nI highly recommend this game to anyone that is interested in WW2, tanks, weapons or just anything with shooting.", "hours": 23.6, "username": "Kozarsson", "products": 22, "early_access": true}
{"product_id": "734580", "page": 19, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-11", "text": "Pretty sure the first people who downloaded this, myself among them, thought it'd be your standard garbage free-to-play with stolen assets.. Well, it's not, it's actually really fun, and has a TON of potential (although I swear the animations are ripped from Call of Duty: World at War, but that's fine I guess?). Some are claiming it's \"pay to win\", but I don't really classify that 'cuz the paid for content literally costs less than 3 bucks, the most expensive bought content right now is 1.59, you can literally get that much by selling a few trading cards in your steam inventory.", "hours": 46.5, "username": "Sensei-tional", "products": 130, "early_access": true}
