{"product_id": "734580", "page": 19, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-10", "text": "Well, well, well.  Foxhole and Hero's and Generals had offspring...BUT! Game is fun, it's NOT paytowin, which if anyone understands how much work goes into making games like Battlerush, then will understand its a GEM. Besides, all the DLCs COMBINED add up to $10, which you still have to gather resources so it is not a autowin button.\nI think the Dev is trying to combine all the things that we love about modern combat titles, thats not featured in a single title.\nHere we go; It has base building, but its not OVERwhelming like foxhole(foxhole is TOO MUCH behind the scences boring\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665logistics).  It has good ole Allied vs Axis(The japs are coming in an addon I'd bet) this is a plus, i hated the fake factions in Foxhole.  Combat is good, standard stuff. Hopefully the Devs have played squad and try and emulate the sound of that game, which IMHO puts it in a class all its own.  Devs, you are headed in a good direction with the art, I would aim towards gritty cartoon and away from the cartoon battlefield I played when I first got steam in 2008.  Cartoony graphics means that you can still play with friends on all spectrums of machines, ie cartoony is less hard on your hardware, but do NOT take it anymore that direction please devs.\nDEVS please stear towards gritty artwork(think hardcore GIJOE punk), keep the DLCs cheap, promote Squad persistance, stats, league play, somesort of ingame currency rewards for winning, its needs an EGO hook - like in depth - player ranking through a highly detailed scoreboard.  In game currency like WorldofTanks(clanwars, {biggest EGO hook ever}), this game has some SERIOUS potential.  I love the fact it is NOT grindy like HERO's and Generals, although the persistance of Hero's is fantastic.\nThings that would be cool:\nAI squad control with the ability to control and outfit individual squad members(like that free co-op alien shooter).  Squad members have learning AI and will learn how you play and have adaptive qualities.  Adaptive AI is less code with more variance in game play, DEVS need to focus on smart bots so game still plays well with the occasional low population.\nCool REALISTIC sound, with realistic ballistics and realistic pentration(play SQUAD for a weekend) the sound is amazing and really puts you IN the WAR.\nBetter Persistance, like Hero's and Foxhole, needs EGO hooks.\nOFF to buy all the DLCs, spread the word troops - if the DEVs listen to playerbase, then have a diamond here!", "hours": 12.3, "user_id": "76561197981716582", "username": "LavaJava", "products": 215, "early_access": true}
