{"product_id": "410380", "page": 14, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "text": "Welcome to a round up of the week! It has been a hurricane of news, including publishing changes, new tournaments, developer updates and more! Let's brave the storm and see what is new in the world of Entrath:\nOn Tuesday, Cory Jones addressed the community with a big change - HEX Entertainment is taking over the publishing of HEX\n! You can read more about it in his own words\n. You can also view a recording of his live Q&A session on twitch\n.\nWe are introducing the HEX Clash, a weekly 1K sealed tournament in which players can compete for cash and cool cosmetic prizes! This tournament will be held every Sunday starting at 8am Pacific. Read on for full details\n.\nSpeaking of cosmetics, we announced a bunch of new ways to bling out your battles. The full details live here\n, but this announcement includes a collectors deck with our first ever AAA card (Animated Alternate Art), as well as customizable battleboards and the introduction of the Chark Mart section of our store.\nIs good deal! We can't wait to see those fancy new cards, sleeves, and boards in-game.\nOur transition patch happened this Wednesday. It went pretty smoothly, but we know a few players have had issues after the patch. If that's you, please make sure you go to the Transition FAQ thread\non our forums. We are collecting answers to common questions there. If you have a problem not covered by the FAQ, please make sure to post on our forums\nor contact our support\n.\nA hero fell, but the battle rages on\u2014our sixth set arrives on February 28th!\nintroduces over 275 cards and several new mechanics to triumph with. Diligently Conscript your troops and Mobilize your forces to victory with brand new tactics. Can you (and Entrath) escape the\nunscathed?\nSharpen your swords and your wits to find out next Tuesday! We\u2019ll see you on the battlefield.\nOur designers have been hard at work making sure\nis the best experience offer. In this article\n, they discuss changes to two spoiled cards as well as a few tweaks to existing champions.\nOur Ardor Day\ncelebration starts today! Play campaign for exclusive PvE cards and equipment. Play tournaments for exclusive AA cards. Dodge Pucid's arrows and try not to get lovestruck. Happy Ardor Day!\nAlso, our VIP event is this weekend! It is your chance to nab some Lazgar's Vengeance and Ripple of Janai'ngo AAs. The format this month is\n. Tournament times are as follows:\n\nWe also have another Legendary spoiler to close out the week:\nThis creepy crawly weaves a truly tangled web. Whenever you bring another troop over to the Underworld (through Conscription), he gets +1/+1. Not only that, but you get\ntroops for the price of one. With so many threats assailing them from each side, this is sure to leave your opponent tied up in knots. How do you plan to use the Webspeaker? Let us know in the forums below!\nGot any questions? Want to chat with other players? Then discuss this article in our Forums\n! You can also follow us on Twitter and Facebook, or enjoy regular streams on our official Twitch channel\n.", "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "410380", "page": 14, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "text": "Welcome to a round up of the week! We released our Scars of War patch, started a brand-new ladder season, and are gearing up for the next Cosmic Crown Showdown:\nreleased this Tuesday! We added over 275 new cards, 4 new champions, and all new strategies to succeed in both PvP and campaign. Join us as we celebrate our 6th set this weekend. Starting March 3rd, you can compete for exclusive alternate arts in our special Release Weekend formats\n.\nConscript a friend and play today!\nSpeaking of events, our second ladder season started on March 1st. Everything is fresh and you are ready to climb anew! Compete for cosmetics, packs, and gold\u2014not to mention that animated sleeve for those who make it all the way up to cosmic.\nRead more here\n.\nHey all, Corey Burkhart here to discuss an issue with the Ladder results for Season 1 of 2017. As a part of the transfer from the Gameforge servers to the HEX Entertainment servers, there were some issues reporting the standings and results of the ladder.\nThe issue spawned during the server transfer. If a player played a game before verifying their Keep Name (in-game name) on the new HEX entertainment servers, their rating was saved to the false name that the servers used to protect the privacy of these players. Then, when their new name was re-established, the database pulled a rating at random to associate with the player. Thus, some players saw that their in-game rating was much lower than they anticipated.\nWith some effort, we were able to backtrack over the last week and correct for the ratings that were off. With this data, we were able to solve which players should have ended in Cosmic at the end of the season in both the limited and constructed ladders. This issue has been solved in the database now, and players don\u2019t need to worry about the current 2017 Ladder Season 2 data being collected.\nThe final corrected standings can be seen here\n.\nTo those players not on these leaderboards\u2014but who were shown on the leaderboards in client at the end of 2017 Season 1\u2014you will also be qualified for the upcoming Cosmic Crown Showdown. We determined that it would be unfair to these players who believed that they had earned a spot in the CCS to exclude them from the event. These players\u2019 names are posted below each list for which they qualified.\nWe apologize for the issues. These have been corrected going forward. Congratulations once again to the winners and good luck next weekend in the Cosmic Crown Showdown!\n~Corey Burkhart\nGot any questions? Want to chat with other players? Then discuss this article in our Forums\n! You can also follow us on Twitter and Facebook, or enjoy regular streams on our official Twitch channel\n.", "early_access": false}
