{"product_id": "410380", "page": 15, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "text": "You wake face down in the muck. It is hard to breathe. Blood and earth conspire to trap you in their clammy embrace, but despite the burning agony in your side and the dwindling strength in your limbs you manage to flip yourself onto your side. The rust colored sky matches the stained field below, like the heavens themselves bled too.\nThe battlefield is still, save for the terrible squawking of hungry crows, but you can\u2019t stop hearing the cries of the fallen in your mind. So many gone. Tears trickle down your face, but whether they are for Prince Talysen or yourself you do not know. Everything smells like copper.\nSuddenly, you hear a rustling and the flap of hundreds of angry wings disturbed from their meal. A bony hand grips your shoulder and flips you onto your back. You recoil, your already shallow breath catching in your throat as you catch the glint of Diamonds where eyes should be. Something glimmers in those depths, and your skin crawls with the sensation that the stones are\nyou. With as much bile and hatred as you can muster, you choke out one word, \u201cNecrotic.\u201d\nMadam Anana stares down at you, head cocked to the side as if she were listening to something. Her feathered collar and tattered cloak are somehow spotless, as if she were somehow standing above the carnage all around her. For a moment, there was silence. Then Anana spoke, her words echoing slightly as if a dozen voices lived within, all clamoring to get out.\u201cWe knew the shin\u2019hare were up to something when they gave us your prince. Bloodshed. Chaos. War.\u201d\nHer face twists slightly as she looks down at you, her eyes burning like twin stars in the face of a disapproving grandmother.\u201cBut war was an acceptable price to pay, Sleeper. What were you thinking, burning your dead? Foolish. Selfish.\n.\u201d\nWith each word her voice grows louder, hands clenched and trembling at her sides. \u201cYou are like children, breaking your toys because you do not want to share. All that knowledge, all those Orphaned shards without a home because of your stubborn pride. We need your shells, Sleeper. If you will not gift them to us after you are done with them, we have no choice. We will take them by force.\u201d\nA crow lands on her staff, breaking her tirade. She looks up at the human finger clutched in its beak, and then out at the blood-soaked battlefield.\u201cThis was not my first choice,\u201d she whispers. \u201cBut even if these scars go deeper than we intended, we will fulfill our purpose.\u201d\nHer eyes flash as her thin hands go to a pouch at her waist.You feel your vision dim as Anana leans over you, her dry breath in your ear.\u201cShh\u2026 sleep, young one. Soon you too will hear the Chant. Awaken, and this will all be like a bad dream.\n*********\nIt\u2019s a new year and a new expansion! We are pleased to announce that our Sixth Set is titled\n.\nWith\n, HEX\u2019s story focuses on the raging war which started in\nand has been shaping the face of Entrath itself. Alliances form and break as the Ardent and Underworld struggle to gain the upper hand, but nobody will escape unscathed.\nThat\u2019s all for now! Don\u2019t forget to keep an eye out here and on social media as we kick off this exciting release.", "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "410380", "page": 15, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "text": "Welcome to a round up of the week! We have champions, cards, lore and more!\n\u00a0\nOn Monday, Corey Burkhart covered what new champions you can expect to throw down with in\n. As each faction begins to work more closely together, everyone will have to pick a side. Are you Ardent or Underworld? These champions will reward you greatly for your allegiance. Will these new heroes be your greatest allies or your most fearsome foes? Read on for details\n! \u00a0\nAs war consumes Entrath, a hopeful fate unfolds. Under the watchful gaze of the Hex comet, a small band ventures ever deeper into the Feralroot. Last Wednesday, the lore team shared an intriguing short story and several exciting new cards. The full text is available here\n.\u00a0\nWith\n, our first two sets\u2014\nand\n\u2014are rotating out. We want every account that starts out to have decks which are legal in Standard play. For this reason, we will be granting the following 50 new cards to all accounts.\n2 Ardent Decree\n3 Ashwood Firebrand\n3 Blazing Hammer\n1 Brightmoon Brave\n3 Canyon Howler\n3 Dread Botonist\n3 Fiend of Nulzann\n3 Goliath Spiderspawn\n3 Gust Mage\n3 Horned Giraffe\n3 Livid Buffalo\n3 Patrol Bot\n3 Sapper\u2019s Wallbuster\n3 Siegesaurus\n3 Skittering Dark\n3 Tanker Trunk\n2 Underworld Decree\n3 Wakizashi Warbunny\nThese cards will be used to create two new Standard Legal decks and will be granted to everyone, old and new accounts alike.\u00a0\nI've gotten word by carrier pigeon that the mercenary we glimpsed briefly in the sky is too rare and shy to stay for long. Where\nhis natural habitat? Perhaps Lord Bernard P. Dunthorpe knows. In the meantime, let's turn our gaze downward to something earthier.\nThis epic orc caries a piece of the Mountain God himself. Give it up for Thulgrund!So, how would you rock out with this mercenary? Let us know in the forums below.\nGot any questions? Want to chat with other players? Then discuss this article in our Forums\n! You can also follow us on Twitter and Facebook, or enjoy regular streams on our official Twitch channel\n.", "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "410380", "page": 15, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "text": "Hello HEX players!!! We have some very exciting news about HEX\u2014we have begun self-publishing!\nI know this was already stated in the general press release\n, but I want to repeat: This will NOT change the core elements of HEX.\nThere will be some minor tech elements to the transition, as is expected. We will have new billing arrangements, there will be a small downtime as we make the actual transition, and there may be a few other slight adjustments. But, overall, it should feel relatively seamless and nothing in your actual collection is in danger of changing or being lost.\nMost importantly, I am (as I have always been) in control of the game and its direction. You can continue to be sure the well-being of HEX and the happiness of its players is our number one priority.\nI want to take this opportunity to thank Gameforge for all of their tremendous support. We literally wouldn\u2019t have gotten here without them, and they deserve all of our thanks (they certainly have mine).\nLet me make it clear that HEX is healthy, and we are carefully managing our resources to maximize our success. Running the game intelligently will allow us, with your support, to continue indefinitely. Not many people know this\u2014and I haven\u2019t really made it public\u2014but to date HEX has had over $25 million spent on development. Yes, $25 MILLION! I know, it\u2019s crazy, and I certainly had no idea when I started out that making a game like HEX would be so unbelievably expensive. As it turns out, one of the reasons there are no other great fully-featured digital TCGs out there is because it\u2019s INCREDIBLY difficult and costly.\nBut here we are! With a great game, an amazing engine, and the best community possible. So, let me assure you our continued focus will be on adding new features (we have a long list) and developing amazing card sets. Luckily, we are in the best possible position to make that happen.\nOne of the things I declared when HEX started is that we would only sell packs and decks but, as time rolled on (over three years now), it has become clear that this may not have been the best decision. We regularly see players asking for fun cosmetic additions to the game. We want to add them too. In the past, we've used these items to reward gameplay, but now we want to provide the opportunity for you to buy some of them as well.\nTo be clear, I am only talking about cosmetic items\u2026 and this will help us achieve our goal to increase revenue so that we can continue to improve the HEX experience. As the publisher, we need to carefully manage the day-to-day business and, of course, part of that is watching the bottom line. However, I still want to increase the amount of money we SPEND to make the game better, and increase the number of prized tournaments. To do this, we need to ensure HEX is generating enough revenue to make these great tournaments possible. I would call this an experiment and, if it doesn\u2019t work or players hate it, we can discontinue the practice. One of the things I love most about HEX is the chance to chase crazy ideas, and I don\u2019t think that is going to stop anytime soon.\nSo what are some of the things we are going to try?\nWell, first off, we are starting the HEX CLASH\n, a weekly limited format tournament with $1000 in cash prizes and some pretty insane in-game rewards! Trust me when I say the cash will be secondary when you see the in-game stuff. One fun thing we are doing is giving fantastic prizes to lucky tournament players as a participation prize each week!\nNext, we have created a COLLECTOR\u2019S DECK, which will be a very special pre-constructed deck that features several alternate arts, our first ever AAA card (Animated Alternate Art), AND an animated sleeve. It should be very, uh\u2026 collectible!\nWe are also adding the \u201cCHARK MART,\u201d a new tab in the store that will sell all kinds of fun stuff. The first big addition is collectible Battle Boards. To begin with, it will be one board a month (available for a very limited time), featuring each of the boards we have created for the PVE campaign.\nThere will also be more items for gold as we look for interesting new sinks. We have the Kismet\u2019s Reserve pack that features a number of in-game items, each built around a specific theme. The first is focused on the Silver Talon and includes a mercenary, alternate art PVP card, a sleeve, and PVE cards/equipment.\nDino has been kind enough to do a more in-depth write-up of all these plans and has posted it here\n. We will also be doing a Q&A stream on the official HEX channel\nstarting at 4pm PT (Worldclock\n). Please leave your questions in this HEX Reddit thread for consideration.\nOverall, I am VERY happy to be publishing HEX. We have some very big plans moving forward and, as HEX continues to grow (the game has gradually grown EVERY month), we will have some great opportunities to be bigger and better than ever. I want to thank you for continuing to support HEX. We love your passion and know that without you we wouldn\u2019t have the chance to spend every day making the game we always dreamed of.\nCory Jones, CEO\nGot any questions? Want to chat with other players? Then discuss this article in our Forums\n! You can also follow us on Twitter and Facebook, or enjoy regular streams on our official Twitch channel\n.", "early_access": false}
