{"product_id": "609150", "page": 14, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-04", "text": "great game and story complaints\nmy only complaints\na couple of game crashes(this seems to have stopped)\nweird black boxes appearing that occur occasionally during the manuever to go around enemies(haven't seen them in a while)\nan inability to select which enemy to personally target along with a couple of camera control glitches(really bad later in the game(you need quick selective targetting not cycling))\nframerate issue\nLater in the game with some of the later companions (if the use there special moves (like 3 characters)) the frame rate would drop from a solid 60 to 15-20 range. I am not sure if  its an optimization problem or if my laptop is not strong enough.\nYeah No\nGame becomes a slog once you get to the phantom nights\nEnemies Boosted to an obscene measure that everything is an insta-kill even for the tank(and that is for a single enemy). You then have enemies piled on top of you with no effetive way to survive except buy using tons of resurrection units to revive you entire party only for you to have your party intsa-killed(this is with grinding and best equipement you can get). This is not even the end of the game or even a boss fight. This is something thrown at you halfway through the game that probably requires you to be at least Level 50 for every party member to survive. There is no way I am spending 15 hours of grinding to have a chance of beating even a single group of enemies.", "hours": 25.2, "user_id": "76561198267935648", "username": "Azamos", "products": 17, "early_access": false}
