{"product_id": "609150", "page": 14, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-04", "text": "One of the few good games that exist in the vast library steam boasts.\nIf you want to know about this game fast... i made that easy for you.\nPROS:\n-Top Tier Visuals, 4k resolution and high Frame rate thanks to glourious remaster\n-Very engaging Action-RPG gameplay that requires both character managment/preparation and more importantly, Skill.\n-Colorful wide cast of heroes and characters\n-nearly 80+ hours of content, and maybe even 20+ more hours if you are a trophy nutcase\n-Motoi Sakuraba composed all the music\n-JRPG Futuristic setting of traveling and backtracking to planets.\n- immensely deep and extensive crafting system.\n-Fully Voice acted in English for normal people, and Japanese voice for silly weeabos who have a brain disorder.\n-No Ingame changable difficulty. GIT GUD. (If you want harder difficulties, you must unlock them <3)\n-\nCONS\n-No hidden characters, this is strange to have for a star ocean as all the prior ones had different characters to recruit\n-Lymle is annoying.\n-Will be very difficult to play the game, as you will spend alot of time looking at Reimi and Myuria with inappropriate intent.\nno real issues or cons with the game...unless you just hate the story or really hate JRPGS. granted this is steam, alot of people hate jrpgs but i think its worth a shot if you are capable of subdueing your negative bias.\nits a far superior game to the mass effect series in terms of polish and design.", "hours": 11.2, "user_id": "76561198074826647", "username": "Sir Millian", "products": 60, "early_access": false}
