{"product_id": "410380", "page": 17, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "text": "Greetings everyone! Many of you have been furiously playing our Chapter II update already, so we won't keep you for long. After all, those ships won't sink themselves! Today we'd like to cover our Alachian Sea patch, the Platinum Plunder, and our New Website.\nWe are incredibly pleased to announce that our Chronicles of Entrath: Chapter II\npatch went live Tuesday without a hitch. This has been one of our largest content releases to date, and we have added a\nof new content for you to explore! Brave the high seas, explore interactive dungeons, overcome crazy encounters and more! Not to mention, we have added over 200 new equips, 90 PvE cards, introduced the mercenary system and a whole new class for you to play with. Set sail, scallywags - adventure awaits!\nTrailer\nAnd if that's not enough to make you yearn for open waters, make sure to check out our new trailer above. Our teams have worked really hard to bring you this epic introduction to our second chapter. If you have even a touch of a pirate in you, that video should have you singing sea shanties straight away.\nSpeaking of shipwrecks and pirates, our Platinum Plunder tournament\nis coming up soon! Starting December 17th, make sure to join us for a massive, free tournament with several hundred thousand in platinum up for grabs! Additionally, the top 256 players will receive the Salty Sam mercenary (shown below).\nSave the date and begin brewing today!\nYou may have noticed that we are transitioning to a brand-new website. This is a big change, but it comes with some pretty sweet improvements.\nFirst, we have a brand-new slider for our top news stories. If something important is going down in the world of Entrath, we want you to know about it. With major articles pinned right at the top of the page, it is now easier than ever to stay informed!\nSecond, we know that you don't all read our news feed every day. Sometimes you miss an article or a deck write-up by one of your favorite community authors. With our previous website, once something fell off the front page it could be difficult to find it again. Not any more! We now have both a search function and a tagging system to make navigating our archives an easy and pleasant experience.\nThird, we have added a new \"What is HEX?\" video which can be found under 'the game\n' menu on our website. If you have some friends who are thinking of getting into HEX, we now have a short, accessible introduction they can watch to see what kinds of things our game has to offer.\nWhat is HEX Video?\nPlease note that this is just the beginning! We are still adding features to our new website and tweaking its look. While we are in our transitional period, some older articles may be down until we can get them into our archive properly. Thank you for your understanding!\nFinally, we posted full details regarding our Season 3 Cosmic Crown Showdown\n. In this tournament, the top 64 from each ladder will compete for their share of a $5,000 prize pool. There is less than a month left before the end of Season 3, so start climbing today!", "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "410380", "page": 17, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "text": "We are excited to announce the details of our Season 3 Cosmic Crown Showdown! In this event, the best ladder players of the season will duke it out for glory, prizes, and a pool of $5,000 cash from the comfort of their own homes! Here's how it works:\nThe\non each Ladder (constructed and limited) at the end of this season will get a ladder ticket that allows them to participate in this season's Cosmic Crown Showdown. The showdown is broken up into two Stages which will take place on\nand\n. The tournament will be held in-client under the \"Special\" tab of the tournament screen.\nJanuary 7th, starting at 9am PT (Worldclock\n), we will have a Constructed Swiss tournament (with best 2-out-of-3 matches) for qualifying ladder players. The\nfrom this Stage will move on to Stage 2.\nJanuary 8th, starting at 9am PT (Worldclock\n), we will have a Single-Elimination Draft tournament (with best 2-out-of-3 matches). The winner of Stage 2 will walk away with exclusive cosmetics and the lion's share of the prize pool.\nNote that we keep the 9th and 10th placed players from the Swiss tournament on Day 1 as standbys for the Single Elimination portion of the Cosmic Crown Showdown on Day 2. Should one or more of the finalists fail to show up for Stage 2, the 9th placed player will have a chance to join (2 minute response limit), before the 10th placed player will have a chance to do so (2 minute response limit). After this, the tournament will commence, even if there are fewer than 8 players present to avoid long wait times for the finalists.\nPlayers who qualified for the final stage but don\u2019t show up will be rewarded with the in-game rewards corresponding to the 9th place of Day 1.\nFull Terms and Conditions will be available here shortly.\nWill you be the next to wear the Cosmic Crown? Start climbing and find out! Best of luck on the battlefield!", "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "410380", "page": 17, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "text": "On 14/12/2016 the servers will be undergoing maintenance, during which time we'll be installing a new bugfix patch. The patchnotes will be avaliable when the server goes offline (14th December, 10AM CET)\nThings start at 8:30 AM (CET), when we'll close registrations for new tournaments. Then at 10 AM (CET) we'll take the servers offline. If everything runs according to plan, the servers will reopen their gates to you again at 16:00 PM (CET).\nNote: Occasionally, while giving our servers a once over, we discover a spider egg in the deck or catch a shroomkin chewing on one of the cables \u2013 when that happens, it sometimes takes a little longer before everything is back online.\nThanks for your patience and understanding!\n08:30 CET (9pm PDT) \u2013 Tournament servers lock\n10:00 CET (1am PDT) \u2013 Servers offline\n16:00 CET (7.00am PDT) \u2013 Expected end to maintenance", "early_access": false}
