{"product_id": "378860", "page": 6, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2018-01-06", "text": "This is my first review, so here it goes.\nI am a huge motorsports fan, and I love racing games. I enjoyed the first PCars, and I love how much is offered in PCars 2. But, it does have its issues. Here are my thoughts:\nPros:\n-Graphically, its gorgeous.\n- Racing can be fun.\n- Variety of divisions.\n- Large variety of tracks.\n- Dynamic weather.\n- Car list is amazing.\n- Sounds are fantastic.\n- Finally fixed the controller, you can actually race with a controller. I use a G29 wheel mostly.\nCons:\nNow, for the cons section I feel like writing is best. The game still has glitches, many really. The cars can easily be destroyed, Indycar the most. But for me, the biggest issues is the AI's consistency. Now, I know having AI trust right if difficult in racing games, but the challenge slider from 10% to 110% is way off. In some series, 70% is too difficult and in others 90% is too easy. At 75%, the AI in the Indycar series is like a bunch of 10 year olds driving blind, and at 90% the cars are a challenge, but forget you're there. That is another thing, no matter what series or aggression level you place the AI, they don't seem to understand that you are under them or above, they will simply turn in and sometimes this crashes you; and with some glitches it can be so annoying.\nOverall, I like this game, I don't love it. My rating would be 7.5/10. F12017 is fantastic, iRacing is still amazing and even rFactor 2 is a great choice for it's price. Do I think that PCars is worth a full price of $50.00 to $79.00, my answer is no. I would place PCars around the $29 or $39 price point.", "hours": 24.2, "user_id": "76561198132540997", "username": "LJLIVE88", "products": 47, "early_access": false}
