{"product_id": "234820", "page": 10, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-05-19", "text": "Comes in handy when you're particularly lazy about updating your drivers. Scan/Fix is always a good win button for any computer. For that reason, its a really good program if you just want to keep your system up to date.\nCaveat:\nHave to say, though, requiring a persistent internet connection in order to operate premium features is really counter-intuitive to its own functionality. If Driver Fusion already collected and backed up all drivers to your local HDD, it really shouldnt nanny you by refusing to restore them because the internet tollbooth is out of operation. You paid for the files to be stored locally, so they should be able to be executed locally without the extra step. (360 XBLA flashbacks...)\nAfter a clean OS install on a recently formatted HDD, you may find yourself asking \"Driver Fusion refuses to install the Ethernet drivers it backed up for me because I have no Ethernet drivers installed?\"  Thats like going to the DMV because you lost your licence and them refusing to give you a new licence because you dont have your old licence.\nI like what you did, Treexy, but please stop locking premium features behind Ethernet walls. You're better than that.\n*Updated with dev response. (Much appreciated)\nTreexy  [developer] Posted: May 20 @ 3:45am\nWe understand your concern. Internet access is required because many features rely on our online service; features that simply cannot work without it. If you end up reinstalling Windows where a network driver is not installed by default, you can install a backup you've made with Driver Fusion through Windows's device manager (Install from disk) and then use Driver Fusion to install the rest automatically. We have some idea's of preparing some sort of offline mass-installer for Windows reinstalls but this is still in very early stages.", "hours": 18.0, "user_id": "76561198035392694", "username": "BjaOckX", "products": 495, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "410380", "page": 24, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "text": "Our latest tournament let\u2019s everyone become a salty swashbuckler and pillage the platinum from our purses! Are you ready for the Platinum Plunder?\nWhat makes the Platinum Plunder tournament stand apart? This tournament pays out some unique items and fills the pockets of the top 8 players with heaps of platinum. Here\u2019s how it works:\nAnyone can enter and the event has no entry fee! Just show up on December 17th for Day 1 of this exciting event with your best constructed deck and prepare to send your opponents to the Kraken\u2019s depths. The Platinum Plunder is broken up into two Stages which take place on Saturday, December 17th and Sunday, December 18th. The tournament will be held in-client under the \u201cSpecial\u201d tab of the tournament screen.\nDecember 17th, starting at 9:00am PT (Worldclock\n), we will have a Constructed Swiss tournament (with best 2-out-of-3 matches) for everyone. The\nfrom this Stage will move on to Stage 2.\nDecember 18th, starting at 9:00am PT (Worldclock\n), we will have a Single-Elimination Constructed tournament (with best 2-out-of-3 matches) for the top 8 players from day1.\nDo you have what it takes to scuttle the competition? We\u2019ll find out this December!", "early_access": false}
