{"product_id": "609150", "page": 15, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-03", "text": "This is by no means a great game.  It's a decent game that has a weak story, kind of weak character roster, some excessively long bits between save points...\nHowever, it's enjoyable.  Combat is fun, if you get familiar with it.  You can just mash x to win in the beginning, but a lot of fights (including mook encounters) will make that brain dead strategy hard to progress with.  I've beaten it once on PC now, and twice on 2 different difficulties on PS3.  It was an great deal of fun playing it again, so long after last touching it on my PS3.\nThis is the 4th game in the mainline Star Ocean game, but is a prequel.  You don't need to have played the previous games to understand what is going on, but it can help with references to previous games as well as staples of the series as a whole.\nPerformance wise - it's a pretty damn good port.  I'm running on slightly below spec hardware and getting really good framerates.  It doesn't have a litany of options to modify performance and display settings, but even on the lowest detail the game still looks decent enough as to not be distracting.\nControl-wise,, you'll probably want to use a controller versus keyboard and mouse.  The camera is a little dumb at times, overworld and in combat, and there is no pause during cutscenes (unless I an somehow mistaken, since I could not find a way to do so).\nI played this on PS3 when it came out and thoroughly enjoyed it.  This is basically that version with better textures (dual audio is a nice thing to have, sometimes).  Really, the enjoyable bits in terms of challenge aren't unlocked until after you beat the game the first time.  A series of dungeons are available after that, as well as the ability to replay the game at a higher difficulty.  While I'm not entirely the biggest fan of rebuilding my party from scratch to play anew at a new difficulty, having the option is a good thing.\nCrafting is great, though for some progression may be slow.  You need specific characters to join before you can craft certain types of items.  You don't get the most useful, Synthesis, until pretty much the end of the game.  Once that unlocks, it makes the game significantly easier if you know what you are doing with that skill.\nMany have reported issues launching this game (ASKA error).  I didn't have this problem until I tried to install a new USB device.  Once I unplugged it and rebooted, the game ran fine for me.  Keep that in mind that some people can't even run the game after buying it.  Hopefully these problems get fixed by SE in due time.\nHopefully this rambling is somehow informative.  Don't go in to this game expecting a masterpiece; that's not what this game is.  Like most Star Ocean games, it's a flawed experience propped up by a good combat system and some interesting character moments and a not too great story.  Considering the launch price of this game, it's pretty easy sell for me.", "hours": 89.5, "user_id": "76561197990872766", "username": "Loser_Slade", "products": 160, "early_access": false}
