{"product_id": "609150", "page": 15, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-03", "text": "I played Star Ocean The Last Hope on Xbox 360 and wish I had waited till the PS3 release as it had the more anime style option and JP voice acting I believe. This offers the choice between classic (anime style) and modern (the weird CGI I experienced on X360) as well as English or Japanese voices / subtitles. You can always go back to the settings and switch between these options when you first load up the game.\nI liked Star Ocean 1,2 and 3 better than this game initially honestly and possibly the 5th game as well. Edge and some of the characters irk me later on in The Last Hope. But I love the Star Ocean series and fully support it and I am glad Steam has brought this title to PC. I've enjoyed playing so far though I will need to update my Graphics card (game lags for a few seconds when switching scenes is my main complaint so far but its not a deal breaker imo).", "hours": 2.2, "user_id": "76561198001004656", "username": "Xenolicious", "products": 49, "early_access": false}
