{"product_id": "410380", "page": 27, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "text": "As cold winds blow across the Dreamsmoke Prairie and leaves turn in the Sutherlands, young from all over Entrath gather around their campfires to tell stories. You see, the veil is closer on this night of nights and the spirits of the dead roam freely. Some believe that the only way to stay safe is to make a maze of your words, to trap the spirits until the sun rises again and they can be laid to rest once more.\nSo coyotle and shin\u2019hare pups shiver, only in part from the cold, as they swap stories of the deep and dark. One of the tales they tell is that of Stingy Jack.\nSome say he is a harvest spirit driven mad by the unholy energies of zombies as they tromped through a pumpkin patch. Others say he is the result of the primal of greed, Marbaras, whose sickly energies pooled too heavy on the land.\nHis origins a mystery, his arrival is oft heralded by thin voices raising in chorus as children all across Entrath chant these words:\nDuring the haunted nights in Entrath, you will receive the treat of the Stingy Jack Sleeve, just for being brave enough to roam the streets in the dark. (Simply log in and you will automatically receive the sleeve!)\nAs the other half of the saying goes, a well-played trick deserves its own rewards. Show off your plays \u2013 and tricks \u2013 and you can earn the Dread Harvest AA card. (This means you have to play tournaments!)\nPlaying in dungeons across Entrath can reward players with the Stingy Jack card and its equipment pieces, the Scarecrow\u2019s Scythe and the Corn Huskers. In the harvest season, a time of plenty, Stingy Jack wants everything. He wields his terrifying scythe and grabs hold of this treat or that with his ever-sticky gloves. Hide your harvest well, for ol\u2019 Jack is a-coming to trick-or-treat.\nTo earn these rewards, champions must defeat any dungeon during the Haunted Harvest holiday:\n\nSo how do you get the rewards?\nThe first time a player logs in during this holiday, they will receive the Stingy Jack sleeve.\nAll tournaments will have a participation prize of an AA Dread Harvest card. Basically, enter a tournament, get the card.\nPlayers that win a constructed ranked ladder match will have a 25% chance of earning an AA Dread Harvest card.\nPlayers can earn PvE items by playing in the Campaign dungeons. There is one card and two equipment items to earn. By defeating any dungeon you will earn one of the three items at random. Each of them has a percent chance to drop: 15% on the Rare Equipment, 25% on the Uncommon Equipment, and 60% on the Card.\nJoin the spooky-scary campfire between October 18 at 19:00 CET (10 AM PST) and November 1 at 18:59 CET (9:59am PST) to gather your harvest. Happy Haunted Harvest!", "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "410380", "page": 27, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "text": "We are pleased to announce that we are now offering \u201cAdventure Pack 1\u201d for sale in the ingame store. These packs are purchasable for gold!\nEach of these Adventure Packs contains 2 common cards, 2 pieces of equipment or Stardust, and 1 card from the campaign. Purchasing Adventure Pack 1 from the store also carries a chance at one of the racial exclusive rares found in the campaign.\nThis is one of the latest steps we are taking to enhance the campaign experience for everyone making their way into Entrath.\nAnother change you may have already noticed is increased gold rewards across all encounters. With these increased rewards, it should be easier to get a good purse together and supplement your campaign decks through Adventure Packs.\nIf you are curious about new and great ways to tackle the campaign, including the slightly harder encounters \u2013 Wormoids anyone? \u2013 make sure to check out Nicosharp\u2019s articles!", "early_access": false}
