{"page_order": 24, "recommended": true, "date": "2018-01-18", "text": "Gorgeous art direction, character design, and overall atmosphere with a very sleek in game UI.\nSuperb and unique background music and soundtracks.\nVery likable and relatable main protagonist.\nWhile the entire plot is a simple magical girl story with melancholic mood, the game is very relaxing and charming. The story is well executed and has a memorable ending.\nVery poor game engine optimisation and limited graphic option. Well, it's a Gust game, so crap engine is quite within an expectation (even the PlayStation 4 version is badly optimised).\nLimitation in production budget is very obvious: limited map and enemy varieties, partial voice acting, and somewhat short side story for other characters other than the main trios.\nWhile the game mechanics and combats are very unique, they are not quite balance and overall game is a bit too easy, even on the hardest difficulty.\n\nWhile this is very minor, pointless, and doesn't affect gameplay or plot at all, the vertical camera control in the changing room model viewer is very limited in the English version of the game.\nThe story is linear, and combat can be quite repetitive on later chapters (though, you can choose to safely skip any optional quests).\nWhile it certainly has some technical and gameplay issues, Blue Reflection is a very unique flawed gem. Its colourful atmosphere and simple magical girl story about friendship is charming enough to capture my attention until the end.", "hours": 40.6, "username": "LAMBDA", "products": 132, "early_access": false}
