{"product_id": "746800", "page": 1, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-11-21", "text": "So from what I gather from my few hrs of gameplay,I must say that the game currently need some polishing.Though I must say the graphics is absolutely astounding which is why I purchase this game.The lighting in the game is what makes is unique from the rest from what I played.The level design is well-made and unique in each level and it is REALLY gorgeous to look at.Be prepared for rage inducing puzzles because once you die in one of the long puzzles,you have to start over and there is no checkpoints mind you.The game is more to puzzle-platformer aspect than action which is quite wierd why theres no puzzle tag for the product currently when I am writing this review.I haven't really  finish the game yet and heres why:\nTechinical issues with the game, Like for example,When you so happens to leave mid-game, you have to start ALL OVER again which is game breaking,there is no save option either so you have to start back from the VERY BEGINNING OF THE GAME. I was a chapter 4 when it happen.So you might need to play in one sitting.\nSecondly,Theres no exit option for the game. When I press Esc and press 'Menu',it goes back to the title screen, and I cant find any options to leave the game so I have to manually go to my desktop using alt+tab and quit the game from there.\nThirdly, the 'subtitles' are either not in sync with the voice or the voice said something that is not in the subtiles so I was confused.The speed of the subtitles coming in was super fast and I haven't have the time to read and the (robotic?) voice is not helping. Oh and there are few spelling errors here and there too like 'evcerday'.\nIf only steam have a neutral option because the game is good but it still need to polish up some defacts here and there", "hours": 1.6, "user_id": "76561198202014886", "username": "Paradox", "products": 67, "found_funny": 2, "early_access": false}
