{"product_id": "410380", "page": 29, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "text": "Greetings everyone!\nOn Wednesday, 07/09/2016 the servers will be coming offline for a maintenance and the installation of a new update.\nAs you may have guessed already, this update is our fifth card set,\n.\nHere\u2019s what this new expansion has in store for you again:\n\u2022    275 new cards\n\u2022    4 new keywords, 2 of which are faction-specific\n\u2022    20 new Champions\n\u2022    20 completely new gems\nThe patch day starts at 06:00 AM CEST (21:00 PST, -1), when we\u2019ll close registrations for new tournaments. We wouldn\u2019t want you to be in the middle of a match when the servers come down.\nThen at 10:00 CEST (01:00 PST) we\u2019ll take the servers offline to give our databases a good scrubbing and put in the new cards one by one.\nThe servers should be coming back online at 14:00 CEST (05:00 PST) if everything goes according to plan.\nOccasionally, while giving our servers a once over, we discover the odd Dreadling interfacing with one of the nodes and need to valorously get rid of the little bugger. While this isn\u2019t the most strenuous activity, it might take some extra time and the maintenance might last a little longer as a result.\nBut fear not, even while the servers are down, there'll be enough HEX to keep you entertained. Starting at 10:00 CEST (01:00am PST), our special guest Rollup\nwill be streaming for you on our official Twitch channel\nto give you some impressions of the new set. Of course, there'll be plenty of giveaways, too. So don't miss it!\nThank you for your patience and understanding!\nHere\u2019s the schedule in short-form:\n\u2022    06:00 CEST (21:00 PST, -1) \u2013 Tournament registrations closed\n\u2022    10:00 CEST (01:00 PST) \u2013 Servers offline\n\u2022    14:00 CEST (05:00 PST) \u2013 Servers online (expected)", "early_access": false}
