{"product_id": "378860", "page": 7, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2018-01-03", "text": "Project CARS 2 is probably the first sim racing game I got into with a proper wheel setup. Coming in as a new sim racer, here are some of the pros and cons in my perspective.\nPROS:\n- Force Feedback: As a new sim racer, the force feedback feels great on a wheel!\n- Graphics: This game look beautiful, probably one of the best looking sim racers out there.\n- Sounds: The cars sound amazing, you can really feel the sheer power of the car just based on the sound alone.\n- Ranking System: It isn't perfect, but it works. You can definitely tell which players have more experience based on their ranks and how they do in races.\n- Multiplayer: You can for sure find good and genuine races which can really pump your adrenaline when fighting for positions. But there are flaws (see cons).\nCONS:\n- Multiplayer: There are going to be people who will intentionally ram you or swerve left and right on the track trying to \"defend\" their position... Also, there will be races where you will probably get caught in a carnage on lap 1. Especially on turn 1. Some players just don't know the breaking points and may just run into you on a turn.\n- Bugs: Sometimes races don't start properply and you may be stuck on the wait screen or the start-line of a race. (usually happens in larger games).\n- Freezes: I do occasionally get freezes in this game. But it doesn't happen too often to annoy me.\nOverall:\nI love this game. The game just feels so good, looks great, and sounds great! Yes, there are cons in multiplayer, but I'm not saying there will be carnage in every single race. You will have races that can be really fun and competitive!\nTo me, it feel as if the skill set in this player base has a wider range than other sim racers how there. If you want a sim racing game with a more serious player base, maybe check out iRacing or Race Room (That's my opinion, definitely do your research.).\nWhether you are new to sim racing or not, I say give this game a try!\nBut again, if you want something more serious, maybe check out other titles.", "hours": 179.1, "username": "\u25e2\u25e4 kLA", "products": 93, "early_access": false}
