{"product_id": "734580", "page": 21, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-08", "text": "BattleRush is a basic WW2 shooter with a small variety of weapons vehicles and a basic but fairly intuitive. The game is still in alpha, and plays like one.\nThis wont be a full review, because it cant be. The game is still in alpha, so with the very frequent updates adding and fixing things, which is good, things are going to change.\nThe game overall at the moment should not be played competitively. The mechanics aren't smooth, the combat is sometimes unresponsive and the gamemode is flawed and overly basic - AT THE CURRENT STATE. What this game is now, is the foundations for a GREAT game, the combat although fidly at the moment, will feel very satifying when it is developed some more. The building aspect of the game, though minimal now, is still enough for it to impact the game greatly and is the base for a very easy to use building system comparable to the one in Fortnite.\nThe physics and destruction isn't the best, but works. With development, it will create some cool and tactical battles while playing.\nThe weapons are fairly balanced but can feel unresponsive and hard to hit shots with certain weapons in certain situations, for example bot action rifles, however with some tweaking to hit registry and movement this can feel a lot nicer. Grenades dont feel too useful except in buildings, which from experience combat barely happens in single buildings. This can be fixed by making them go a little further when thrown.\nThe crafting and gathering is a good idea, but basic. This allows it to not get in the way and I think it should stay this way. Soem things are harder to craft and gather than others, but not overly difficult to the point where you dont see action. Still, I'm sure later people will be more serious and assign squads to do this job for the team.\nThere is currently a single gamemode, with more to definately come because the current is probably the weakest point of the game. The overall objective of the game is to destory the enemy base, and thats it. Obviously this will be tweaked, as it is just the early playable test version, but more smaller sub-objectives need to be added sooner rather than later.\nOverall, I definately recommend giving this game a try even if its just for the one time. I'd also say to come back in a few weeks to a month as I think by then the game will be much better, as its still in its very early stages. This is fine and all you can do is give it time to mature as with some more time the game will be very good. Cheers", "hours": 4.9, "username": "Tyyler", "products": 84, "early_access": true}
