{"product_id": "609150", "page": 16, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-03", "text": "Star Ocean The Last Hope.\nNot the BEST in the series, but definitely great. While my favourite will always be The Second Story / Second Evolution, this game will always go down as a great Star Ocean game.\nThe English dub is a little jarring, but if you don't mind the cheesiness, go for it. But I would definitely recommend the Japanese dub. Also, the classic style > the modern style. Gives the character portraits an anime vibe rather than the CG modern.\nAll I can say is, give it a shot if you're into action-JRPGs.\nAnd yes, it is Action, not turn-based.", "hours": 22.9, "username": "Sunbringer Kyo", "products": 313, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "609150", "page": 16, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-03", "text": "I love the star ocean series, and missed out on this one shortly after my friends xbox died. (not my fault). I only got a few hours on it then and going 8 hours now. Game play holds up but some of the cut scenes do suffer from the puppet on a string syndrome. I only ever noticed it in the opening scenes. Those are when you get the real close ups with the eyes....\nBut other than that, the game has been a joy. the sprint helps so much but the camera suffers for it in narrow corridors like in star ships.", "hours": 10.1, "user_id": "76561198049974479", "username": "lorduvlight", "products": 34, "early_access": false}
