{"product_id": "609150", "page": 16, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-03", "text": "before i start with this review:\nMy Pc Specs:\ni7-4790K 4.0GHz\nGTX 980 4GB\n16GB Ram\ni am currently running this game at 3840x2160p 4K Resolution @ 60FPS with no lag at all\nNow this game should take you awhile to complete if you are a 100% get all the stuff gamer, the graphics are amazing at 4K and really pop out Really vivid to me. You can use a controller or use your keyboard i prefer keyboard since it has more of a keybind option than the controller. Gameplay is really fun and can get addicting the battles are not turn based so as soon a battle starts you can run around the battle area while attacking the enemy. Story is really well done and i would most likely have to say i love this more than skyrim in some areas, I played this game on xbox 360 and still own the game but the  fact that console has 30FPS and crap resolution just makes it awful to play on.\nthis is the first Star Ocean Game on pc though i wish they would of also brought over Integrity and Faithlessness  from ps4 since i loved that game a lot.\nI Would Recommend This Game To Anyone that enjoys JRPGS and Anime", "hours": 8.0, "username": "MoogleSummoner", "products": 526, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
