{"product_id": "609150", "page": 16, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-03", "text": "I played this game years ago on the PS3 but due to high school final exams, I never had the chance to finish it. Since my PS3 is broken beyond repair, I'm using this chance to finally lay this game to rest. Unfortunately for me, this game proves that I'm no longer a teenager.\nSTAR OCEAN\u2122 - THE LAST HOPE is a JRPG through and through. It tries to be taken seriously but failed spectacularly in the first 10 minutes. The game has the most stereotypical anime plot ever, that anyone who frequently watched animes and read mangas knows will happen next. It literally uses all tropes and cliches that each and every other animes used. The characters are even worst as none of them are remotely interesting or unique. All of them are copy and pasted from any other Japanese media for teenagers ever existed.\nJust like any other low effort JRPG, the game is padded with mindless grind where players either need to fight certain amount of enemies to 100% the database or to farm crafting material. It gets old, real fast as crafting is essential in every Star Ocean game. Not doing it means players are basically missing out half of the game.\nBattles are okay, in the first hour at least. Thanks to the grind, fighting enemies became more like a chore than fun and like in the previous Star Ocean games, the bonus board makes a return. These bonuses are crucial to the game's level progression, so players are incentivize to get them as soon as possible. Unfortunately, the bonus board resets every time players exits the game so this further forces players to keep playing as they're grinding. Coincidentally, the bonus board always seems to break easier while fighting the boss for some reason...\nIf the story and characters are bad, then the voice acting are even more atrocious. The English VO is so jarring and cringe worthy but I really don't want to blame the VAs as they were given bad scripts in the first place.\nIf you like animes/mangas, then you'll probably enjoy this game more than I ever will. If you expect quality from this, look elsewhere. Unless this game is on a 75% sale, I will never recommend this game to anyone above 25 years old.", "hours": 34.1, "user_id": "76561198058043953", "username": "kandnm115709", "products": 101, "found_funny": 4, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "410380", "page": 31, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "text": "Here\u2019s how it works: The\nplayers on each Ladder (Constructed and Limited) at the end of this season will get a ladder ticket that allows them to participate in this season\u2019s Cosmic Crown Showdown.\nThe showdown is broken up into two Stages which will take place on\nand\n. The tournament will be held in-client under the \u201cSpecial\u201d tab of the tournament screen.\nSeptember 10th, starting at 9am PT (6pm CEST), we will have a Constructed Swiss tournament (with best 2-out-of-3 matches) for qualifying ladder players.\nThe\nplayers from this Stage will move on to Stage 2.\nSeptember 11th, starting at 9am PT (6pm CEST), we will have a Single-Elimination Draft tournament (with best 2-out-of-3 matches). The winner of Stage 2 will walk away with exclusive cosmetics and the lion\u2019s share of the prize pool.\nCheck out the prizes in detail:\nKeep your eyes peeled for the full (Terms and Conditions), we\u2019ll have them for you soon.\nWill you be the first to wear the Cosmic Crown? Start climbing and find out!\nBest of luck on the battlefield!", "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "410380", "page": 31, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "text": "This is it. The stalemate is broken and war is coming.\nWith Herofall, HEX\u2019s story will focus on the growing conflict between the Ardent and Underworld. Herofall lets you experience the precarious balance between Entrath\u2019s factions and will give you a front row seat to see it crumble.\nHerofall will feature over 275 new cards and introduce completely new mechanics to the game. There are a whole host of new style choices thanks to 4 new keywords \u2013 with both Ardent and Underworld having one keyword each exclusive to them. We are also introducing 20 new champions and 20 new gems to HEX!\nBut this is not all, there is more to come!\nIf you are heading out to GenCon this year, there is a chance you will discover the first few cards of Herofall.\nStay tuned for more info on Herofall, our fifth card set, in the coming weeks.\nIt will be some time for the wounds to heal and become fading scars of war.", "early_access": false}
