{"product_id": "609150", "page": 16, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-03", "text": "It's a good game. People that think that it's cringe worthy probably have no experience with JRPGs. I suggest turning off the english dub. There are some people that played for 1.5 hours and gave it a bad review. Really? 1 hour because you can't figure out the controls? It really shows the new generation of gamers. Casuals that expect everything to be handed to them. Overall,  It's a highly underrated Star Ocean game. When it came out I think it got a 7 or 6 out of 10. I bought it anyway and it's defintely at least an 8 maybe a 9 in today's standards. For the price it's defintely worth the buy.\nSome Key Points:\n-There's a lot of meaningful grind and progression is at a pretty good spot.\n-Story isn't as corny and cringy if you leave it on Japanese Dub because English Dub tends to exagerrate character expressions.\n-Battle system is pretty good with a variety of characters to choose for your party and strategies.\n-I suggest not skipping through cut scenes and looking at the character development while you're on the ship or certain areas. Because that's what Star Ocean is known for. It's not the Loot Box, Cut content DLC, Fanboyism that some casual gamers are addicted to.", "hours": 13.9, "user_id": "76561198109636824", "username": "Strikedeezfosheezy", "products": 43, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "410380", "page": 31, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "text": "Hey everyone! Hey everyone! Dino here with another Friday Update.\nFirst up, I want to remind everyone that we will be at Gen Con next week!\nWe will have fabulous swag (like the sleeves/posters above) as well as competitive events using special boosters designed specially for the convention. It will be a party! Plus, I want to meet each and every one of you. So if you happen to be in the area, make sure you stop by Booth 501. See you there!\nWe also have a special article this week from our one and only Ben Stoll. We\u2019ve let Ben out of the game-making cage so he could share our goals for Set and Gem rotation in HEX. If you want to know what an \u201cImmortal format\u201d is or \u201cwhat\u2019s the deal with all those gems,\u201d make sure you go here.\nFinally, I want to remind everyone that Five Shard\u2019s Lixil Series will be rotating to Tuesdays in August. If you enjoy winning packs and exclusive Alternate Arts through constructed play and weren\u2019t able to make July\u2019s Monday events, make sure to click the AA Lixil for details on how to join!", "early_access": false}
