{"product_id": "410380", "page": 32, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "text": "The Ladder system in HEX is now live and we sat down with one of the developers to give you the full scoop on the new ranked modes. Here's all you need to know about the update:\nThere are two separate Ladders, one for Limited format tournaments - that is Draft, Sealed and Evolution Sealed - and one for games in the Constructed format.\nThe Limited format has its name because you have to build your deck from a\nnumber of cards. Here's how:\nIn a\n, you and your opponents bring 3 booster packs to the table and open them together, passing the packs around,\none card each until the packs are empty.\nThe Sealed format works slightly different. In the classic\nformat, you enter with 6 booster packs and open them all to construct your deck from those cards. In\n, you bring 2 booster packs yourself and the game provides you with 3 more packs of\nand\ncards to build your deck. You can earn more packs as you win games, with one win granting you 1 additional pack to round out your deck and your third win granting you one more for the final touches.\nPlayers will have two separate ranks for those two modes.\nAbove is an example of how it will look in-game. The player here has achieved a Gold ranking in the Limited format and the highest ranking - Cosmic - in the Constructed format.\nPlaying any Limited format tournament will affect your rank in that ladder, playing in a ranked Constructed match will affect your rank there. Both formats are exclusive and do not count towards the other's rank. The ranks go from Bronze all the way to Platinum and the elite division of Cosmic, with five tiers to each of the five divisions:\nYou advance through the ranks by playing matches. Win a match and earn a star, lose a match and you lose a star. Go on a winning streak and you will earn an additional star for winning!\nThe system will always attempt to match you with players of the same or similar skill level and widen its search to avoid wait times. Here's a special bit: once you graduate from the beginner's division, Bronze, you cannot go back down for the remainder of that Season.\nSeasons last 2 months and are played back to back with no offseason.\nWith that said...\nWhat's in it for you? Well, besides the obvious bragging rights, there is epic loot waiting to be had as you climb the ladder.\nDuring any ongoing Season, you will be able to show your current rank with a Sleeve for your decks. After a Season has concluded, you will be granted a Sleeve reflecting your\nin that Season. Here's how they look for Season 1:\nTo furhter impress your opponents and show off your aptitude, your cards will rest on a special plinth during your matches. These plinths reflect your current rank, just like the regular Season Sleeves. Check them out:\nHEX wouldn't be HEX without a few new Alternate Art (AA) cards. Advancing through the ranks in both Limited and Constructed play will reward you with these cool new interpretations of classic cards:\nAs if all that's not already loot a-plenty, you will also earn Gold - our in-game currency - and booster packs as you move up the ladder.\nThat's it everyone, the full scoop on the ladder! Do you have what it takes to reach Cosmic? Show us!\nGet your competitive juices flowing and hit the ladder in\n.\nYour HEX Team.", "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "410380", "page": 32, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "text": "Greetings everyone,\nDuring the time of (even more) fun and games, Quest will reward you with the Impulse AA Sleeve for making merry with your fellow Entrathians. (Simply log in and you will automatically receive the sleeve!)\nThose of you following the ancient tradition of playing with or against each other in (more or less) friendly duels will receive the Impulse AA card.\nPlaying in dungeons across Entrath can reward players with the Entrath Settlers card and its equipment pieces, the Helm of a Good Game and the Robber\u2019s Gloves. As Settlers do, these crafty and skilled folks set out to gather resources and build villages. Manage your settlements during the time of Questmas to bring the advantage of a happy populace to bear. To earn these rewards, champions must defeat any dungeon during the Questmas holiday:\nThe first time a player logs in during this holiday, they will receive a Questmas sleeve.\nAll tournaments will have a participation prize of an AA Impulse card. Basically, enter a tournament, get the card.\nPlayers that win a Constructed ranked ladder match with have a 25% chance of earning the Impulse AA card.\nPlayers can earn PvE items by playing in the Campaign dungeons. There is one card and two equipment items to earn. By defeating any dungeon you will earn one of the three items at random. Each of them has a percent chance to drop: 15% on the Rare Equipment, 25% on the Uncommon Equipment, and 60% on the Card.\n\u2022    Entrath Settlers\n\u2022    Helm of a Good Game (Rare)\n\u2022    Robber\u2019s Gloves (Uncommon)\nJoin the fun between July 11 at 19:00 CET (10 AM PST) and July 25 at 18:59 CET (9:59am PST) to earn these utterly delightful rewards and make merry with your fellow Entrathians!\nGood luck and \u2013 more importantly \u2013 have fun!", "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "410380", "page": 32, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "text": "Greetings everyone!\nOn 05/07/2016 the servers will be undergoing maintenance, during which time we'll be installing a new update for you.\nThings start at 6 AM (CEST), when we'll close registrations for new tournaments. Then at 10 AM (CEST) we'll take the servers offline. If everything runs according to plan, the servers will reopen their gates to you again at 1 PM (CEST).\nNote: Occasionally, while giving our servers a once over, we discover a spider egg in the deck or catch a shroomkin chewing on one of the cables \u2013 when that happens, it sometimes takes a little longer before everything is back online.\nThanks for your patience and understanding!\n06:00 CEST (9pm PDT) \u2013 Tournament servers lock\n10:00 CEST (1am PDT) \u2013 Servers offline\n13:00 CEST (4am PDT) \u2013 Expected end to maintenance", "early_access": false}
