{"product_id": "563610", "page": 1, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-11-30", "text": "If you like Squash then this is a good Squash VR game. There are some minor issues but the developer is working and releasing updates to improve. An example is ball physics, it was not good before and I had hard time to hit but now it has been fixed and improved.\nI think this game could be an Early Access to start with lower price so that people would understand this scenario before buying it, give their feedback for improvements and later on make it finalized release with more price as necessary.", "hours": 0.7, "compensation": "Product received for free", "username": "Zeeshan", "products": 26, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "563610", "page": 1, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-11-27", "text": "As I am huge fan of Eleven, I was thrilled to test VRSQUASH. However I`ve never played squash in my life. So it was a bit figuring out myself. The game however still needs some work. The physics are a bit slow if you compare to Eleven which feels more realistic in physics terms. However I`ve never played Squash so I can`t really compare to real life :D. But this game do has opportunities. If the physics get optimized and you have a room scale setup this could really be an awesome competitive game on vr. And multiplayer is on the horizon. The developer seems to be really responsive and uses the tips of the community. If you`re a squash fan you can buy this to support the developer. I`m pretty sure more updates will follow.\nSummary:\n+Good basis\n+opportunity to become a competitive vr game\n+responsive dev\n+multiplayer coming\n+would bash my table again\n-design is a bit dull atm\n-responsiveness/physics not yet on point\nGet this game if you want to support the developer optimizing this game, he takes note of your comments", "hours": 1.1, "username": "ABU", "products": 84, "early_access": false}
