{"page_order": 17, "recommended": true, "date": "2018-01-12", "text": "Awesome game, except the part that is Open World game but though they force you to play firstly the main missions, otherwise you get on missions like The arena where you can't complete it because it's a bug and if you have higher lvl than 10-11 it seems you can't pass the mission and you have to start the game over again from the very first start..which sucks. I played secondary missions like 5-10 hours and then when I played The Arena I noticed that I can't complete it and can't finish the game because of this stupid bug.. Completely dissapointed and I loved the game..", "hours": 23.5, "username": "wolfy \ud83d\udc3e #\u03c9\u03b1\u0438\u2202\u0454\u044f\u2113\u03c5\u0455\u0442", "products": 2023, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"page_order": 18, "recommended": true, "date": "2018-01-14", "text": "This game was good before they put out the rebellion update it really lacks give and take. Now there is no common balance you can spend an hour going after a couple orcs and then they turn around and take five from you it is not fair. Not worth my time its hard enough to go thru the campaign without constantly having to backtrack to help your army before your kingdom gets taken over.", "hours": 23.4, "user_id": "76561198047116526", "username": "GrillColman", "products": 316, "early_access": false}
{"page_order": 19, "recommended": true, "date": "2018-01-13", "text": "The game itself isn't bad, the story is fine even though it seems to take a back seat to everything else, the grindiness of it all is OK as long as that's not something you hate, the item system is a little limited but much better then Shadows of Mordor, the follower system could have been a little more interesting imo but it's not the worst either. Almost everything about this game is at least alright except for one glaring thing...\nThe controls are infuriating, towards the end of the game when mob fighting becomes pretty standard it's disgusting how often you get knocked out of things from a wayward arrow or a grunt who suddenly launches through the air because the game decided he was locked onto you Wraith teleport be damned.. the amount of times my character has glitched out while trying to dominate a captain is depressing not to mention Wraith teleporting into trees, walls, etc. I thouroughly enjoy the game for about 30 minutes until something like this happens, at the end captains hit like trucks so if your controls betray you twice in a fight you're done for, if you die the captain levels up (usually far past your own level) making them impossible to be dominated unless shamed which is depressing because shame tends to ruin them.\nAnyway, the game suffers from the controls so often that I find it to be a slog.. not to mention the actual slog it becomes (which I'm okay with, I enjoy grinding... huehue).\nP.S.\nYet another gripe with the controls being if you do end up getting knocked out of anything the controls seem to queue up your previous command... say you get hit by a grunt and then want to drain the grunt you press and hold drain while you're \"stunned\" and it will sit there doing nothing, so you let go of drain and try it again and you instead Wraith punch at nothing. Fml.", "hours": 41.7, "user_id": "76561198019327818", "username": "JohnFrancais", "products": 119, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "410380", "page": 35, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "text": "Greetings HEXers!\nThe HEX servers will be going offline for a critical hotfix on 04/05/2016.\nAt 10 AM (CEST) we will take the servers offline. If everything runs according to plan, the servers will reopen their gates to you again by 14 PM (CEST).\nNote: Occasionally, while giving our servers a once over, we discover a spider egg in the deck or catch a shroomkin chewing on one of the cables \u2013 when that happens, it sometimes takes a little longer before everything is back online.\nThanks for your patience and understanding!\n6 AM (CEST) / 9 PM PDT (3rd May) - Tournaments will be locked.\n10 AM (CEST) / 1 AM PDT \u2013 Servers offline.\n14:00 (CEST) / 5 AM PDT -  Expected end to maintenance.", "early_access": false}
