{"product_id": "734580", "page": 22, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-07", "text": "Has been playing this all day today. I may have enjoyed it but I often seen far too many hackers on server. Not only that, server have been lagging all the damn day. Oh don't even try to press Del key because it will break your game completely. You will have to reinstall the game if you press Del key while in game. This game is completely buggy and have many things that need to be fixing and rebalanced. Like sometime game itself will flash in green color and I would have to change the video setting to fix it every time. It does not have much video option and no v-sync option either. So its basically a screen tearing game since there is no fps cap on it. At the moment the paid kits are p2w in some way. You cant even get scoped guns unless you happen to find a air drop. Paid kit came with scoped gun easily. Game chat system blows because everyone can see your texts to team. It totally needs to be fixed. Enemies will set up tents near your base and camping there. Devs need to do something about this. This game has potential to be great game to play. But it needs a lot of improvments. For now I would not recommend this game till things get fixed first. I will come back and give thumb up if it indeed get better.\nUPDATE: 12/12/2017: I decided to uninstall this game due annoying rubber banding, green screen flickering, and weird crashing bugs like it prevent me from do anything all of sudden out of no where. This game needs a ton of fixing. I kept losing my hard work and stuff when game decided to stop me from playing. I am done.", "hours": 23.6, "compensation": "Product received for free", "user_id": "76561198148750482", "username": "DeafGamerDucky", "products": 51, "early_access": true}
{"product_id": "734580", "page": 22, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-07", "text": "FIX THE \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665ING RESOLUTION BUG", "hours": 14.5, "user_id": "76561198151689932", "username": "420tokes2", "products": 58, "early_access": true}
{"product_id": "734580", "page": 22, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-07", "text": "Hi\nIn itself, the game is very interesting, especially the looten / manufacture of objects brings a lot of fun. But I do not want to rewieven too much because it's still pretty much the beginning of the creation process or beta but what ever schonmal is very positive that almost every day an update for the game comes out!\nOne thing I would like to explain, though:\nSo in about every 3min. For me the whole game starts to freeze for a short time, which is after 10-15 sec. normalized but still extremely frustrating !!\nWould be really nice if you could do something!\nOtherwise, I'm looking forward to the (eventually) finished game could be an alternative to some games of the genre ^^", "hours": 8.1, "user_id": "76561198125916068", "username": "[zm] BeeNiie", "products": 15, "early_access": true}
{"product_id": "734580", "page": 22, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-07", "text": "12/8/17\nIt can only get better, and it's pretty good.\nThey recently fixed stuff that seemed to be causing problems with server's stability.\nThey're doing great so far, managing the game with hotfixes.\nI'll put up more feedback as the game gets updated, so my review can change by the time this leave early access. I know all too well about it being possible to ruin a really fun game, as of now, it's going great.\nBase reinforment is an awesome concept. Being able to destroy, what I assume to be everything, with non-grenade explosives is awesome. You can also set yourself up with a mobile spawn point in the crafting, that lets you spawn anywhere. I mean, you can basically just make a new base right next to the enemy. Which, with the update today, you might be able to do with some of your teammates, with the in game team chat.\nOr you can play a game of diss the snipers.\nIn regards to the assumed P2W aspect, I disagree with it. You can find the guns just lying around on the map, or loot them from guys they died. So, it's not like it restricts you from getting these things. The only thing I haven't seen just around as loot would be snipers, but I havent' explored the massive map yet to confirm that.\nI like this game.\nI haven't gotten to try vehicles yet. You have to survive and stock up, alone or with your team to get something. The XP system, I think, needs some work. But, we'll see where they go with this class system. Being in alpha, I'm sure they'll rework it at some point.\nIt's a good F2P game in early access, Alpha version.", "hours": 3.4, "compensation": "Product received for free", "username": "Mysterious Mr.Grim", "products": 168, "early_access": true}
{"product_id": "734580", "page": 22, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-07", "text": "good game but it boring  far  pay2win // ping //hack", "hours": 2.3, "username": "sir ZEED", "products": 16, "early_access": true}
{"product_id": "734580", "page": 22, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-07", "text": "This game looks quite bad on first glance but after i decided to give it a try i must say that the gameplay is extremly fun.\nVery unique gameplay\nTruly feels like a *war* especialy when both sides are on trenches trying to just get a few meters of ground.\nDLCs are very cheap and while they do give a bit of an advantage in the end what matters is the teamplay and what you build much more than the guns you have etc.\nIf you are reading reviews to check if the game is worth your time then take my word and just download this.\nTo the devs: Keep the very frequent updates up you got something good here and thanks", "hours": 18.9, "username": "Constantine", "products": 22, "early_access": true}
{"product_id": "734580", "page": 22, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-07", "text": "PAY-TO-WIN;PAY-TO-WIN;PAY-TO-WIN;\nTerrible. Would've fit more on\nthan Steam. Youre mixed in with people who've bought scoped weapons and the best tank and SEVERELY out-class(and out-range) you. Gameplay was the only saving grace only to be disappointed with a bland 25vs25, often lopsided, and absolutely NOTHING happening. THERE'S NO PROGRESSION and NOTHING happens when you defeat the enemy base, it's futile. 0/10, not even with a rented\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665", "hours": 17.4, "username": "Swagrid The Walrus", "products": 17, "early_access": true}
{"product_id": "734580", "page": 22, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-07", "text": "A perfectly executed WWII game that i find very fun. The game has alot of bugs but the game is in alpha so it just what i should expect. The only problem i have is its a bit hard to level up (Gain XP). But those are my only complaints. I would give the game 9/10 for an overall rating.", "hours": 3.4, "username": "Durry McFlurry", "products": 61, "early_access": true}
