{"product_id": "410380", "page": 37, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "text": "Good News Everyone,\nOn the 26th of April we are going to update the game with our latest card set - Primal Dawn.\nTo do this, we will need a server maintenance with the following schedule:\n11:00 PDT (8:00 CEST) \u2013 Lock tournament server\n03:00 PDT (12:00 CEST) \u2013 Bring down servers and begin the update\n07:00 PDT (16:00 CEST) \u2013 Estimated time to open up\nWe will keep the community informed with all the latest news as we update the servers.\nIn addition, once the game has been brought down Infam0usne0\nwill be doing a special live stream where you will get to see a preview of the new cards, and hear all the latest news on our update progress.", "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "410380", "page": 37, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "text": "Greetings, HEXers.\nHot off the server, we have your patch notes.\n(Expect some tweaks and additions as the day progresses)", "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "410380", "page": 37, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "text": "Greetings everyone,\nOver the past few days, the community has been providing us with extremely valuable feedback regarding the pricing of HEX on Steam.\nWe have seen your passion on this topic and after carefully weighing your arguments, I am very happy to inform all of you that we agree with you \u2013 the community \u2013 in that a game like HEX should not have different prices between our clients.\nTherefore, the Steam shop has been updated so that all purchases give you the same amount as it would in the normal store.\nYour feedback is always valuable to us and I\u2019d like to encourage you all to continue to provide us with your opinions, arguments and any constructive feedback about the various parts of the game! You are the ones giving life to the great community that is HEX.", "early_access": false}
