{"product_id": "609150", "page": 17, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-02", "text": "Squeeeeenixxxxxxxxxx!\nGreat game! Buy it! support the devs and publishers they truly deserve it for this masterpiece of a game. In contrast this game is barely costing $20 for a ported remastered version compared to most horrible triple A+ title releases these days.\nYou can play it in both Japanese or English Voice-overs with subtitled text to boot (so whatever you fancy). The graphics are fantastic (on my 2K/1440p resolution), music is fun and gameplay is good.\nAlso heard there's over 100 hours of solid gameplay which also seems unbelievable but amazing (the game is 52 gigs intalled).\nLong live JRPGS!\nfor any of those having issues with fullscreen not working there's a fix for this already using Kaldaien's borderless fullscreen.\nThere's a thread on this in the community discussion forum so go check it out! (Just search \"Fullscreen\" in the steam discussion forum search bar)", "hours": 20.7, "username": "Chairo (Broadcasting)", "products": 116, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "609150", "page": 17, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-02", "text": "Ah! One of the greats.\nThis Star Ocean is falls in line with the others in story and gameplay. It's Pretty standard. Though the Main Character in this one is a bit annoying, and managing to be the most annoying out of the others. Probably be a better game in Japanes as the voice actors in this are forcing alot of things.\nPro\nGreat game and story\nClassic Star Ocean feel I.E. Welch is here making Items for you.\nTri-Ace Graphics on Space scenes. These were the best in all the games.\nCons\nWell it an old game use a game pad.\nLastly I am playing on my comm hook to a large TV. So you basic mid range computer should not have a problem.", "hours": 15.7, "user_id": "76561197988693069", "username": "Jupman", "products": 97, "early_access": false}
