{"product_id": "609150", "page": 17, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-02", "text": "Mass Effect: The JRPG...\nWith Final Fantasy graphics, combat pretty close to the more modern 'tales of' games and a musical score very similar to those used in Star Wars / Star Trek games and movies, this game has a lot going for it.\nAlso as I stated above, the story line is literally the equivalent of the first 3 mass effect games, so if you enjoyed them, like the anime-esque art style, dungeon crawlers and JRPG's, then you may as well give this a go.", "hours": 26.7, "username": "Goughy", "products": 375, "found_funny": 3, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "609150", "page": 17, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-02", "text": "A real blast from the past.\nCons:\nI've got it in 1920x1080 on a 24\" monitor but it doesnt seem to scale to the full widescreen. Which is odd, as this game came out on the ps3....\nPros:\nyou can perv on Reimi in the shower.", "hours": 8.5, "username": "Sheepykins", "products": 180, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "609150", "page": 17, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-02", "text": "I cannot recommend, at least for the PC. Controls are anti-intuitive, requiring surgical precision to simply open chests. Automatic view and targeting options are non-existent. Monsters can easily interrupt your attacks, but you can barely (if ever) interrupt theirs. Anti-Blindside Game Mechanics: Why? Why even? Your split-second timing is rewarded with a crit to the face? Really? Bounce off the armor, to be sure, but punishment for accuracy in such a critical (no pun intended) game element? Boss Fights: Don't make any plans for the next half hour, and that's just a single attempt. Main character can sprint a total of 10 feet before getting tired (I'm fat and old, and I can still sprint 100 yards before I need to admit that I'm having a heart attack). Main character cannot climb anything - only jump down. Main character cannot step over any landscape feature larger than a dead squirrel, and will hang up upon encountering said landscape feature. Flying opponents will freely engage the group, though the group (despite having ranged weapons) cannot engage the flying opponents. What's more: Flying opponents will float along, completely ignoring you, despite all of your best efforts to attract them to combat... until you've passed under them - at which point they will ambush you from behind, despite your wariness of their existance and eagerness to engage them in combat. Those are the nits.\nThe story is kinda meh. The plot is kinda meh. I didn't expect a Shakesperian presentation, to be fair. I got exactly what I paid for, in those departments.\nBoiling these things down: The game has the potential to be engaging and entertaining, if the raw mechanics didn't drag the progression to an intolerable slog.\nThings might be better with some kind of controller, but if you're a hardened keyboard-and-mouse player like myself - save yourself the grief and pass.\nI love the Star Ocean IP, but this could have been done ~much~ better.", "hours": 15.7, "user_id": "76561198022646537", "username": "Stormraven", "products": 460, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "609150", "page": 17, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-02", "text": "As a fan of the star ocean series i was very excited for this when i found out about it. My friend got it for me for my birthday/ christmas so for me being free it is worth it haha. Now first thing that i didnt necessarily like is there isnt a vsync option. (for some people you will have to go to your Nividia Control Panel, add the game , and put on the Vsync option) Game looks beautiful and runs pretty smoothly,  my only problem with the game at this moment is that during combat, skills will cause a small pause in frame with each connected hit so when there is a large amount of enemies grouped up around you and your using a skill, it begins to lag. Fix this port and others that have been mentioned besides mine and im sure this game will be highly recommended. All in all wait until they fix the bugs before you buy this game because you can never be sure if your pc will be the one that does or doesnt have problems with this game. Or you can always just wait for a sale haha. Honestly though besides that hiccup its well worth the money", "hours": 3.6, "compensation": "Product received for free", "user_id": "76561198249793140", "username": "8BitPoochy", "products": 89, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "609150", "page": 17, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-02", "text": "Sweet Holy Crablettes!\nI first played Star Ocean The Last Hope on my Xbox 360. Which upon nearing the end of the game I ran into a game breaking glitch on the console. SO close to the ending but if I went past a save point the game would crash.\nThen the International version came out on the PS3. Played through halfway on my PS3 before it finally died sealing the game disc inside the system. (PS3 80gb Backwards compatible \"Fatty\" PS3. Might try to fix this one.)\nNow again I have a chance to play Enix's Star Ocean The Last Hope. (I know SquareEnix, but they weren't SquareEnix then). With Steam Cloud at my back... maybe I have a shot at finishing this remarkable masterpiece of storytelling.\nTruly gorgeous graphics this time around. And for those of you wondering... English AND Japanese voices are included. As well as the modern and classic interface themes! Don't let my playtime on Steam speak, I've enjoyed Star Ocean The Last Hope for hundreds of hours. Even if I had to star again and again. Seriously, no spoilers! I know what awaits me, and I'm NOT going to ruin the game for anyone. I'll let others do that.\nSo sit back and enjoy... well... play and enjoy this remarkable gem of the past.\nNow if we could get Star Ocean III on Steam too...", "hours": 16.5, "username": "Protos Heis", "products": 152, "found_funny": 7, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "609150", "page": 17, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-02", "text": "As a huge Tri-Ace fan, I'm excited to see this get ported over to the PC, moreso now that my PS3 is starting to get flaky. I'd love to see more Tri-Ace titles come to steam, especially more SO and Valkyrie Profile. Aside from a few technical things that need to be patched (vsync, audio sample above 44k crash bug) the PC port seems pretty top notch, especially for the price.", "hours": 62.4, "username": "Antares", "products": 59, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "609150", "page": 17, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-02", "text": "I played this back on the 360, liked it then (minus the disc swapping) and I still like it. It's hard to tell/remember if the character models look any better but good God the backgrounds will blow you away at full resolution, especially space. There are still some graphical issues (especially with hair and even more so with facial hair) but if that pushes you from this game you were looking for a reason. I imagine little things like that will be touched up if Square feels like it.\nGraphics aside, this is pretty standard fare for JRPGs/Star Oceans. Turns out you're a hero, using a sword, has special powers, yada yada. Fairy interesting story, entertaining characters (though there's little to be said for character development for all but one, maybe 2, crewmates), entertaining and challenging combat that took what it learned from SO3 and expanded on it and improved in all the right ways.\nIf (and with Square it's a BIG if) the game gets updates and even add-ons it'd be nice to see some more of the anime art style replacing some the of the spoken scenes as the portraits were incredibly well-done (I don't foresee this but since they went to the trouble of remastering and pushing this into 4k graphics, why not?). It'd also be nice to see some new outfits visible on the field and in battle.\nAll-in-all the game certainly doesn't do anything new for the genre but it's a great entry into it and the Star Ocean franchise.", "hours": 50.3, "user_id": "76561198054352818", "username": "dragonknight159", "products": 55, "early_access": false}
