{"product_id": "378860", "page": 8, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2018-01-02", "text": "I havne't been able to play this game at all. I can't select gears. I've tried so many things to get this working that I won't bore you with everything I've tried. PC2 refuses to let me play. I haven't moved my car one milimeter in game because I can't get out of neutral. When I assign my controls, it registers my wheel buttons just fine, but when I load up a race, I can't move. All I can do is sit there, turn my wheel and rev my engine. What a great sim you've built, Slighty Mad! When I assign other buttons they won't register when I try to drive either. This is the most frustrating \"gaming experience\" I've had in my entire life. Auto clutch - on, off - it doesn't make a difference at all. This is unreal. I'm using some of the best wheel and pedals that money can buy too.\nThe only thing that works is AUTOMATIC. I didn't buy a racing simulator to drive a damn automatic, SMS! I have a brand new Fanatec Wheel Base v2.5 with Porche 918 RSR Wheel. I'm using Thrustmaster pedals until my inverted Fanatecs arrive in March. I admired this game for months, and when I finally get to play it... nothing. I have to rate this one a massive thumbs down. I couldn't find any solutions online, because when I search for what is happeing tons and tons of results pop up from people having other problems with their controlers. Is this game just one massive bug?\nAssetto Corsa works just fine with my setup, so do other titles. PC2 is the only one that gives me troubles. Guess I'll keep playing those and try to get a refund on this. Come on, Slightly Mad. I used to wonder why people gave you so much crap on forums, now I know why. You've built a beautiful game. The problem is that it doesn't work. This is the first and last time I'll let you trick me into taking my money.", "hours": 0.8, "username": "Nitro Knight", "products": 30, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "378860", "page": 8, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2018-01-02", "text": "10/10 I truly loved this game, only played it an hour, I don't own a driving wheel but I enjoyed understanding the physics. This is an amazing racing sim. BUT! the only thing I have to complain about, it's not supported for Windows Mixed Reality just yet, so the game kept crashing on me multiple times, and I had to return it until that gets sorted. But don't let that stop you from playing Project Cars 2, it's seriously 100% worth the purchase.", "hours": 1.4, "user_id": "76561197967407966", "username": "[LAW]Numix", "products": 45, "early_access": false}
